title: samilson double fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk thoroughly with spoon in large saucepan (3-quart or larger).
Add salt, corn syrup and chocolate.
Stir carefully.
Butter inside rim of pot to prevent overflow when cooking.
Cook slowly on top of stove until soft ball stage, about 230° on candy thermometer, while stirring occasionally. Remove from stove, add butter and vanilla.
Cool to 160°, then beat in pot with mixer.
Add a few drops of milk if mixture becomes too thick to pour.
Beat extremely well.
Pour into buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cut when just about cool.

title: kolbassi bake
directions: Cut kolbassi in 1 1/2-inch pieces and cook for 5 minutes. Remove from water.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan and add other ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chili tacos
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add green pepper, onion and garlic.
Cook over medium heat until meat is brown and vegetables are tender. Drain off fat and liquid.
Stir in seasonings, corn, hot pepper sauce, tomato sauce and refried beans.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir 2 or 3 times.
Serve with chips as a dip, or fill pita pockets and eat as a sandwich.

title: country tea room pastry
directions: Blend flour, sugar and salt.

Cut in Crisco while particles are the size of peas. Beat egg. Blend in vinegar and water. Sprinkle over flour mixture, a tablespoon at a time, tossing with fork to mix. Gather dough together with fingers so it cleans the bowl. Chill before rolling. Makes two 9-inch 2 crust pies and one 9-inch pie shell.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs; add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix lightly, then beat well.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan (greased) or two (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken corn pie
directions: Line pan with crust and layer ingredients.
Begin with corn, followed by a layer of cooked, diced potatoes, layer of chicken and a layer of hard-boiled eggs.
Keep going until pan is filled. Season to taste.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk; boil one minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix oatmeal and cocoa. Pour hot mixture over oatmeal and cocoa.
Mix well and drop on wax paper to cool.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a large skillet, fry bacon until crisp. Set aside. Drain fat from pan.
In the same pan, cook and stir ground beef, onion and celery until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water. Stir bouillon and remaining ingredients into meat mixture.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Crumble bacon and sprinkle over beans.

title: potato and mushroom salad(makes about 5 cups)
directions: In shallow dish, combine potatoes, mushrooms, celery and onions.
In small bowl or jar, mix remaining ingredients; pour over potato mixture.
Cover; refrigerate 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: french toast
directions: Soak slices of day old bread in a little lukewarm milk, sweetened with a few tablespoons of sugar and flavored with a few drops of vanilla.
Beat eggs. Dip soaked bread into beaten eggs, then in flour. Shake off excess flour.
Fry in butter on both sides. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: onion 'n potato omelet
directions: In medium skillet, melt butter and cook potatoes until tender. In a large bowl, beat onion soup mix, eggs and milk. Add egg mixture into skillet. Cook, covered, over low heat for 25 minutes or until almost set. Top with cheese.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: fire station chicken
directions: Cut chicken breasts in pieces and cook on low heat for 4 to 5 minutes with salt and pepper in butter.
Add marmalade, grapes and oranges.
Mix lemon juice, cornstarch and dry mustard.
Add to chicken; cover and simmer for about 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: baked carrots with apples and raisins
directions: Put alternate layers of carrots, apples and raisins in a buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and a little salt.
Bake at 350° until apples are done.

title: stuffed fresh ham
directions: Put ham into a roasting pan and surround with water.
Cook in a 400° oven for about 2 hours.
Remove.
Strip sausage meat from casings and stuff pocket of ham with sausage meat.
Add more water to pan, if needed.
Return to oven until ham is cooked, about 1 hour longer or until meat is no longer pink.
When ham is done, drain off juice from pan and put into a can or pot.
Place in refrigerator for 1/2 hour.
Remove the fat that has risen to the top.
Use juice to make pork gravy.

title: baked rice pudding
directions: In heavy, medium pan, bring 2 cups milk, rice and raisins to boiling. Reduce heat. Cover and cook over very low heat about 15 minutes or until tender. Remove from heat. Stir in margarine until melted.

title: italian beef for sandwiches
directions: Cook 24 hours in crock-pot on low.
Separate with fork.

title: salmon burgers
directions: Drain salmon.
Remove and discard skin.
Mash salmon with bones.
Add onion, egg substitute, bread crumbs, mustard and hot pepper sauce; mix thoroughly.
Form into patties.
Brush burgers with oil and grill over hot coals, turning once, until nicely browned and heated through, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use square baking dish.
Put all in baking dish; cover with Saran Wrap.
Bake on High in microwave for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: beet preserves
directions: Cook whole beets until tender, in boiling water for about 30 minutes.
Let cool; peel and dice.
Combine diced beets, sugar and ginger in medium saucepan and cook over medium-low heat for 30 minutes.
Add chopped lemon and continue cooking until slightly thickened, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking, about 30 minutes.
Stir in almonds.
Transfer to jars with tight-fitting lids and seal.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, 1 egg and melted butter.
Batter will be stiff.
Pour in greased pan. Blend cream cheese, 2 eggs and confectioners sugar.
Pour over batter.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: hamburger pot-pie
directions: Place hamburger in medium size saucepan.
Cover with water; cook while you are dicing onion and celery, after which you add to hamburger and continue cooking.
Dice potatoes; add to mixture, cooking only until potatoes are half done.
Pour into baking dish and place your favorite pie crust on top.
Cut slits in dough. Bake in a 375° oven until crust is nicely browned, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: crispy baked fish
directions: Wash and dry fillets and season with the salt and pepper.
Dip in the oil and drain.
Coat with corn flake crumbs.
Arrange in a lightly oiled or Pam sprayed baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until fish flakes when tested.
Serves 4.

title: peanutty date bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together peanut butter, shortening and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla. Beat until light and fluffy.

title: apricot banana nut bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together, add apricot and nuts. Combine remaining ingredients, add to dry ingredients, stirring just Until Well Blended.
(Note:
Less sugar may be added.)
Turn into greased (wax paper lined) loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
(Test with a toothpick--may not take 1 full hour.) Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Turn out to cool on wire rack.
This recipe may be doubled.

title: pineapple cheese balls
directions: Mix cream cheese, pineapple, bell pepper, onion and salt. Form 2 balls and chill.
Roll in nuts.
Enjoy!

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix dressing mix with melted butter.
Put 1/2 mixture in bottom of pan.
Add squash mixture; then add other half of dressing mix on top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: sweet summer snack
directions: Melt morsels in separate microwavable cups, 1 cup for chocolate, 1 cup for white chocolate, or if assorted colors, divide colors into separate cups.
Melt in microwave until smooth, 1 to 2 minutes on High.
Immediately dip strawberries in melted sauce. Place on a plate.
Store in refrigerator for 1 to 2 hours.
Enjoy.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Pour off water from yams.
Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook in middle of rack.
Cook for 20 minutes, then check.
It sometimes takes 30 minutes.
Leave soft in middle so it won't be dry.

title: cowboy cornbread
directions: Add cream-style corn to cornbread mixture and set aside. Brown hamburger meat, drain and add onion, salt and pepper.
Add jalapeno pepper.
Pour half of the cornbread mixture in a hot greased pan, then add the meat and onion.
Top with cheese and then pour the rest of the cornbread mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Let set 15 minutes before serving.

title: sweet peanut treats
directions: In the top of a double boiler, over simmering water, melt chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and peanut butter.
Stir until smooth.
Spread half into a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Chill until firm.
Meanwhile, in a saucepan, bring butter, milk and pudding mix to a boil.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add confectioners sugar and beat until smooth.
Spread over chocolate mixture in pan.
Stir peanuts into remaining chocolate mixture; mix well.
Carefully spread over pudding layer. Refrigerate.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Yields 10 dozen.

title: sausage mushroom breakfast casserole
directions: Spread croutons in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Set aside.
Cook sausage until browned, stirring to crumble; drain well.
Sprinkle sausage over croutons.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken with a little salt until tender (keep broth).

title: simple southern fried chicken
directions: Season chicken pieces with seasoned salt and garlic.
Roll chicken in flour until covered.
Shake off excess flour.
Sprinkle with additional seasonings.
Fry chicken in vegetable oil in frying pan.
Begin with oil very hot and then reduce the heat later.
This seals in the juices and flavor then cooks it.

title: mexican bread
directions: Mix all ingredients to make batter.
Pour batter into greased iron skillet.
Bake at 450° until done.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Combine tomatoes, half and half, milk and onion in sauce mix. Heat gently.
Do not boil.
Stir in soda.
Add salt, pepper and butter.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: south-of-the-border layered dip
directions: Layer on large platter.

title: john's world famous pasta salad
directions: Drop the noodles into boiling water and boil for exactly 15 minutes.
Drain in colander, then run under cold water to stop the cooking.
Slice and dice the onion, tomatoes and cucumbers.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine ingredients. Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: pecan pie(my grandmother, mrs. blick's, recipe)
directions: Mix, by hand, all ingredients as listed.
Pour into unbaked 10-inch pie shell.
Start in 375° oven and bake for 15 minutes. Turn oven down to 300° and bake for 45 minutes.
The pie should be firm in the middle when it is done.

title: chicken soup-stew
directions: Boil chickens and bacon in water until tender.
Remove from heat; cool, skin and chop chicken in large bite size pieces.
Store chicken in refrigerator.
Skim fat from broth and add carrots, onions, beans, corn, potatoes and tomatoes.
Cook vegetables until tender.
Parboil celery in a separate pan in 1/2 cup water and then add to cooked vegetables, chopped chicken and pepper.
Adjust seasoning.
Add evaporated milk just before serving and heat but do not boil.
Serve in soup bowls with hot crusty French bread.
Makes a large pot and can be frozen.

title: simple meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven at 375°.
Combine all ingredients.
Form into a loaf.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Drain fast.
Top with additional catsup and bake another 5 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Place apple slices in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake for 30 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is golden brown.
Serve with ice cream.

title: cottage cheese roast(vegetarian dish)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a greased baking dish. Bake 35-40 minutes at 350 degrees until firm in center.

title: zucchini pie
directions: In skillet, cook zucchini, onion and garlic until tender. Stir in parsley and seasonings. In large bowl, blend eggs and cheese. Stir in vegetables. Separate dough into 8 triangles. Place in ungreased 10-inch pie pan; press over bottom and up sides to form crust. Spread crust with mustard. Pour vegetable mix evenly into crust. Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes. If crust browns too quickly, cover with foil.

title: jane's italian dressing
directions: Put mixture in quart jar and finish filling with water until full.
Pour from jar into pan and bring mixture to boil.
Add the 1 tablespoon cornstarch (add water to the tablespoon of cornstarch until milky like and then put in).
Boil all until clear.

title: walnut jewel salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in hot water.
Drain pineapple, saving syrup.
Combine syrup and lemon juice; add enough cold water to measure 1 2/3 cups liquid.
Add this to gelatin mixture. Chill until mixture begins to thicken slightly.
Fold in walnuts, celery, cranberries, crushed pineapple and chopped apples.
Turn into oiled 1 1/2-quart mold and chill until firm, at least 4 hours.
Unmold on lettuce leaves.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt together and add to rhubarb.
Beat eggs and mix them in.
Pour into crust and dot with butter.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for about 1/2 hour longer.

title: potato omelet
directions: Peel potatoes and slice thinly.
Rinse in cold water and dry. Salt and pepper.
Saute onion in oil over low heat until lightly browned.
Add sweet pepper and potatoes about halfway through cooking.
Drain and save mixture.
Wipe pan with paper towel.
Add butter and melt.

title: freezer pecan cookies
directions: Mix as given.
Divide dough in half. Make into long rolls. Wrap in foil and freeze until ready to use.
Slice partially thawed in dough.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: champion chili
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer 1 hour.
Serve.

title: mam-ma's blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream softened butter and sugar in electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time; whip well in between at high speed.
Sift flour with spices and salt.
Add soda to buttermilk and stir well.
Fold in flour, mixing alternately with buttermilk mixture.
Add wine. Lastly, mix in pecans and blackberry jam.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) well-greased and floured pans.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes. At 30 minutes, test with straw, when straw is clean, remove from oven.
Cool in pans for 5 minutes.
Invert on cake rack and leave pans over cake for 10 minutes more.
This insures a moist cake.

title: fat free apple cake
directions: Combine sugar, applesauce, corn syrup and Egg Beaters.
Mix well.
Add flour, spices and vanilla.
Mix until combined; stir in apples.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, lard and salt with a pastry blender until it is crumbly.
Add remaining ingredients and blend.
Do not overwork or handle dough excessively.
Roll out on floured surface and put in pie pans.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Put warm water in warm bowl; add yeast and sugar.
Let work. Add salt, egg, 1/4 cup butter and 3 cups flour; mix well with wooden spoon or electric mixer at medium speed.
Beat very hard 2 minutes or until smooth.
Gradually add 1 cup flour, beating well after each addition.
Work in remaining 2 cups flour by hand if necessary.
Knead.
Place in greased bowl.
Brush with grease and let rise in refrigerator about 2 hours or until double.
Punch down.
Refrigerate up to 3 days; punch down each day.
Remove from refrigerator; punch, shape and place on greased cookie sheet. Brush with butter; let rise in warm place.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: cold vegetable medley salad
directions: Combine peas, corn, artichokes, onion and green pepper.
Add dressing.
Just before serving, stir in tomato and lettuce.
Top with bacon and croutons.
Leftover salad will keep for several days in refrigerator.

title: apple-walnut cake
directions: Beat together brown sugar, butter and vanilla at medium speed on electric mixer, about 3 minutes or until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add combined flour, cornmeal, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg alternately with sour cream, mixing well after each addition.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Spoon into well-greased 9-cup Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Ice with Browned Butter Icing.

title: mix pickle dressing
directions: Mix the ingredients thoroughly and cook until thick.
Stir in the pickles.
Heat thoroughly.
Empty into glass jars.
Stand away until needed.

title: judith c. michael's easy icing
directions: Combine flour and milk.
Cook until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
Let cool.
In mixer bowl, combine sugar, oleo, shortening and flavoring.
Mix well.
Add cooled flour mixture and beat until the consistency of whipped cream.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Mix together and bake in 9 x 13-inch glass dish at 300° for 2 hours.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Saute hamburger, pepper and onion with celery and garlic salt. Drain off liquid.
Mix all other ingredients and bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: diane's banana cake with sour cream filling
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch round pans.

title: vodka pasta cream
directions: In frying pan, add olive oil and Prosciutto; brown.
Add onions, mushrooms and garlic; saute lightly.
Use 1/4 cup vodka to deglaze pan.
Once deglazed, add crushed tomatoes, heavy cream, parsley, basil, salt and pepper.
Bring sauce to boil, then reduce flame.
Add remaining vodka.
Simmer for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add peas; cook 5 minutes more.
In large bowl, toss drained rigatoni with sauce and grated cheese.

title: "simply good" soup
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add onion, vegetables and soup.
Simmer for a few minutes until flavors mix.
Serve with a salad or fruit and hot cornbread for a complete meal.

title: hunter stewwaterford, michigan
directions: Cook pheasant, quail, venison and fish until tender.
Cut into bite size pieces and combine all ingredients in large crock pot. Cover with water and cook until done.
4 to 5 hours.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: mom's potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes.
When done, drain and add remaining ingredients.
If not quite sweet enough, I always add 1 to 2 tablespoons sugar.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Oat Flour:
Place 1 cup Quaker oats in blender or food processor.
Cover and blend about 1 minute, stopping blender occasionally to stir oats.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order listed.
Cover.
Mix right before serving.
Can be made day ahead.

title: mennonite lemonade
directions: Wash lemons and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Place slices in a stainless steel bowl and add sugar.
Grind down the lemon slices to release the juice by using a wooden spoon or potato masher. Let sit for 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
In several bunches, squeeze the lemon slices hard with your hands to extract all the juice.
Mix in the quart of ice water.
(You may add a little more water if desired.) Transfer to a pitcher and chill in the refrigerator or add a tray of ice cubes and serve right away. Garnish each glass with a sprig of mint, if desired.

title: honey glazed peas
directions: Cook peas according to directions.
Add remaining ingredients; stir and serve immediately.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and mix well.
Slowly add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in greased and floured pan (10 x 14-inch) for 45 to 60 minutes until well done.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Heat oil in electric skillet to 375°.
Beat milk with egg. Blend dry ingredients and gradually add the milk mixture, beating constantly, until batter is smooth.
Holding your finger over the bottom of a funnel, fill funnel with batter.
Holding funnel as near surface of oil as possible, remove finger and drop batter into hot oil, using a circular movement from center outward to form a spiral cake about 3 inches in diameter.
Fry until puffy and golden brown, turning once.
Remove and place on paper towels. Sift powdered sugar on top.

title: hershey's chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, flour, syrup and vanilla flavoring.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Add milk, onion and bacon drippings.	Spread batter evenly 1/2-inch thick on a flat surface with pancake spatula.
Using a knife, push a 1/2-inch wide "finger" of batter off the pancake spatula and into the hot oil.
As hush puppies float, turn them.
Keep repeating until all the batter is used.
Drain on a paper towel.

title: mexican spoon bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese and chilies. Grease casserole dish. Pour half mixture in dish. Spread with chilies and half of cheese. Add remaining mix and sprinkle remaining cheese over top. Bake 45 minutes at 400°.

title: s & w margarita chicken
directions: Brush chicken with a mixture of the oil, lime juice and honey. Roll chicken in the tortilla crumbs to coat.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Puree tomatoes and cilantro. Remove chicken from oven.
Pour on puree.
Top with cheese. Return to oven until cheese melts.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate dip for fruit
directions: Melt ingredients together in microwave or in small crock-pot. Serve warm with fresh bananas, apples, strawberries, pineapple, marshmallows and/or chocolate chip cookies.

title: never fail chocolate icing
directions: Mix ingredients in saucepan.
Let come to rolling boil.
Boil one minute.
Set off to cool.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Set saucepan in large pan of cold water.
Beat 3 or 4 minutes or until right consistency to spread.
If cools too quickly, add small amount of milk to thin.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour the boiling water over the oatmeal and let stand 20 minutes until cool. Cream together the sugars, margarine and eggs. Sift the flour, cinnamon, soda and salt together.
Add all together and add the vanilla; beat.
Bake in loaf or 13 x 9-inch pan for 35 minutes in a
325° or 350° oven.

title: florida salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp. Drain on absorbent paper towels. Saute onions in 3 tablespoons bacon drippings. Combine onion, cabbage, tomatoes, green pepper, salt and pepper in a Dutch oven. Cover and cook over medium-low heat for 15 minutes or until crisp-tender. Do not add water. Add soy sauce, stirring until blended.
Crumble bacon. Stir into cabbage mixture. This is equally as good hot or cold, and even better the second day! Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).
Lightly grease 2 baking sheets. In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar and baking powder; stir well.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal.
Add 2 cups buttermilk and mix just to moisten.
Roll out dough to 1-inch thick and cut into biscuits.
Place biscuits on prepared baking sheets; brush tops with remaining 1/4 cup buttermilk.
Bake in preheated oven for 15 minutes or until golden. Serves 12.

title: honey-lemon fruit salad
directions: Combine pineapple chunks, pears and oranges in a bowl; toss gently and set aside.
Combine 2 tablespoons of the pineapple juice and the remaining ingredients in a jar.
Cover tightly and shake vigorously.
Pour over fruit and toss gently.
Cover and chill up to 24 hours.
Serves about 10.

title: western pate
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line bottom of loaf pan crosswise with bacon slices, bringing bacon up sides and over edge of pan (reserve any remaining bacon slices).
Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly.
Spoon into pan, being careful not to disturb bacon. Smooth top.
Fold bacon ends over top of meat mixture.
Place remaining slices of bacon lengthwise on top.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until done; drain carefully, leaving pate in pan.
Let stand, uncovered, 1 hour before serving.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans.
Put pecans in bottom of unbaked pie shell.
Pour mixture over nuts.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until filling appears to be set.

title: nacho rounds
directions: Arrange chips on two (10-inch) microwave proof serving platters.
Cover each with cheese, chilies and olives.
Use Defrost cycle and cook, one plate at a time, for 4 to 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Add 1/2 stick margarine and cubed Velveeta cheese.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Crush Ritz crackers and add remaining 1/2 stick margarine, melted.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until browned. Serve hot.
Yields 8 servings.

title: hurry up yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix in Bisquick and beat vigorously.
Turn dough on board well dusted with Bisquick and knead until smooth, about 20 times.
Shape as desired.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Cover with cloth.
Let rise in warm place free from draft, about 1 hour.
Heat oven to 400° (moderately hot).
Bake 10 to 15 minutes, until golden brown. Brush with oleo.
Makes 16 rolls.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, flour and salt.
Mix.
Add buttermilk mixture and beat.
Mix bananas and nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray or wipe an 8 x 11 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish with vegetable oil.
In the blender, place the Mozzarella, Asiago and 1/2 the Parmesan; blend until smooth. Place the pasta on a large bowl.
Add the cheese mixture; toss until well coated.
Season with cayenne, salt and pepper to taste. Place the cooked pasta in the baking dish; top with the bread crumbs and remaining Parmesan.
Place in the oven; bake until bubbly, 20 to 25 minutes.
Place under the broiler for 3 to 4 minutes, until the top is golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: sugarless sweet bread
directions: Boil raisins, dates and prunes for 5 minutes in 1 cup water; cool.
Add all ingredients with cooled fruit and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Stir all together and cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: lemon bush
directions: Mix together margarine, flour and walnuts and press into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix together cream cheese and sugar; fold in Cool Whip and spread on top of cool crust.
Mix pudding and spread on top of filling.
When pudding has set, spread Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with finely chopped nuts.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: ham and pasta bake
directions: Combine flour, onions, salt, mustard and pepper in saucepan and add milk.
Stir until blended.
Bring to a boil and cook 2 minutes or until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in broccoli.
Add macaroni, ham and cheese.
Place in 2 quart casserole.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar, water and salt.
Cook until thick and clear, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Continue beating while slowly pouring cooked mixture into egg whites.
Beat 5 minutes. Cover cooled filling in pie shell with meringue, sealing edges to crust.
Bake in 450° oven for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: pecan frosting
directions: Cook sugar and milk over low heat for about 10 or 15 minutes or until a light syrupy feel.
Remove from heat and stir in ground pecans and 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: rice krispie treats
directions: Melt the marshmallows and butter in pan over medium heat. Remove from heat and add Rice Krispies gradually.
Pour into a pre-greased 12 x 22-inch pan and flatten.
Let cool and eat.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna 12 to 15 minutes or until tender; drain.
In large skillet, combine ground beef, onion and garlic.
Cook until beef is brown; drain.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, oregano and pepper.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
In large shallow buttered baking dish, layer 1/3 each lasagna, meat sauce, Ricotta and Mozzarella cheeses.
Repeat layers.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° until hot, about 45 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: apple cheese crisp
directions: Arrange apples in buttered baking dish.
Add water.
Combine sugar, flour, salt and cinnamon.
Cut
margarine in with pastry blender until mixture is consistency of corn meal.
Lightly stir in cheese.
Cover apples with this mixture and bake 35 to 40 minutes in 450° oven.

title: tomato pie
directions: Bake pie crust at 425° for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven; reduce heat to 400°.
Cover bottom of pie crust with tomato slices; sprinkle with salt, pepper, basil and chives.
Combine mayo and cheese; spread evenly over top, making sure to seal the edges of the pie crust completely.
Bake 35 minutes.

title: carrot-peanut apple mix
directions: Wash and scrape carrots; grate coarsely.
Add chopped peanuts, raisins and apple.
Toss with mayonnaise.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop into skillet with 1-inch or less hot oil.
Brown each side.
Makes 8 to 10 patties.

title: hush puppies
directions: Stir together corn meal, flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in egg, onion and enough milk to make a batter stiff enough to drop, not pour.
Drop by level tablespoon, without crowding, into 375° oil.
Cook for 3 or 4 minutes until brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: twelve cup salad
directions: Mix all together.
Let chill to meld flavors.

title: old fashioned chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cornmeal, mix well. Add butter and mix. Add beaten eggs - mix well. Add buttermilk and vanilla, mix until well blended. Pour mixture into an unbaked pastry shell and bake

in a preheated oven @ 425° for 10 minutes. Reduce temp. to 325° and bake 30 minutes longer. When pie starts to brown, cover with a sheet of aluminum foil to prevent deep browning or burning. Pie is done when inserted knife comes out clean. Filling makes 2 - 9-inch pies or 1 - 8-inch pie and 8 tart shells.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt margarine.
Add pretzels and 3 tablespoons of sugar. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: homemade pizza bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; stir in rest of ingredients. Beat vigorously and let rest 5 minutes. Divide dough in 2 parts and spread or roll on 12-inch pizza pan (greased and floured).
Or use all of the dough for deep dish.
Top with favorite pizza sauce, (Pastorelli) meat, onions, peppers and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 425° for about 18 minutes.
Makes 2 (12-inch) pizzas.

title: cajun cheese
directions: Mix cheese, onion, mayonnaise and red pepper.
Heat in serving dish in microwave on High for approximately 35 seconds or until cheese is just melted.
After removing from microwave, spoon raspberry preserves over top.
Serve hot with crackers or bagel chips.

title: spoon bread
directions: Combine all ingredients, folding muffin mix last.
Bake in 8 x 12-inch pan (greased) for 40 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.

title: pizza surprise
directions: Combine rice, eggs and 1 cup cheese.
Press firmly into two 9-inch pie pans.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Spread Quick Tomato Sauce evenly
over rice crust.
Top with remaining cheese. Bake 10 minutes.

title: noodle kugel
directions: Note:
The more fruit, the fluffier the noodles.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into crusts.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat
eggs
and mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sauerkraut soup
directions: In a large saucepan or Dutch oven, combine sausage, potatoes, onions, carrots and chicken broth; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 30 minutes, until potatoes are tender.
Add sauerkraut and tomato paste; mix well.
Return to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 30 minutes longer.
If a thinner soup is desired, add additional water or chicken broth.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: pam's vegetable soup
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil in a large soup pot.
Reduce heat to medium/medium-low and let cook until all ingredients are well done, stirring occasionally.

title: sausage-potato casserole
directions: Cook onions and butter until tender.
Stir in soup and milk and heat.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan combine potatoes, peppers and pimento.
Slice sausages and add to potatoes and pour soup over. Top with rest of sausages and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Saute onions; add to all ingredients except tortillas and cheese.
Bring to boiling point.
In large greased casserole, place 1/3 tortillas, 1/3 mixture and 1/3 cheese.
Repeat 2 layers.
Bake until bubbly.

title: gumdrop cake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add brown sugar and water.
Sift flour, salt and cinnamon.
Add to egg mixture.
Add gumdrops and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: jello pudding
directions: Mix jello with 1 1/2 cups hot water and 2 cups cold water. Stir in pineapple.
Slice bananas and mix together.
Let jel completely.

title: pull-apart cinnamon rolls
directions: Roll frozen rolls in melted margarine, then in sugar cinnamon mixture.
Place in a greased Bundt pan.
Cover and let rise overnight (will overflow the Bundt pan).
In the morning, replace any rolls that have overflowed in the Bundt pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.

title: mother's dutch apple pie
directions: Layer half thin sliced apples in pie plate.
Sprinkle with half of above ingredients.
Add another layer of apples and remaining dry ingredients.
Strip with crust and dot
with butter. Bake 1 hour @ 350 degrees.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender. Drain and place in buttered casserole.
Cover with cheese. Add the soup and chicken pieces. Cover with slightly crushed potato chips and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry freezer jam
directions: Combine berries and pectin.
Let stand 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add sugar and stir for 3 minutes.
Quickly spoon into freezer containers or hot sterilized jars.
Leave 1/2-inch headspace.
Cover at once with plastic or metal lids and screw-on bands.
Let stand at room temperature 24 hours.
Freeze.
Yields 7 1/2 pints.
May store in refrigerator for 3 weeks.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and cornstarch; add hot water.
Place in top of double boiler, bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Cook 2 or 3 minutes until thick.
Remove and cool slightly; add margarine or butter.
Keep warm.

title: fluffy potato casserole
directions: Put potatoes in a large bowl.
Add cream cheese, onion, eggs and flour.
Beat at medium speed until blended.
Put on high speed and beat until light and fluffy.
Add salt and pepper.
Spoon into a greased 9-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle potato chips atop potatoes.
With a knife, poke crumbs into potato mixture.
Bake, uncovered, for 35 minutes in a 300° oven.

title: crispy cereal cookies
directions: Boil Karo syrup, sugar and peanut butter together for 5 minutes.
Stir in the cereal.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix altogether and let stand 2 hours.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: In glass bowl, layer fruit. Combine cheese, lemon juice and lemon peel until smooth. Beat whipping cream until soft peaks form and add sugar until stiff peaks form. Fold into cheese mix and chill. Pour on top of fruit and sprinkle with pecans, if desired, and chill before serving.

title: turkey breakfast sausage
directions: Mix turkey, egg white, sage, marjoram, thyme, summer savory and pepper together in large bowl.
Shape into patties and chill at least 1 hour (makes about 12 patties).
Spray skillet with vegetable cooking spray.
Place skillet over medium-high heat until hot.
Place patties in skillet; cook 5 minutes on each side until done.
Makes 12 servings, 1 patty per serving.

title: breakfast before
directions: Fry sausage until crumbled.
Drain and pour into casserole dish.
Mix milk, eggs, salt and dry mustard.
Pour on top of sausage.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Add cheese.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Line cookie sheet (10 x 15-inches) with wax paper.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour batter on cookie sheet and spread out evenly.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn on tea towel and roll up like a jelly roll.
Let cool 30 minutes.
Unroll and spread with filling.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies and set aside.
Mix cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar and set aside.
Mix vanilla pudding, milk and Cool Whip and add to cream cheese mixture.
In a flower pot, place a layer of cookies.
Next, put a layer of cream cheese mixture; alternate until pot is full.
Finish off with a layer of cookies. Garnish with a flower of your choice.

title: baked zucchini
directions: Slice zucchini in 1/2-inch slices.
Place in a 2-quart baking dish with green peppers, onion and garlic.
Mix in green beans and tomatoes and top with dots of butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mud pie
directions: Crush Oreo cookies and melted butter in a food processor and place in a
9 x 13-inch pan. Smooth ice cream over crushed cookies, then freeze.
Melt butter and unsweetened chocolate together.
Add a dash of salt, sugar and milk.
Cook for 4 minutes.
Cool and spread over ice cream.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over the top, then freeze again.
Serve.

title: easy stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef quickly with mushrooms, onion and salt in large skillet, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream.
Stir water and bouillon cube.
Bring to a full boil. Stir in rice.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Peel apples and cut in half. Remove the core.
Wash and lay aside to drain.
Roll biscuits thin; place half apple, round side down, on biscuit and sprinkle cinnamon on flat side of apple.
Pull dough up around apple and place flat side down in pan of melted butter.
Dissolve sugar in warm water and slowly pour around dumplings.
(Do not pour on top of dumplings.) Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Baste dumplings after baking 20 minutes.
It is best to prepare all of the dumplings before putting in the pan of melted butter.

title: crispy potato wedges
directions: Cut each potato lengthwise into 8 wedges (24 wedges total). On an ungreased 15 x 10 x 2-inch baking pan, arrange wedges in a single layer, skin side down.

title: quick cooked spaghetti
directions: Brown meat in skillet.	Saute bell
pepper and onion in butter.
Cook spaghetti until tender; drain.
Mix all ingredients together in skillet, stirring as it simmers.
Serve hot.

title: baked corn
directions: Cook corn.
Beat eggs and milk.
Combine eggs, corn and milk with seasonings and 2 Tbsp. butter.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 1 1/2 qt. baking dish.
Mix crumbs and butter and sprinkle over corn.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes or until mixture is set.

title: grandma's turkey stuffing
directions: Mix ingredients with milk until soft.
This can also be poured into a baking dish and baked till apples are soft and tender.

title: old fashioned candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut lengthwise.
Place in large saucepan. Add sugar, butter and water.
Cover and boil rapidly for about 10 minutes.
Remove lid and allow to cook slowly until syrup is thick and potatoes are tender.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut dough in 1/8-inch slices (cheese cutter does nicely). Line a 14-inch pizza pan with slices, overlapping.
(I leave space between slices; try both.)
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: corn casserole
directions: Drain corn, mix with
sour cream, soup and onion.
Pour in buttered dish and
top
with
crushed
crackers
and melted margarine.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tater tot hot dog casserole
directions: Line Tater Tots in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add package of corn and cut up hot dogs.
Heat up soup and milk together and pour on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheese ball
directions: Allow cheeses to soften at room temperature.
Combine with remaining ingredients; blend until smooth.
Refrigerate about 30 minutes.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts, if desired. Serve as spread for crackers.
Yields about 3 cups of spread.

title: allison's frozen strawberry dessert
directions: Crust:
Mix first 4 ingredients.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until light brown.
Stir while baking.

title: millers pasta salad
directions: Mix all together and toss with dressing.

title: family favorite frosting
directions: Cook milk and flour until thick.
Set aside and cool.
Beat together sugar, margarine and vanilla with electric mixer.
Add milk and flour mixture and beat well.

title: christmas aroma(not for consumption)
directions: Place all ingredients in a large kettle and bring to a boil for several minutes.
Turn down to a simmer and allow house to fill with a wonderful Christmas aroma.
Keep mixture for days, adding water and stirring as needed.

title: pork roast
directions: Have meat market person loosen backbone of pork loin.

Place roast, fat side up, on rack in open roasting pan in center of oven. Roast in 325° oven for 2 to 3 hours or until meat thermometer which has been inserted in center of roast's thickest part (not touching bone) registers 170°.
In saucepan, combine applesauce, molasses, ginger and garlic over medium heat.
Brush pork every 10 minutes the last 30 minutes of cooking.
Serve pork with remaining applesauce.
The size of the roast will determine length of cooking time.

title: lemon pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order given, blending by hand.
Pour into 8-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake an additional 40 minutes or until pie is set and crust is brown.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt oleo in Corning Ware casserole.
Add onions, stir until cooked but not brown (use low heat).
Add rice and continue cooking and stirring until rice turns white.
Add consomme and bouillon, stir well.
Cover casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 300° to 325°.

title: new mexican cherry bombs(yields 24 appetizers)
directions: Slit each chili.
Remove seeds with a small spoon or knife and stuff chilies with pieces of cheese.
If necessary, insert a toothpick to hold chili together.
Dip each stuffed chili in flour, then egg, then in flour again.
Deep-fry at 350° or until chilies are golden brown.
Drain and serve.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook, drain, rinse and cool pasta.
Add vegetables; mix well. Combine milk, vinegar, mayonnaise, sugar, salt and black pepper together; add to pasta mixture, mixing well.
Chill 4 hours.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
When almost set, whip with mayonnaise, then fold in shrimp, pimento and chopped celery.

title: potatoes and onions au gratin
directions: In a large skillet, cook the onions with salt and pepper to taste in 6 tablespoons butter over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until they are golden.
Spoon half the onions into a buttered 4-quart gratin dish; cover them with the potato slices, then sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover the potatoes with the remaining onions; pour the cream over the mixture and sprinkle the mixture with the combined cheeses.
Dot the top with the remaining 6 tablespoons butter and bake the gratin in a preheated 400° oven for 30 minutes or until tender and golden brown.

title: marinated black-eyed peas
directions: Drain peas. Rinse with cold water. Drain well. Add celery and onion. Combine oil, vinegar, mayonnaise and cayenne. Mix well. Pour over peas. Stir gently. Chill in refrigerator several hours or overnight. At serving time, add tomato and salt if needed.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Peel and cube potatoes into microwave-safe bowl with lid. Cook on High 5 to 8 minutes or until done. Fry and drain bacon. Crumble. Saute onion in small amount of bacon fat until golden. Blend in flour and seasonings. Cook over low heat, stirring until smooth and bubbly. Remove from heat. Stir in water and vinegar. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil 1 minute. Carefully combine sauce, potatoes and bacon. Keep warm until ready to serve. Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Slice bananas and place on bottom of graham crust.
Mix lemon juice with condensed milk and pour mixture over bananas.
Drain pineapple and spread over the milk mixture.
Mix whipping cream with sugar and a few pecans.
Spread over pineapple and top with coconut and the rest of the pecans.
Place a few cherries on top and refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.
This recipe makes one pie.

title: fancy green beans
directions: Drain water from beans.
Add mushroom soup and half the onions.
Mix together.
Put rest of onions on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: "kota kapama" - greek stewed chicken
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces and sprinkle with lemon juice, cinnamon, salt and pepper.
Brown chicken in butter.
Mix tomato paste with water in large saucepan; bring to boil.
Reduce heat and place browned chicken in tomato.
Pour butter through strainer over chicken and tomato.
Add wine and cook about 1 hour until rice is tender.
This chicken is very good served with macaroni, rice or potatoes.

title: rice and cheese
directions: Cook rice in water (1/2 to 1 teaspoon salt). Bring rice to boil; cover and cook seventeen minutes or until done.
Layer in baking dish 1/2 of rice, 1/2 of sour cream mixed with green chilies and pimentos and 1/2 of grated cheese. Repeat layers. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: honey-cornmeal biscuits
directions: Roll and cut with cutter and bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: kielbasi pineapple casserole
directions: Bring kielbasi to boil for 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain.
Mix remaining ingredients together in large baking dish (press down). Put kielbasi in sauce.
Cover and bake at 350° to 375° for 45 minutes.
Remove cover the last 10 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for approximately 1 hour at 325°.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Cook in 4 1/2-quart Dutch oven.
Heat oil.
Add onion and brown.
Add paprika and chicken.
Stir to coat.
Add salt and pepper.
Cover with water.
Add pepper, tomato and celery.
Cover and cook 1 to 2 hours until chicken slides off bone.
Remove chicken, cool, debone and cut into small pieces.

title: low-fat lasagna
directions: In skillet, cook meat.
Add onion and garlic and cook until brown and onion tender.
Drain any fat.
Stir in next 7 ingredients, stirring often, for about 15 minutes.
Cook noodles (no oil) and drain.
Stir together egg, Ricotta or cottage cheese, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, parsley and pepper.

title: easy oatmeal candy
directions: Mix first four ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Mix in last three ingredients. Pour into container, let cool. Candy may be kept in the freezer.

title: marinated london broil
directions: Mix the wine, oil, soy sauce, oregano, marjoram and pepper. Place steak in a deep bowl; pour marinade over it.
Cover; chill at least 12 to 18 hours, turning meat once or twice.
(Much easier if you use the Tupperware marinating covered container and just turn over several times during the 12 to 18 hours).
(Or, you may use a large Ziploc bag to marinate steak in instead of bowl.)

title: cheesy potatoes(for the barbecue)
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towel and crumble. Peel and slice potatoes onto a large piece of double heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Add onions separated into rings.
Add bacon bits, cheese, salt, pepper and chervil and toss all together lightly. Dot with butter and drizzle bacon fat overall.
Wrap foil loosely around the potatoes making double folds to seal well.
Cook about 4 inches from hot coals for 1 hour or until tender, turning the package often.
Note:
Bake in oven at 400° for about the same time; if desired.
Serves 4.

title: quick bearnaise
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan with wine, vinegar, tarragon and onion.
Place yolks, lemon juice and cayenne in blender.
With machine running, add hot butter mixture slowly.
Will thicken. Yields 1 cup.

title: elephant stew
directions: Clean elephant thoroughly. Sprinkle with onions, garlic, celery, carrots, salt and pepper. Bake at 350° for 2 weeks in a deep pit.
This will serve up to 500 people.
If more are expected, you may add the rabbits, but use caution as most people do not like hare in their stew.

title: key lime pie
directions: In saucepan,
combine
1/2 cup sugar, gelatin and salt. Beat egg yolks,	lime
peel,
lime
juice and water until well blended. Stir
into
gelatin.
cook
and
stir
until mixture thickens slightly.
Remove from heat, stir in food coloring to tint green. Chill until partially set, stirring mix occasionally.
Beat egg whites
to	soft peaks. Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold lime mixture into whites, whip cream
to soft
peaks,
fold and chill until mix mounds.
Fill
into crumb
crust.
Garnish
with
chocolate shavings.

title: easy fried won ton
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Add water chestnuts, onions and egg. Put small amount on each wrapper and wrap tightly.
Fry in hot oil.

title: bacon wrapped chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Pound chicken with mallet on both sides. Salt and pepper to taste, then sprinkle with sage. According to the size of the chicken, wrap 1 or 2 slices of bacon tightly around each breast. Sprinkle with sage and place in baking dish. Repeat for each breast. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until chicken is brown and bacon crisp.

title: gugelhuff
directions: Cream the butter to consistency of mayo. Add sugar slowly, while continuing to cream. Beat until light and fluffy.

Beat in egg yolks, one at a time. Sift flour, salt and baking powder. Combine with milk and flavoring. Add flour mixture and milk alternately to butter mixture, stirring gently but thoroughly. Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry. Fold in thoroughly. Spoon into well-greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done. Cool in pan 10 minutes. Loosen cake gently around rim and tube.
Invert on cake rack. Cool and dust with confectioners sugar. Garnish with maraschino cherries, if desired.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix well, then drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.

title: saucepan chocolate brownie
directions: Melt oleo and chocolate in top of saucepan, stir in other ingredients.
Spread into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 300° until done.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients, except sauce, in a bowl, until well combined.
Form into golf ball size balls and microwave 3 to 5 minutes or until done all through.
Pour sauce in crock-pot and put on low.
Add meatballs to sauce and simmer all day, at least 5 or 6 hours.

title: brandy slush
directions: Bring water and sugar to boil; cool.
Boil 2 cups water, add tea bags for 15 minutes.
Combine tea and sugar water.
Add orange juice, lemonade and brandy.
Freeze.
Fill 1/4 of glass with slush and add 7-Up.

title: apple stuffing pork roast
directions: Cut steaks to serving size.
Spray with low-fat Pam on each side.
Sprinkle each side with seafood seasoning.
Place on broiler tray.
Cook maximum of 5 minutes on each side on broiler setting.
Serve with steamed rice and salad.
Top with favorite salsa or picante sauce.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix well and cover with waxed paper.
Let stand 8 to 10 hours. Punch down and divide into 3 equal parts.
Place in pans sprayed with Pam.
Brush tops with melted butter and cover with waxed paper.
Let rise 8 to 10 hours.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter. Add cooked broccoli, rice, soup, milk and Cheez Whiz. Bake in greased casserole 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: pesto
directions: Combine basil, garlic and walnuts in the bowl of a food processor or half the recipe and use a blender and chop.
For basil, I use my Sunbeam Oscar, then add to blender with other ingredients.
Leave the motor running and add the olive oil in a slow, steady stream.
Shut the motor off to add the cheese and a big pinch of salt.
Process briefly to combine, then ready to use. Makes 2 cups; enough to sauce 2 pounds of pasta.

title: crock-pot macaroni
directions: Mix macaroni with remaining ingredients and put in a crock-pot that has been greased with butter.
Sprinkle some on top.
Cook on low 3 1/2 to 4 hours.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Mix and pour on cream cheese layer. Chill. Allow to set before serving.

title: lo-cal meat loaf
directions: Place eggs, hamburger, onion, celery, dill pickle, parsley, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and 1 can tomato sauce in bowl; mix well.
Shape into loaf and place in shallow baking pan.
Mix remaining 1 can of tomato sauce, mustard, vinegar and honey in bowl.
Pour over loaf.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until done.

title: aunt fannie's fattin' chocolate pie(serves 8)
directions: Blend sugar, cocoa and 1 1/2 cups milk.
Cook about 15 minutes or until rolling boil has stopped and steady even boil develops. Add butter.
Blend flour with 1 cup milk and add to chocolate mixture.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick. Add 3 tablespoons of hot pudding to egg yolks.
Mix thoroughly, then add egg yolks to pudding.
Beat until eggs are thoroughly mixed.
Blend in vanilla.
Pour into 2 baked (8-inch) pie crusts and top with meringue.

title: pickled beets
directions: Heat all ingredients except beets, until boiling.
Add beets and let stand until using, in vinegar in refrigerator.

title: barn yard "cow pies"
directions: In a double boiler over simmering water, melt chocolate chips and shortening, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in raisins and almonds. Drop by tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper. Chill until ready to serve.
Yields 2 dozen "Cow Pies".

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream together butter or margarine and sugar.
Add flour and eggs.
Beat well and add buttermilk, vanilla and nutmeg.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix hash brown potatoes, margarine, salt, pepper, onions and chicken soup; add sour cream and cheese.
Pour mixture into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with crushed corn flakes mixed with melted margarine or bread crumbs and crushed potato chips and stuffing mix mixed with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and pour into buttered casserole.
Top with crushed crackers and butter mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate nut squares
directions: Blend eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Add chocolate and shortening.
Gradually add flour.
Mix until well blended. Pour into a greased pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lenten pirohi with potato filling
directions: Combine and work to make a smooth dough.
Add more or less flour as needed.
Set aside and cover with damp cloth.
Pare and cut up potatoes.
Boil.
When done, mash them with a little of the water they cooked in and add chopped, sauteed onions which were browned in a little oil.
Roll out dough, cut into squares and fill with mashed potato mixture.
Moisten edges of dough with water, fold over and pinch firmly together to seal tightly.
Drop pirohi a few at a time into boiling, salted water.
Cook about 5 minutes or until they float to the top.
Lift out of the pan with slotted spoon and drain well in colander.
Saute some onions in oil and pour over pirohi before serving.

title: quick spinach supreme
directions: Cook spinach as directed on package.
Blend soup, seasoned salt, onion and milk.
Combine with spinach and mix well.
Place in buttered casserole and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken delight
directions: Arrange the Chicken Breasts in an oblong baking dish, place Swiss Cheese on top, pour Chicken soup that has been diluted with cooking sherry over the swiss cheese, sprinkle
the crumble stuffing on top and drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 325 degrees for 1- 1/2 hours.

title: small quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Pour into small greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield: 40 small quiche.

title: sweden house bread pudding
directions: Cut crusts from bread and discard.

Toast bread lightly on both sides; spread with butter and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Form bread into 3 sandwiches (buttered and sugared sides together). Cut each sandwich into finger shaped pieces, approx. in quarters. Arrange pieces in well buttered 8-inch square baking dish. Sprinkle with brown sugar and raisins.
In small bowl, combine eggs, sugar, milk and vanilla beat until well mixed and pour over bread pieces.
Place baking dish in pan containing one inch of hot water.
Bake at 375° about 40 to 45 minutes, until custard is set. Serve warm with sweet whipped cream or vanilla ice cream if desired.
Makes about six servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook over low heat until thickened. Pour over beef, pork or chicken.

title: italian chicken and bric
directions: Coat large skillet with cooking spray.
Saute chicken until lightly browned.
Add zucchini.
Cook until tender-crisp.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes or until heated through.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix dry cake mix, butter and 1 egg.
Mix by hand.
Do not use cake mix directions.
Spread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the rest of the ingredients and put all of it over your first mixture.

title: enchilada sauce for chicken or beef enchiladas
directions: Saute onion and garlic in margarine or oil.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 30 minutes or 45 minutes.
Pour over enchiladas.
Just before baking, top with cheese.
I use this sauce for chicken or beef enchiladas and for Spanish rice.
Rice recipe is as follows:

title: stuffing or dressing mix
directions: Take old bread (not molded) and dry it in a 200° oven for about 10 to 15 minutes.
Crumble bread into crumbs.
To dry celery leaves, place leaves from stalks of celery into a pie pan and dry in a 200° oven for about 15 minutes until crumbly.

title: coney island hot dogs
directions: Cook beef and onion in skillet on medium heat, stirring often until beef is browned.
Add tomato sauce, seasonings and wieners. Bring to a boil.
Turn down heat.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll dough into finger shapes.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until brown. Roll in confectioners sugar while hot.

title: sausage brunch bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a square baking dish (8 x 8 x 2-inches).
Cook sausage until brown and drain.
Mix baking mix, milk and eggs in bowl with fork until batter is uniform color. (Batter will be lumpy.)
Stir in sausage and remaining ingredients, except tomato.
Bake immediately or cover and refrigerate up to 24 hours.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 to 50 minutes.
Garnish with tomato.
Yields 6 servings.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain off fat.
Add green chilies.
Mix together soup and milk. Alternate layers of chips, meat and soup mixture.
Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese melts or casserole is hot through.

title: tofu patties
directions: Mix in rice and oats.
Form into patties on lightly oiled cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes on the first side; flip patties, 20 minutes on the second side.

title: zucchini squash relish
directions: Bring to boil; add the first ingredients and cook 25 minutes and can.
Makes 4 pints.

title: macho nacho
directions: Spoon chili over chips.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Heat in microwave oven or broil until cheese melts (1 to 2 minutes).

title: oven fried eggplant
directions: Mix bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Peel eggplant, slice and spread both sides with mayonnaise.
Dredge in bread crumbs. Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.

title: horseradish cheese ball
directions: In food processor, blend 2 cheeses.
Add horseradish and butter briefly blending.
Spoon into bowl and refrigerate about 3 hours until stiff.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt, baking powder and brown sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Mix together the vinegar and egg; add water to fill 1 cup.
Makes 4 single crusts.
Dough may be frozen until ready to use.

title: venison in a crock-pot
directions: In an iron skillet, heat the vegetable oil.
Dip the steaks in the flour, salt and pepper and the seasoning salt..
Brown on both sides, then transfer to the crock-pot.
Pour both kinds of soup over the meat and 1 can of water.
Cook approximately 1 1/2 hours. I usually have to make more gravy from the drippings in the skillet to pour over at the end of cooking time.
"The poor dogs get no scraps when I cook this meal."

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; stir into sliced apples. Pour into a 9 x 9-inch cake pan.
Combine the last 3 ingredients by mixing the flour and sugar.
Cut in butter until crumbly. Sprinkle mixture over apples.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until done.

title: noodles alfredo
directions: Cook noodles as directed; drain.
Over low heat melt butter and cream in a saucepan.
Stir in cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
Reduce heat to low.
Put noodles in serving dish.
Pour in sauce and stir gently until noodles are coated.

title: icebox bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over the cereals and wheat germ.
Next, mix in extra large bowl the oil, sugar and eggs.
Sift the flour, soda and salt together.
Add alternately buttermilk with second and third mixtures.
Store in refrigerator in covered container not more than 6 weeks.
Bake in greased muffin pans at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 60 muffins.

title: apple brandy brew
directions: Combine ingredients in slow cooking pot.
Cover and heat on low for 3 to 4 hours.
Serve hot.

title: los amigos salsa(guatemala)
directions: Combine all ingredients into a blender or food processor and blend to a chunky puree, Do not over puree. Transfer to a bowl or jar.
Serve cold with chips or your favorite dish. You can make this salsa hotter by increasing the amount of chiles in the mixture.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in a buttered casserole dish in the order listed.
Bake in 350° oven until bubbly and topping is lightly browned.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix everything together at the same time.
Do not mix with mixer.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured, at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
(Can use icing or powdered sugar for topping.)

title: wild rice and chicken casserole
directions: Prepare rice as directed.
Drain mushrooms; reserve liquid. Saute onion in butter until transparent.
Stir in flour, chicken broth, mushroom liquid and cream, stirring constantly, cooking until thick.
Add all ingredients except almonds.
Mix well. Place in baking dish.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cook rice by package directions. Brown sausage and onion; drain and set aside. Heat soup and milk. Layer 1/2 of the rice in casserole dish. Add layer of sausage and onion, then 1/2 of soup mixture and 1/2 of cheese. Repeat. Cook for 30 to 40 minutes, until cheese melts and slightly brown.

title: seafood dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir well and chill. Serve with boiled shrimp. Yield: About 3 cups.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Wash rhubarb.
Cut in 1/2-inch pieces.
Set aside.
Combine sugar, flour and eggs.
Add to rhubarb; mix thoroughly.
Pour into prepared 9-inch pastry lined pie pan.
Cover with top crust. Brush with mixture of 1 tablespoon milk and 1 teaspoon brown sugar.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: brown bag apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Toss with next 4 ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, 1/2 cup flour and 1 stick margarine until crumbly.
Sprinkle over pie.
Place in a heavy large brown paper bag and fold down twice.
Fasten with three paper clips.
Bake in a 400° oven for 1 hour.
Do not open and peek until time to take pie from oven, as bag might catch on fire.
If left alone the pie does fine and there's nothing to worry about.

title: macaroni fruit salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and put in a baking dish.

title: d.t.'s favorite stuffed mushrooms
directions: Take mushroom and remove stems to have center to fill.
Mix together sour cream, cream of mushroom soup, and Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix.
Put in center of mushrooms.
Place mushrooms in melted margarine.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Add parsley on top before cooking.

title: mom's granola
directions: Combine oatmeal, brown sugar and cinnamon in very, very large stainless
steel
bowl.
Add
the bran flakes, honey and vanilla. If
using
regular
oatmeal, sprinkle 1 cup of water all over the mixture.
Stir well before baking.
Bake at a low heat for 1 hour, stirring thoroughly every 15 minutes.
If not using stainless steel bowl,
pour
into
a
baking
pan before baking!

title: chicken and noodle dinner
directions: Heat oil.
Brown garlic.
Discard garlic.
Add chicken.
Fry until pink color is gone.
Add vegetables; cook until crispy done. Add soy sauce and serve over Ramen noodles.
Serves 4.

title: applesauce dessert
directions: In skillet, melt margarine.
Add oats and cook until golden, stirring constantly.
Stir in sugar and cinnamon.
Remove from heat.
Spoon applesauce into bowls.
Sprinkle warm oats on top of applesauce.
Top with whipped cream.
Serve at once.
Quick and easy.
One of our family favorites!

title: glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes; place in large saucepan.
Cover with boiling water; bring back to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered, 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain; let cool.
Peel and halve lengthwise.

title: cheddar cheese pineapple salad
directions: In medium saucepan combine gelatin and water.
Heat and stir until gelatin dissolves.
Beat in sour cream and mayonnaise.
Stir in undrained pineapple.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in cheese.
Pour in ring or container and allow to mold.

title: shuck beans
directions: Put beans in warm water way up over beans in kettle.
Place plate upside down on them to keep beans in water.
Let soak overnight.

title: calico beans
directions: In a skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove to paper towels to drain.
Discard drippings.
In the same skillet, cook beef and onion until the beef is browned and the onion is tender.
Drain fat.
Combine ground beef and bacon with all remaining ingredients.
Spoon into a 2-quart casserole.
Bake uncovered at 300° for 1 hour or until the beans are as thick as desired. Recipe can easily be doubled for a larger group.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: skillet meal
directions: In large skillet or electric fryer, braise chops in 1 tablespoon oil.
Place sliced onions and potatoes cut in halves or quarters on top of your chops.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper. Cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir to make sure it is not sticking to pan.
Add peas and tomatoes (don't stir).
Cover and let this simmer another 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with rolls or Jiffy cornbread mix.
Quick and easy.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: "Mix red stuff with water and put in oven.
Bake it.
Take it out and mix it and put icing on it and eat it."

title: sinful pudding
directions: Cut oleo into flour like pie dough.
Press into 7 x 11-inch baking dish and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cream together cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add 1 cup of Cool Whip.
Spread on crust.
Then spread drained pineapple on top of cheese mixture. Beat until thick the instant pudding and milk.
Spread over pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with nuts and refrigerate.

title: turketti
directions: Cook spaghetti as usual.
Mix all ingredients in large casserole, retaining enough cheese to cover top.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes (until hot and bubbly).
Can be made the day before and kept in refrigerator.
An easy party dish with a salad and French bread.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup.
Boil 5 minutes.
Add soda and stir.
Pour immediately over corn.
Put in large roaster in oven set to 200°.
Stir every 15 minutes for 1 hour.
Remove, cool, and store in covered container.

title: yummy pork chops
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Remove fat from pork. Place pork in ungreased square baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inches. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over pork. Cover and bake about 45 minutes or until pork is slightly pink when cut near bone. Uncover and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: microwave candy
directions: Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Beat with hand mixer until creamy.
Pour in buttered pan and refrigerate.

title: avocado dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Serve with chips.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix shortening, peanut butter, sugars and egg thoroughly. Blend all dry ingredients and stir into shortening mixture. Chill dough.
Heat oven to 375°.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls. Place 2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Flatten crisscross style with a fork dipped in flour.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: chocolate dump cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Put half of wafers in bottom of pan.
Combine lemon jello, water, sugar and lemon juice.
Let stand until thick syrup. Beat.
Chill milk and beat.
Add to above and beat again.
Pour over crumbs.
Pour rest of crumbs on top.
Put in refrigerator to set.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add beaten eggs
and lemon peel. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and add alternately with milk.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until lightly brown (check in 45 minutes).
Remove. Dissolve the 1/3 cup sugar in the lemon juice.
Pour over the bread.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: In large bowl, mix eggs, sugar, vanilla and entire can of cocktail.
Combine together flour, salt and soda; add to previous mixture.
Nuts are optional.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Ice with cream cheese icing.

title: butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and oleo thoroughly and press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: new age collards(cooking without pork)
directions: Wash collards in cold water until clean.
Roll the leaves in a tight roll and cut across the roll in 2-inch widths.

title: marbled brownies
directions: Cream Cheese Mixture:
Soften cream cheese and margarine. Beat together in a small bowl.
Add sugar, 2 eggs, flour and vanilla; beat until smooth and set aside.

title: hamburger-corn casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Mix ingredients and pour into a 2-quart pan.
Cover with crumbs and margarine.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: green punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Great for parties.
Kids love this.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch cake pan with oil.
Sprinkle pecans on bottom of pan.
Sprinkle coconut over pecans.
Mix cake mix according to package directions and pour over coconut/pecans.
Mix cream cheese and melted butter and confectioners sugar and pour over cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: deep-dish southwestern pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Combine biscuit mix, cornmeal, water and butter in medium bowl.
Mix well.
Pat dough on bottom and up sides of greased 15 x 10-inch baking pan.
Bake 10 minutes. Remove from oven.
Brown meat with onion in large skillet and pour off fat.
Add tomato sauce, chilies, bouillon, chili powder and cumin.
Cook and stir until bouillon dissolves.

title: blueberry molded salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Combine the saved pineapple juice with enough cold water to make 1 1/2 cups of liquid.
Add to other mixture; let mold completely.

title: pistachio pineapple dessert
directions: Mix all and chill before serving.

title: baked corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole dish. Set dish in pan of water and bake 1/2 hour, uncovered, at 400°.

title: pasta with herbs
directions: Cook pasta until tender; drain and rinse.
Mix herbs, garlic, oil and cheese in a blender and liquify to make sauce.
Add sauce to cooked pasta and gently heat while stirring.
Serve immediately, 25 minutes to make, as a side dish or main dish.

title: dried peaches(to fry pies)
directions: Slice peaches (Remove seed) Add sugar and vinegar.
Let set over night.
The next morning cook slowly for 2-3 hours.
Put in pint jars and put under water bath for 15 minutes.

title: egg custard
directions: Combine milk, sugar and flour.
Mix eggs, butter and vanilla in blender and let stand for 3 minutes.
Pour into buttered pie dish and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: turnip souffle
directions: Peel and slice turnips and onion.
Cook with sugar until tender, drain and mix in remaining ingredients.
Place in buttered casserole dish and top with cracker crumbs mixed with melted butter.
Bake in moderate oven until knife inserted between edge and center comes out clean or about 50 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter, 1/2 cup sugar and brown sugar together.
Add egg and vanilla, beating well.
Blend in flour gradually; mix thoroughly.
Shape dough into balls, using rounded teaspoon for each ball.
Roll balls in sugar; place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes. Remove from oven. Place candy Kiss on top of each cookie, pressing down firmly until cookie cracks.
Return to oven.
Bake for 2 to 5 minutes longer. Yields 3 dozen cookies.

title: all-in-the-blender salmon mousse
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in blender and blend at high speed until onion is pureed.
Add next 4 ingredients and blend again. Add cream, 1/3 at a time and blend until very smooth.
Pour into a 1-quart mold and chill overnight.
To unmold, dip bottom and sides of mold into warm water and invert onto a serving plate.
Decorate mousse with parsley.

title: orange fondant-stuffed dates
directions: Cream together powdered sugar and butter.
Mix in orange peel, juice and extract.
Place in pastry tube; pipe into dates. Makes about 32.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Mix together next 3 ingredients. Stir in liquid.
Add blueberries.
Fill lined muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° about 20 minutes or until browned lightly.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Crumble crackers.
Add melted margarine and nuts.
Chill while mixing softened ice cream, instant pudding and milk, blending well.
Pour over chilled crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle chopped nuts or reserve some cracker crumbs from crust mixture to top with.
Freeze solid.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cut sausage into 1/4-inch rounds and place in bottom of large skillet or Dutch oven.
Wash and slice mushrooms and place on top of sausage.
Add celery, bell pepper and onion and saute lightly. Cut potatoes into large, diced pieces and place on top of other ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are done.
This will usually cook in its own juice from the sausage; should it need liquid, add 1/2 cup of water.
Serves 6.

title: creole shrimp
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Blend in rest of ingredients except shrimp.
Cook slowly, stirring occasionally, about 30 minutes. Stir in shrimp and heat.
Serve on hot cooked rice.

title: 100 good cookies
directions: In bowl, combine first 9 ingredients.
Beat until fluffy.
Add and mix well the remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: five cup salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients. Stir. Serve chilled.

title: easy chocolate peanut brittle
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil.
Place crackers on foil in single layer.
Melt butter in saucepan just to boiling.
Add sugar to dissolve.
Pour mixture over crackers.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Immediately sprinkle chocolate chips over and spread chocolate smooth when melted.
Sprinkle with peanuts.
Cool in refrigerator.
Cut to squares.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Put in large baking dish.
Add onion, soup, milk, salt, pepper and corned beef.
(Chunk up corned beef before adding.)
Add 1 cup of grated cheese; mix well.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple oatmeal crunch
directions: Put apples, granulated sugar and 2 tablespoons flour in a 9-inch
buttered
baking
dish.
Mix brown sugar and 1/2 cup flour and
cut in margarine.
Add oats and cinnamon.
Put over apples and
bake
at
for
hour.	Serve warm or cold. Freezes well and will serve 6 to 8 people.

title: tropical carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients and set aside.
In a large bowl, with mixer, beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar; beat until thick and lemon colored.
Fold in oil.
Add dry ingredients slowly.
Stir in carrots, pineapple, nuts and coconut.
Mix well.

title: pork tenderloin deluxe
directions: Cross 2 strips of bacon and place 1 patty in the center.
Then place 1 onion slice and 1 tomato slice on top of patty.
Bring the bacon over the top and fasten with a toothpick.
Do this with all 4 patties.
Bake 2 hours, covered, in a 350°
oven.
Uncover the last 15 minutes.
If necessary, in the last half hour of cooking, add a little water.

title: chili con queso bean dip
directions: Partially mash beans in chili with fork.
Combine with remaining ingredients in saucepan; simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot with corn tortillas or potato chips. Makes 5 cups.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until soft.
Drain liquid but reserve 1/2 cup. Mix all ingredients together well.
If salad is too thick add the liquid you reserved until it is as moist as desired.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Add uncooked macaroni.
Coat well with butter.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and cheese over top.
Pour milk over this.
Stir and mix well.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chunky vegetable chili
directions: In large pot, saute pepper and onion in oil until tender. Stir in all remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until rice or macaroni is tender, 25 to 30 minutes. Stir occasionally.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Mix in a jar.
Pour into greased muffin pans.
Bake in 425° oven until brown.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Drop by 1/4 cupfuls in hot frying pan with a little bacon grease or on a hot griddle. Cook on both sides until done and lightly browned.
Can serve with syrup.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
