Set a rack over a baking sheet and oil lightly or spray with nonstick cooking spray.

title: chinese meatballs
directions: Mix chuck, rice, eggs, salt and pepper.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Brown meatballs in oil on all sides in a skillet.
Line 2 shallow 3-quart casseroles with aluminum foil.
Divide meatballs evenly between casseroles. Add onions to pan drippings and cook until wilted.
Add Chinese vegetables, mushrooms and chicken broth.
Mix cornstarch, soy sauce and sherry until smooth.
Stir into sauce and simmer, stirring constantly, until thickened. Spoon equal portions of sauce over meatballs.
Bake 1 batch, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Freeze second batch. When frozen solid, lift from casserole, overwrap tightly in additional foil.
Return to freezer.
When ready to bake, replace frozen block in casserole.
Bake, covered, in 400° oven until hot through, 1 1/2 hours.
Each batch makes 8 servings.

title: english pea and asparagus casserole
directions: Drain peas and asparagus.
Layer peas, asparagus, sliced boiled eggs, cheese and mushroom soup.
Top with cheese and crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crawfish jambalaya
directions: Saute onions in cooking oil.
Add crawfish tails and cook about 10 to 15 minutes until crawfish turns pink, over low heat, stirring frequently.
Add broth and heat to simmer.
Add rice, green onion tops, bell peppers and seasonings.
Bring to full boil; lower heat.
Cover and simmer for about 30 minutes or until rice is tender.
Serves 6.

title: salmon patties
directions: Crush crackers until fine.
Mix salmon and eggs in a large bowl.
Gradually add crushed crackers.
Form mixture into 3 to 4-inch patties.
Melt enough butter in skillet to thinly coat skillet.
Fry patties until done over medium high heat.

title: twenty-four hour salad
directions: Combine first six ingredients in top of double boiler.
Cook and stir over hot, not boiling, water until thick.
Cool.
Stir in fruits and marshmallows.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon gently into serving bowl.
Chill 24 hours and serve.
We think we can't have Christmas dinner without it; we call it Snow Salad.

title: fancy saucy franks
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, cook preserves and barbecue sauce until bubbly.
Cut franks 1/4-inch thick.
Add franks to saucepan. Boil.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Mix water and cornstarch until smooth. Add to hot mixture.
Cook until thick.
Serves 25.

title: salmon roll
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Roll in chopped walnuts and parsley.
Roll in foil or Saran Wrap.
Chill well so they slice easily for your appetizer tray.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage, carrots and onion very fine.
Combine all ingredients well.
Cover and chill.

title: reese's cups
directions: Cream the margarine and peanut butter.
Add sugar until the consistency to form into balls the size of large marbles.
Add vanilla.
Mix thoroughly (this is best done with your hands).

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: In a large bowl blend sugar, margarine and chocolate.
Add eggs, one at a time, until blended.
Mix in vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add gradually to chocolate mixture, mixing well after each addition.
Cover and chill 2 hours or overnight.

title: chocolate and butterscotch easy fudge
directions: Butter 8-inch square pan.
In small microwave bowl, melt butterscotch chips with 1/3 can sweetened condensed milk; set aside.

title: hershey cake
directions: Mix cake batter accordingly.
Bake three layers for 20 minutes at 325°.

title: lemon tea bread
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Cover; let stand 5 minutes.
Cool.
Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy. Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine the next 3 ingredients; add to butter mixture alternately with milk mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix after each addition.
Stir in lemon rind.

title: easy banana sheet cake
directions: To sour milk, add 1 tablespoon vinegar or lemon juice to milk to equal 1/2 cup.
Let stand until it curdles.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Cut in shortening; add yeast mixture and buttermilk.
Mix with spoon or hands until dough is formed.
Roll and cut on floured paper.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Keep in refrigerator the leftover dough in covered bowl.

title: curried wild rice salad
directions: Cook rice.
Add rest of ingredients with rice.
Best when made 1 to 2 days in advance.
Optional:
Add chicken or shrimp.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg yolks and mix well.
Add lemon rind and juice.
Add flour.
Mix; add milk.
Beat egg whites until very stiff and fold into mixture.
Put into 2 unbaked 9-inch pie shells and bake 10 minutes at 400°, then 30 minutes at 350° on lower oven rack.

title: italian pork chops mozzarella
directions: Moisten chops with water. Shake off excess. Shake or coat 1 or 2 chops at a time with coating mix. Discard any remaining mix. Place in 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until cooked through. Top chops with spaghetti sauce and cheese. Bake an additional 10 minutes or until sauce is warm and cheese is melted. Makes 8 servings.

title: easy cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease two 9-inch pie plates.
Brown meat and onion.
Drain well.
Spread in plates.
Sprinkle cheese on top of each plate.
Mix Bisquick, milk and eggs.
Pour over meat and cheese.
Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: carol's easy chicken pot pie
directions: Mix together:
chicken, soup, Veg-All, salt and pepper.
Pour into one pie shell.
Top with the other pie shell, pinching sides to seal.

title: coffee mocha
directions: Make the coffee and syrup in advance and have cold.
Mix all liquid ingredients in punch bowl.
Spoon ice cream on top.
Serve immediately.
Serves 20.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cube and boil potatoes.
Drain.
Add onion, mushroom soup, sour cream and Velveeta cheese.
Put in casserole dish and bake about 30 minutes at 375°.
Layer top with cheese slices.
Do not return to oven.

title: chicken pie
directions: Use enough cold water to mix.
Roll out thin and cover with grated cheese and pimentos.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Cut into slices and put on top of chicken like biscuits.
Cook until done at 400°.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches. Beat
brown sugar and butter until fluffy.	Stir in baking mix and walnuts until mixture is crumbly; reserve 1 cup.
Press remaining mixture
in pan.
Bake 12 minutes.	Mix cream cheese and granulated	sugar;	beat
in
remaining
ingredients until smooth. Spread
cream cheese mixture over layer in pan; sprinkle
with reserved crumbly mixture. Bake until center is firm, about 25 minutes.
Cut in about 16 (2-inch) squares.
Store in refrigerator.

title: strawberry swizzle
directions: In blender, combine orange juice and strawberries.
Blend until pureed.
Put into a large pitcher and pour both sodas down the side of the pitcher, stirring gently.
Garnish with berries.
This can be made using sugar-free sodas and is very good for diabetic or other diets.
Serves 8.

title: quick camp stew
directions: Cook onions and potatoes in salted water until tender; drain. Combine all ingredients and cook on low for 1 hour. Freezes well.

title: battletown baked squash
directions: Wash and slice squash; boil in salted water until tender. Drain and mash.
Saute onion in butter, add cream and crackers, stirring and cooking for a few minutes.
Mix with squash and place in greased casserole.
Cover with crumbs; dot with butter.
Bake 1/2 hour at 400°.

title: orange glazed pecans
directions: Oil a work surface, i.e., counter top, marble slab, flat baking sheet.
Combine orange peel, juice, sugar and spices in medium size saucepan.
Stir until sugar is dissolved and bring to a boil over medium high heat.
Add the pecans a few at a time, stirring constantly.

When all the pecans have been added, continue to cook until pecans begin to lose their shine (2 to 3 minutes or more); remove pan from heat and continue to stir until all the pecans are clinging in a mass.
Spread pecans on oiled surface to cool.
Use 2 forks to separate pecans so they are not stuck together.
When pecans are cooled and crisp, store in a covered jar.
Makes 2 cups.

title: quickie lasagna
directions: Brown meat well, then stir in soup mix, tomato sauce and water.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
In a 2-quart baking dish, alternate layers of noodles, meat sauce and cheese, ending with cheese.
Bake in oven at 400° for 15 minutes or until bubbling.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread rolls out flat on large cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at oven temperature given on package.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, Ranch mix and mayonnaise together.
Spread on cooled crust.
Add chopped vegetable of your choice (broccoli, carrots, cauliflower, green peppers, cucumbers, tomatoes, etc.).
Top with grated cheese.

title: sausage supper(soup)
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, heat oil.
Add sausage and onion; stir occasionally.
Add tomatoes, water and bouillon; boil.
Add pasta and beans.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer until pasta is tender, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: french raisin pie
directions: Mix in order given and bake in an unbaked pie shell at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter; add brown sugar, beaten eggs and sifted dry ingredients; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Mix together and pour into 1-quart casserole dish. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: roasted preacher
directions: Mix thoroughly neglectful church goers along with self-rising hypocrites.
Add the dried deacons, sleepy singers and a pinch of tightwad tithers.
Mixture should be good and lumpy.
Let sit for sermon. Gradually add in jealousy, frozen amens and whispers. These ingredients will make it thick and stiff.
Be sure to use a spoon.
You don't want to miss a crumb.
After all these ingredients are mixed up and sermon is over, add twinkle tongues and fault finders.
This will add a good flavor to the roast.
By this time, your preacher should be cooked, stewed and boiled.
You should now have a well unbalanced roasted preacher.
This recipe is well known throughout the churches today.
It's simple and tasty and you don't even use a stove.
A very weak Christian.

title: italian "love" cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured cake pan.
Mix the remaining 5 ingredients, beating until smooth.
Pour evenly over cake batter. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until cake is done.
When cool, sprinkle confectioners sugar on top.

title: warm spiced fruit
directions: Drain fruit and combine in baking dish.
Add apple juice and sprinkle with spices.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Serve warm.
109 calories per serving.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread bean dip in bottom of 9x6 glass dish. Spread guacamole dip on top of bean dip. Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, and taco seasoning together. Spread over guacamole. Chop onions, tomatoes, and jalepeno. Mix gently and spread over top of sour cream. Top with cheese. Use Doritos or taco chips for dipping.

title: dill pickles
directions: Fill quart jars with fresh cucumbers any size you like.
Pour mixture over cucumbers to fill jar.
Cold pack 10 minutes.

title: swiss cheese chicken
directions: Combine all but almonds; mix well.
Pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle on nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hot chicken sandwiches
directions: Mix chicken, eggs, mushrooms, mayonnaise, onion and black olives.
Butter both sides of bread and make sandwiches with the filling.
Mix together chicken soup and sour cream.
Place sandwiches in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour soup and cream mixture over sandwiches.
Add a dash of paprika and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk, butter and cocoa for 1 1/2 minutes (starting when mixture has reached a full rolling boil).
Remove from heat and add oats, nuts, vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat well until well blended.
Spoon onto wax paper.

title: italian-sauced fish(even people who say they don't like fish will like this)
directions: Arrange fillets in single layer on well-greased (or use Pam spray) 10 x 15-inch baking sheet.
Sprinkle with salt.
Mix spaghetti sauce and onion.
Pour over fillets.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until fish flakes easily with fork, about 25 to 30 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts, about 3 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: squash and apple bake
directions: Cut each squash in
half
and
remove seeds and fibers; pare squash and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Stir together brown sugar, butter, flour, salt
and
mace.
In an ungreased baking dish (11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch), place squash, then apples. Top with sugar mixture.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until squash is tender.
Yields 6 servings.

title: zesty peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove seeds from peppers.
Combine remaining ingredients; fill each pepper with approximately 1/3 cup of rice mixture.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Cover.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy baked stew
directions: Place meat in Dutch oven.
Season with salt, pepper, paprika and onion soup mix.
Add potatoes, carrots, celery and mushrooms. In saucepan, blend celery soup with water and wine, cooking over medium heat.
Before mixture begins to boil, remove from heat and pour over meat and vegetables.
Cover and bake at 250° to 300° for 4 to 5 hours, until vegetables are tender.

title: pancakes
directions: Melt Crisco into frying pan.
Mix all ingredients in bowl. Pour mixture onto pan according to desired size.
Flip as pancakes become solid.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into thin strips, dust with flour and pepper.
In large skillet, brown meat in butter.
Add mushrooms, onions and garlic.
Brown lightly.
Stir in soup.
Cover and cook 1 hour or until meat is tender, stirring now and then.
Gradually blend in sour cream.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Serve over noodles.
Makes 4 generous servings.

title: chalupas
directions: Place roast in large roasting pan.
Cover the roast with water. Then add all remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook at 250° for 8 hours.
Remove bones.
(Meat should cook to pieces.)
Stir meat mixture together.
Serve over Doritos.
Top with grated cheese, chopped onion, lettuce, tomatoes, sour cream, sliced ripe olives and picante sauce, if desired.
Serves a large group.
Can also be served with flour tortillas.

title: jello salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O per package instructions.
Pour into a cake pan and jell slightly.
Fold sliced bananas and drained pineapple chunks into slightly set Jell-O (reserve pineapple juice).
Mix together sugar, flour, beaten eggs, pineapple juice and butter. Cook until thickened.
Add marshmallows.
Stir and let cool.
Mix Dream Whip per package instructions.
Fold into cooled custard mixture.
Pour over Jell-O.
Sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs or nuts.
Chill about 1 hour.

title: nancy's copper pennies
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix remaining items for marinade.
Pour over carrot mixture. Refrigerate for at least 12 hours before serving cold.
Serves 12.

title: shrimp and angel hair
directions: Saute green onions and oil on medium heat for 3 minutes.
Chop shrimp in.
Put fire on high and put shrimp stock and whipping cream in; mix well.
Add lemon juice and paprika.
Mix for 5 minutes.
When ready to eat, mix in cold stock and cornstarch until smooth.

title: spaghetti and cheese
directions: Drain and set cooked spaghetti aside.
Mix all ingredients, cook and stir until it forms a creamy sauce and cheese is melted (cook on medium heat).
Stir often.
Mix cheese sauce with cooked spaghetti.
Place in baking dish.
Sprinkle paprika on top of spaghetti.
Bake 20 or 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: crisscross turkey casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Blend in flour and seasonings. Gradually add milk; cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Add turkey, broccoli and 1/2 cup of the cheese.
Mix well.
Spoon into 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Separate crescent dough into one large and two small rectangles; firmly press perforations to seal.
Cut large rectangle lengthwise into fourths, forming four 12-inch strips.
Cut remaining rectangles lengthwise into thirds, forming six 8-inch strips.
Place dough strips over turkey mixture in lattice design.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and drop potato pieces in a few at a time.
Blend until potato is fine.
You may have to pour a little of the liquid in dish to make room for all of the potato. Spray an 8-inch square baking dish with Pam.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, baking soda, vanilla, eggs and fruit cocktail.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup brown sugar and nuts on top. Bake for 40 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apples in 8-inch square baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and crumble over top of apples.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: drunken sailor dogs
directions: Mix, heat, serve and enjoy.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Combine spaghetti sauce mix, tomato paste, tomato sauce and water; bring to a boil over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Combine eggs, Ricotta cheese and spinach, mixing well.
Set aside.

title: pork chops on rice
directions: In a skillet, brown chops on both sides.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place rice in a 12 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Pour orange juice over rice.
Arrange pork chops on rice.
Pour chicken soup over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: italian acorn squash soup
directions: Split squash in half and scoop out strings and seed.
Cut squash in quarters and steam for 30 minutes or until
very soft. Scoop out pulp and set aside.
In skillet, melt butter and add oil.
When hot, add onion and saute until wilted.
Add potatoes to skillet and stir.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Place potato mixture, stock and squash in large kettle.
Bring to a boil, then stir in thyme.
Simmer soup for 25 minutes.
Let cool slightly and puree in blender.
Return to kettle, stir in milk and heat again.
Serve hot with Parmesan cheese and parsley sprinkled on top.

title: sensational chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a bowl, cream together butter and brown and white sugars.
Add eggs and beat well.
In a separate bowl, sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to butter mixture. Blend.
Stir in chocolate chips, oatmeal, vanilla and nuts.
Blend thoroughly.
Drop by the tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Makes 36 cookies.

title: bavarian pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shells.
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: pork chop favorites
directions: Brown chops slowly in frying pan.
Place in casserole. combine cracker crumbs, onion, egg, salt and 1/2 cup milk.
This makes a dressing.
Place a mound of dressing on each chop.
Add remaining milk.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove cover and continue cooking for 15 more minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: potato soup
directions: boil / cook potatoes;

title: veg-all casserole
directions: In medium casserole dish, mix together Veg-All, onion and mayonnaise.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top and bake for 20 minutes at 325°.
Sprinkle French fried onions on top of cheese and bake for 5 more minutes.

title: easy (peach) cobbler
directions: Combine peaches, sugar, 1 tablespoon baking mix and cinnamon in 1-quart casserole.
Mix remaining 2/3 cup baking mix with brown sugar in medium bowl.
Cut in butter until size of small peas.
Stir in milk until moistened.
Drop by spoonfuls onto peaches.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until toothpick in crust comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Good served warm with ice cream.

title: unleavened bread
directions: Combine hot water, sugar, salt and shortening. Cool to lukewarm.

title: linda's shrimp dip
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Chill for several hours or overnight in a covered container.
Serve on crackers.

title: chili beans
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until brown; pour off fat.
Add tomatoes, kidney beans, tomato sauce, chili powder, brown sugar, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potatoes supreme
directions: Defrost potatoes.
Combine with butter.
Add rest of ingredients and mix together. Put in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add fried onions for last 10 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook onion, celery and garlic in hot oil until tender but not brown.
Add tomatoes and next 6 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 45 minutes.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Line large rectangular pan with about 9 tortillas.
Brown ground beef and onion; add seasonings.
Pour meat mixture over tortillas.
Mix together beans with cubed cheese.
Pour over other mixture.
Cut remainder of tortillas in strips and place on pie. Mix together Ro-Tel and soup.
Pour over pie.
Cook for 30 minutes at 275°, then turn oven down to 250° and cook for an additional 30 minutes.

title: tuna pate
directions: Beat all ingredients except tuna until smooth.
Gradually add tuna.
Chill, covered, for 8 hours.
Serve as a spread with chips or crackers.

title: lemon filling
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, lemon juice and egg yolks.
Slowly add boiling water.
Add butter or oleo.

title: georgia goulash
directions: Saute onions in bacon fat until tender.
Place sliced tomatoes on top of onions.
Pour okra over top.
Salt and pepper on top of okra.
Also, sprinkle about 2 tablespoon sugar over all.
Pour 1 1/2 cups boiling water over all.
Cook in skillet.
Cover and cook slowly 1 hour.
Server over rice.
This is for fresh vegetables only.

title: raisin pie
directions: Bring water to boiling.
Add raisins.
Cover and cook for 5 minutes.
Mix sugar and flour; stir into raisins.
Lower to medium heat.
Stir and let boil 1 minute.
Add lemon juice.
Pour into shells.
Top with crust and bake for 30 minutes or until browned at 425°.

title: chocolate and peanut butter candy
directions: crush crackers and mix all the ingredients together.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt 6 ounces chocolate chips and 2/3 cup peanut butter together.
Pour over graham cracker mix.
Let cool.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine chicken, pineapple, celery, oranges, pepper and onion.
Blend mayonnaise and mustard.
Toss gently with chicken mixture.
Cover and chill several hours.

title: dorito casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Mix onion and green pepper; add a little water and simmer.
Mix cream of chicken and Cheez Whiz into meat mixture.
Place Doritos on bottom of casserole; add layer of meat mixture.
Layer again with Doritos and meat mixture.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° until cheese is bubbly.

title: italian chicken with rice
directions: Marinate chicken in Italian dressing overnight. Dice chicken into 1 to 2-inch cubes. Saute in marinade dressing until chicken is fully cooked. Add carrots and broccoli. Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally until chicken is fully cooked and vegetables are tender. Drain marinade into pan; add cornstarch and water. Stir over low heat until gravy thickens. Serve chicken and vegetables over a bed of rice. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: nutty orange pancakes
directions: In mixer bowl, combine eggs, orange juice and honey; beat with an electric mixer until blended.
Add biscuit mix and nuts; beat on medium about 30 seconds or until well blended.
Pour about 1/4 cup batter onto a hot, lightly greased griddle or heavy skillet. Cook until golden brown, turning when pancake has a bubbly surface and slightly dry edges.
Repeat with remaining batter.
Makes 12 to 14 pancakes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let stand 1/2 hour.
Roll into balls. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: hot biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening to flour mixture.
Stir in about 3/4 cup milk with a fork, gradually add additional milk, if needed, to make a soft, almost sticky dough.
Turn dough out on lightly floured wax paper and knead just until smooth.
Roll dough about 1/2-inch thick and cut with a floured cutter.
Place biscuits on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly brown.
Brush with margarine or butter.

title: sweet and sour chicken (crock-pot)
directions: In crock-pot, place carrots, green pepper and onion. Top with chicken breasts. Sprinkle with salt. Pour sweet-sour sauce and pineapple chunks over all. Cover. Cook on low 7 to 8 hours or high 3 1/2 to 4 hours. Remove chicken, keeping warm. Blend cornstarch and water. Stir into juices in crock-pot. Cover; cook on high 10 to 15 minutes. Season to taste. Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: chocolate raspberry pie
directions: Line unpricked pastry shell with a double thickness of heavy-duty foil.
Bake at 450 degrees for 8 minutes.
Remove foil; bake 5 minutes longer.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: fruit dip
directions: Whip together first 3 ingredients.
Add sour cream.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: slovak pancakes
directions: Beat the eggs well.
Add sugar, salt and 1 cup milk.
Beat very well and then add flour gradually, putting in the remaining milk.
Beat until very smooth.
Have greased skillet hot.
Put about 2 tablespoons of the mixture on this skillet.
Brown both sides.
A filling may be
used such as jams, jellies, etc.
This recipe makes about 30 pancakes.

title: saucepot meatballs
directions: Combine soup mix, water and tomato juice in a deep saucepan. Bring to a boil and simmer covered for 15 minutes. Mix ground beef, seasonings and parsley.

title: overnite baked beans
directions: Rinse and soak beans 2 hours.
Brown bacon and drain. Mix all ingredients in large roasting pan.
Bake for 12 hours, covered, at 200°.
Uncover and stir. If beans are not soft, bake, uncovered, at 350° until soft.

title: quick caramel
directions: Melt the butter, stir in the sugar and salt.
Add syrup and mix well.
Add the milk, stirring constantly, cook until it reaches 245° on a sugar thermometer.
Immediately remove from the heat. Add vanilla and pour into a well buttered 9-inch square pan.
Cut when cool.

title: orange slice cake
directions: (Coat candy and dates in a little flour before adding to cake mixture to keep from sticking together.)

title: chicken out of this world
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place raw chicken breasts in 9 x 13-inch baking dish, single layer.
Lay a slice of cheese on each chicken breast.
Mix soup and milk together and pour over chicken and cheese.
Cover with stuffing mix and drizzle with oleo.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 375°.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain vegetables and water chestnuts. Mix all ingredients together.
Melt margarine in microwave and mix with cracker crumbs. Place over top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pretzel dessert
directions: Mix together and spread in a 8 x 10-inch pan or a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350° and cool.

title: snowball's jewels
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes, or until edges are golden brown.
Immediately remove from cookie sheets.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken.
Remove from bones and skin.
Cut up and place in baking dish.
Mix chicken broth and celery soup, beating and stirring until smooth.
Pour over cut-up chicken.
Mix flour and milk with baking powder and salt, pepper and melted margarine. Beat until smooth.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 30 minutes at 425°.

title: pork chop casserole(serves 4)
directions: Cut up potatoes as in scalloped potatoes.
Put in bottom of large casserole.
Slice onion and separate rings.
Add to potatoes. Dice green pepper; add to rest.
On stove, brown pork chops quickly.
Place on top of casserole.
In pan on stove melt mushroom soup and milk.
Pour over entire casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or so, depending on the thickness of the chops.
Delicious!!

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion, salt and pepper.
Drain.
Stir in cream of chicken soup and simmer for about 15 minutes.
Take 1/2 of meat mixture and put in bottom of casserole dish and sprinkle with 1/2 cheese.
Take other 1/2 of meat mixture and put on top of that, then add the remaining cheese.
Top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: orange marmalade
directions: Cut fruit very thin, peeling and all.
Weight fruit and, to each pound, add 1 quart water.
Let stand 24 hours.
Boil 1 hour. Let stand another 24 hours.
Weigh the mixture and, to each pound, add 1 pound sugar.
Boil 1 hour again.
Put marmalade in jars while hot and cover with paraffin.

title: day after thanksgiving casserole
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, combine uncooked rice and packet of seasoning with remaining ingredients except nuts.
Mix well. Bake, covered, at 375° for 45 minutes.
Remove cover; sprinkle with nuts and continue baking for 15 minutes or until rice is done.
Makes 6 servings, 275 calories per serving.

title: key lime pie
directions: In large heat-resistant bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Stir in yogurt with wire whisk. Fold in Cool Whip with wooden spoon. Spread mixture in crust and refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight. Garnish as desired. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: maraschino sauce
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt together in a saucepan.
Drain cherries and reserve syrup.
Gradually stir in syrup and water. Stir constantly and bring to boil over medium heat.
Cover; simmer 3 minutes.
Cut cherries in halves and stir into mixture.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups sauce.
Good with ice cream.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Beat egg with 1 tablespoon ReaLemon; combine flour, garlic powder and paprika.
Dip chicken in mixture, then in flour mixture.
In skillet, brown chicken with margarine.
Dissolve bouillon in water; add with remaining ReaLemon to skillet.
Cover; simmer 20 minutes or until tender.
Garnish as desired. Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 4 servings.

title: shrimp salad
directions: To boiling salted water, add garlic and shrimp.
Boil 15 minutes.
Peel and devein shrimp and cut each shrimp into 2 to 3 pieces.
Add onion and celery.
Season, then mix thoroughly with mayonnaise to which you have added mustard.
You may add a small amount of chopped sweet pickle.
Serves 6.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and chocolate syrup.
In a separate bowl, sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add flour mixture alternately with the buttermilk to chocolate mixture.
Add vanilla and melted candy bars.
Pour into a large greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry snow
directions: Blend
first 3 ingredients and pour over crumbled angel food cake.
Cook
next
ingredients until clear and thick. Cool and mix in 2 pints sliced strawberries and pour over cake mixture. Top with more Cool Whip.

title: austin's awesome chops
directions: Saute chops.
Deglaze pan with white wine and add beef consomme and thicken with cornstarch to desired consistency.
Lay chops in pan placing a pineapple on each.
Cover each chop with Swiss cheese.
Pour sauce on top.
Heat in 350° oven until bubbly.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash and slice cucumbers and onions. Add salt and place in large bowl; cover with plate. Let stand 3 hours and then drain well. Add remaining ingredients in a large saucepan (preferably in a Dutch oven) and bring to a full boil. Add cucumber mixture and heat, but DO NOT COOK. Seal in canning jars.

title: italian salad dressing
directions: Mix and pour enough over green salad to taste.

title: low-fat pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil, pumpkin and eggs.
Combine all dry ingredients in a separate bowl.
Add dry to pumpkin mix; add raisins.
Pour into 2 loaf pans sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mrs. vick's oatmeal cookies
directions: Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: mayhaw jelly
directions: Juice:
Sort and wash berries.
Put in large pot with water. Bring to a boil for 30 minutes.
Strain juice twice.

title: stove top kielbasa(by louis carter)
directions: Place a layer of beans in bottom of medium pot.
Next, add a layer of shredded cabbage, then a layer of onion slices and a layer of kielbasa.
Top off with tomatoes.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Season to taste and cook over low to medium heat for four hours.

title: banana muffins
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Beat in eggs, mashed bananas, vanilla, soda and salt.
By hand, stir in flour until just blended.
Add nuts, stirring as little as possible.
Bake in muffin tins at 400° for about 12 minutes or until golden on top. Makes 18.

title: crab and spinach quiche
directions: Bake pie crust.
Cook spinach according to directions on package.
Drain and squeeze out excess water.
Beat eggs with yogurt, flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in spinach and crab meat. Sprinkle mushrooms, cheese and onions over crust.
Pour in spinach mixture.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Lower to 350° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: "zippy" vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill overnight.

title: lemon chess bars
directions: Mix well.
Press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: lazy man's lasagna
directions: In a large bowl, combine ziti, eggs, Ricotta cheese and 3/4 of the Mozzarella cheese; mix well.
Layer bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with spaghetti sauce.
Put half of ziti on top, add another layer of sauce, then add the remaining ziti, then another layer of sauce.
Top with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Beat eggs. Saute onion in butter.
Add other ingredients. Cook in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Use a long Pyrex dish, one you would make a cobbler in.

title: black joe cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Blend in 2 beaten eggs. Add sour milk alternately with flour and cocoa.
Stir vanilla in. Dissolve the soda in boiling water.
Add the dissolved soda and blend by hand.
Bake in 2 (8-inch) greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: savory sausage casserole
directions: Break apart sausage and brown in skillet, pouring off excess fat as it accumulates.
When done, mix sausage, rice, soup, onion and celery.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Add soy sauce to water and add to mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: triple layer cooler bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt butter in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs and then coconut over butter; top with sweetened condensed milk.
Bake 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Put milk in refrigerator until icy cold.
Dissolve jello in hot water until partially set.
Whip it.
Add lemon juice, rind, sugar and pineapple.
Whip chilled milk until stiff.
Fold in jello mixture.
Line pan with 1/2 crumbs.
Pour mixture on this. Sprinkle crumbs on top.

title: liver patties
directions: Grind liver, bread and onions.
Add egg, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well and form into patties and fry.
Very good!!

title: easy party fare
directions: In large pot, put butterscotch chips.
Put on medium stove. Add peanut butter, stirring until chips are melted.
Dump in potatoes, stirring until all potatoes are coated.
Drop by tablespoon on wax paper.
Let cool.

title: jello salad
directions: Put pineapple and juice from can in pan with jello.
Bring to boil.
Set aside and cool.
Add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Beat and put in dish.
Refrigerate.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Put bread cubes in 9x13 inch ungreased pan.
Top with sausage and grated cheese.
Beat eggs, milk and mustard.
Pour over bread cubes.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Spread soup on top in morning.
Put mushrooms on top of soup.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: pineapple-coconut pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and margarine, then other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: peanut butter-n-honey cookies
directions: Cream shortening, honey and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Add well-beaten egg.
Add peanut butter and salt.
Stir in flour and soda sifted together.
Mix well.
Form into small balls of dough and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Press with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Peel and slice cukes.
Mix all ingredients and blend well. Add sour cream and cukes.
Mix. Chill before serving.

title: fruit filled cantaloupe
directions: Cut cantaloupes in half.
Combine blueberries and strawberries.
Pile lightly in cantaloupe halves.
Chill at least one hour before serving.
Garnish with fresh mint leaves.
Makes 6 servings.

title: miss birdie's vinegar pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, eggs, vinegar and nuts.
Put in uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sauce for deer
directions: Mix together all of the ingredients and bring to a quick boil. Baste deer about every 1/2 hour. Cook slowly at 225° until meat falls off the bone.
If using crock-pot, wrap meat in foil and follow instructions.

title: pepper steak
directions: In skillet, in 1 tablespoon hot oil, cook beef until browned, stirring often.
Remove, set aside.
In remaining 1 tablespoon hot oil, cook peppers and onion with garlic powder until tender crisp, stirring often.
Stir in gravy and Worcestershire.
Heat to boiling.
Return beef to skillet.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: pork tenderloin with chutney
directions: For marinade, put chutney, chili, lemon juice, vinegar, ginger and curry into a food processor or blender; mix until smooth. Transfer to a large plastic food bag; add pork and seal bag tightly.
Refrigerate 12 hours or longer; heat oven to 450°. Remove pork from marinade.
Arrange on a foil-lined jelly roll pan.
Roast until internal temperature reaches about 155° about 25 to 35 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing (temperature should rise to 160°).

title: salsa dip
directions: Soften and blend cream cheese.
Add salsa and mix well.
Use as dip for chips.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Cook syrup, sugar, water, vinegar and salt (approximately 275°).
Cook until the mixture threads.
Slowly beat in well beaten egg whites.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Cook until thick enough to spoon.
Drop on wax paper.
Mixture hardens fast!

title: fat-free chocolate wowie cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In an 8 x 8-inch baking dish, combine dry ingredients. Make a well in dry ingredients and add remaining ingredients. Stir until mixed well.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes. Cool in pan. Dust with powdered sugar.

title: fruit cake
directions: Roll fruit and nuts in one cup flour. Use other cup in batter.

title: homemade horseradish
directions: Combine all ingredients in food processor or blender; process until pureed.
Carefully remove cover off processor or blender, keeping face away from container.
Cover and store in refrigerator.
Yield: 1 1/4 cups.

title: beef and rice fiesta
directions: Brown beef in skillet, leaving meat in large chunks.
Add onion and cook over medium heat until tender.
Add water, soup, salt, corn and chili powder.
Bring to boil.
Stir in rice.
Add tomato (cut in eighths) and green pepper cut in strips or rings. Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Makes about 5 servings.

title: unbaked strawberry pie
directions: Heat wine and water to simmering.
Add gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Add block of frozen strawberries and lemon juice to hot mixture, breaking up the block to hasten process.
Chill until mixture begins to thicken.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Beat eggs; add salt and sherry.
Set aside.
Heat oil (medium-high); saute onion until soft.
Add beaten egg mixture and scramble cook until dry and crumbly.
Add cooked rice and brown gravy.
Add soy sauce, if desired, to taste (do not add too much or rice will become sticky).
Brown coloring comes from Chinese brown gravy (purchase in Chinese section of grocery store). Secret...cook rice before frying.

title: uncle herb's char siu pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and fry.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Melt and cool chocolate.
Combine the rest of the ingredients (except pecans) until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cashew chicken(casserole)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and put into a greased casserole. Warm the soup and water.
Pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: scripture cake
directions: Heat the oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9-inch square pan. In a medium bowl, beat together the butter, brown sugar and eggs until light.
Add flour, soda, honey, and milk all at once.
Beat just until smooth.

title: broccoli and cheese
directions: Boil frozen broccoli 5 minutes; drain and set aside.
Beat eggs; stir in mayonnaise, soup, onions, cheese and salt and pepper to taste.
Fold in the cooked broccoli.
Place entire mixture in casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven 40 minutes.

title: fruit cookie pizza
directions: Pat cookie dough into an ungreased 14-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.
In a bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread over crust. Arrange fruit on top.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Simmer broth and onion about 20 minutes or until onion is tender. Add broccoli and mushrooms; simmer. In separate pan, melt margarine; add flour and milk. Whisk until blended and thick. Pour mixture into broth. Add cream, salt, pepper and Tabasco. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes. Do not boil.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass pans). Combine flour and sugar; cut in oleo until crumbly. Press firmly in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine shortening, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl; beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Beat egg into creamed mixture.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix into creamed mixture just until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough, 3 inches apart, onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies, or 11 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.
Do not overbake.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet.
Remove to cool completely.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: cajun seasoning
directions: Mix well in a small bowl.
Funnel into a shaker bottle.
Use as a seasoning in most everything you cook.

title: chinese ham soup
directions: To 1 cup salad dressing or mayonnaise, add:

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Crush graham crackers (a food processor works well).
Mix together crackers, sugar, peanut butter and vanilla.
Melt margarine and add to mixture.
Measure level tablespoon of mixture and shape into balls.
Freeze overnight (or longer if you need to store them).
Melt chocolate chips and wax in double boiler.
Keep over low heat and dip the frozen balls.
They will warm up quickly and be ready to enjoy.

title: crumb cake
directions: Grease cookie sheet and preheat oven to 325°.
Cream together 1 stick of butter or margarine, 2 eggs, 1/2 pint sour cream and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Then add 2 cups flour, 1 cup sugar, 2 teaspoons baking powder and 1 1/4 teaspoons baking soda.
Mix well, then spread in cookie sheet.

title: apricot dressing
directions: In a blender or food processor combine cottage cheese, jam, lemon juice and rind.
Blend until smooth.
Transfer mixture into small bowl.
Cover and chill.

title: frozen cherry delight
directions: Mix together and freeze.

title: lean chicken cacciatore(lo-fat)
directions: In
a medium skillet, cut up undrained tomatoes. Add mushrooms, onion, green pepper, wine, garlic, oregano, salt and pepper.
Place chicken pieces on tomato mixture in skillet. Bring to boiling; reduce heat. Cook and simmer 25 minutes.
Remove chicken to serving platter; sprinkle with paprika.
Keep warm.

title: seven-cup salad
directions: Combine all and let set in refrigerator.
For added color, add red or green cherries.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Place crackers in roasting pan.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over crackers.
Mix well. Bake at 350° for 6 minutes, stirring after each 2 minutes. Cool.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Cook peaches, sugar, water and cornstarch until thick.
Add vanilla and butter.
Fill baked pie shell with sliced, fresh peaches.
Pour cooked mixture over sliced peaches.
Refrigerate until set.
Cut and serve with Cool Whip or ice cream on top.

title: thanksgiving cranberry apple salad
directions: Wash and grind the raw cranberries and combine with orange rind and sugar.
Let stand 30 minutes.

title: six layer dinner casserole
directions: Place layers of vegetable and meat in order given.
Season each layer with salt and pepper.
Bake in large casserole dish for about 2 hours at 350°.
Cover for the first hour.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: M&M's can also be placed on cookies before baking.

title: quick spoon rolls
directions: Mix ingredients in mixing bowl.
Grease muffin pans; fill half full.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: yogurt riata
directions: Blend yogurt, cucumber, onion, coriander, tomato and salt until completely coated.
Chill for several hours.
Serve with rice, dal, meat and chicken.
Can also be eaten alone with bread.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Beat the cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla until smooth and creamy.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in pie shell.
Cool; pour cherries on top.
Refrigerate until served.

title: turkey and broccoli casserole
directions: Put broccoli that has been boiled slightly and well drained into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place turkey on top of broccoli; mix soups, egg, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Pour over turkey.
Next add layer of cheese.
Melt margarine and stir into stuffing mix.
Put stuffing on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° uncovered until casserole is bubbling and browning, about 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8 people generously.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix dressing ingredients and keep in refrigerator until ready to use.
Wash and drain spinach on a paper towel.
Break into bite-size
pieces
and put into bowls.
Arrange wedges of hard-boiled eggs and tomatoes in each bowl.
Add dressing.

title: christmas special
directions: Beat 7-Up and ice cream together. Add cherries.
Makes a delicious drink.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water.
Then cool.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks one at a time and beat well after each one.
Add chocolate mixture and vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy.

title: garlic skewered shrimp
directions: Place shrimp in large plastic bag; add soy sauce, garlic to taste and oil.
Close bag and shake well.
Marinate in bag for 10 minutes.
Drain shrimp and alternately place shrimp and onions onto skewers.
Shrimp may be cooked on grill or broiled in oven 5 inches from heat until shrimp are opaque.

title: date loaf
directions: Boil sugar and milk together until soft ball is formed in cold water.
Add dates and cook 5 minutes longer, stirring constantly. (Note:
Cook until mixture looks like jam.)
Remove from fire; add butter, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until it thickens.
Roll in wet cloth and slice when cold.

title: carrie's taco salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot.
Cook over low heat until desired thickness.
Pack in 6 clean, hot pint jars and seal. Process in boiling water bath 20 minutes.
Makes 6 pints.

title: punch
directions: Mix sherbet and ginger ale together. Serve immediately.

title: slaw
directions: Grate cabbage.
Add other ingredients; mix well with your hands, squeezing the cabbage.
Taste.
You may have to add more sugar and vinegar.
Makes about 1/2 gallon slaw.

title: date balls
directions: Melt butter and add egg, sugar and chopped dates.
Cook in skillet at 300° for 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add cereal, nuts and vanilla.
Form balls and roll in coconut.

title: ribbon jello
directions: Dissolve 1 package strawberry jello in 1 cup boiling water. Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan and chill until firm.
Dissolve next package of strawberry jello in 1 cup boiling water, then add 1/2 cup evaporated milk.
Pour over first layer and chill until firm.
Repeat steps 1 and 2 with remaining jello flavors.
Chill until firm.
Cover with Cool Whip.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients and cook.

title: four bean salad
directions: Stir sugar with oil, vinegar and salt until blended.
Add to beans, onion and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate at least 6 hours or overnight.
Stir several times.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend very well and spread on bottom of pie dish.
Pour and spread cocktail sauce on cheese mixture, then sprinkle shrimp on top.
Add Mozzarella to cover.
Add finely chopped red and green peppers to garnish.
Serve with crackers like Wheatsworth.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Mix cranberries and sugar; set aside.
Dissolve jello in boiling water and gelatin.
Cool and add orange juice, pineapple, cranberries, nuts, celery and apples.
Pour into pan and chill.

title: swordfish steaks
directions: Combine all ingredients, except fish and mix well.
Cook fish with oil and place on hot grill for approximately 3 minutes each side or until done.
Don't overcook.
Top with Tomato Basil Vinaigrette.

title: drawing salve
directions: Melt this all together
and boil for a short while.
Cool, but pour into a dark amber jar before the salve starts to set up. Cover with tight lid to keep from drying out.
This lasts for years.
Add ingredients can be purchased in an old fashioned drug store.

title: corn casserole
directions: In microwave oven (cover dish and vent), in a 1 1/2-quart glass dish, melt butter.
Mix well all remaining ingredients and cook on High 2 minutes.
Rotate dish and cook on Medium (70%) for 10 minutes, or until firm.
Casserole will be like a spoon bread texture.
(Check by inserting a toothpick for doneness.)

title: brownie pie
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Grease pie pan and bake for 25 minutes at 325°.
Will make 1 pie.
Put Cool Whip on top for better flavor.

title: chili meat balls
directions: Combine ground beef, bread crumbs, onion, salt, egg and 1/4 cup tomato soup.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Brown in shortening. Mix remaining soup, chili powder and water; pour over meat. Cover; bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: ranger "little boys' favorites"
directions: Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly; stir in well beaten eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Combine with creamed mixture and blend well.
Stir in oatmeal, Rice Krispies and coconut.

title: hearty turkey or beef stew
directions: Brown ground beef or turkey; drain.
Mix meat with remaining ingredients in a large pot.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat. Simmer, covered, 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Cool and freeze.

title: mushroom-cheese scalloped potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in saucepan; cover with water.
Add salt and boil 5 to 8 minutes.
Drain.
Combine soup, milk, cheese and pepper.
Mix well.

title: butterscotch date bars
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar on low heat until melted.
Cool mixture. Add eggs and vanilla. Sift flour and baking powder and add to first mixture.
Put into greased 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Cut into bars.

title: banana pudding
directions: Put half of box of vanilla wafers in bowl.
Slice two bananas and place in bowl with remaining wafers.
Make pudding and pour over bananas and wafers in bowl.
Slice remaining banana on top and top with Cool Whip.

title: fudge cake
directions: Melt the chocolate in top of a double boiler with the butter. When melted, remove and add the sugar. Mix well and add the eggs. Mix well again. Sift the flour with the salt and blend into chocolate mixture. Add the nuts; mix well and add vanilla. Mix again. Pour into a shallow pan (buttered and lined with wax paper; also butter the paper). A 9 x 9-inch pan is a good size. Spread evenly and bake at 325° for about 30 to 35 minutes, until dry on top and firm to touch. Turn upside down on board; cool. Then cut into squares.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs.
Mix flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Mix all well.
Put in 2 or 3 bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: quick shot fruit dip
directions: In small bowl, combine cream cheese and marshmallow cream until thoroughly mixed.
Refrigerate until needed.
Serve with fresh fruit and cookies for dipping.
Preparation time:
10 minutes.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cook raisins until done.
Add flour and sugar;
mix together. Add vinegar and butter.
Pour in unbaked crust and top with crust. Put sugar onto crust and make air vent with spoon.
Makes 1 pie.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin until light and fluffy.
Mix next 5 ingredients and add to pumpkin mixture.
Mix well.
Bake in 13 1/2 x 8 3/4 x 1 3/4-inch ungreased pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Combine chicken and enough water to cover in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 40 minutes or until tender.
Remove chicken, reserving broth for other uses. Cool chicken.
Skin, bone and cut chicken into bite size pieces. Set aside.
Place broccoli in lightly greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Top with chicken.
Combine soup and next 3 ingredients; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese and stuffing mix.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: hearty chicken soup
directions: Thoroughly rinse chicken.
Place all ingredients in a large pot.
Add salt, pepper, parsley and garlic to taste.
Add 1 tablespoon Gravy Master for color.
Cook for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: scriptural cake
directions: Follow Solomon's prescription for a good boy (Proverbs 23:14) and you will have a good cake.

title: party punch
directions: If using presweetened Kool-Aid, omit sugar.
Mix ingredients well; serve over ice with an ice ring or sherbet.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to package directions.
Add condensed milk, Cool Whip and vanilla.
Place bananas and wafers in large bowl with pudding.
Chill overnight.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix in large bowl.
Mix Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cream cheese and sugar, then stir to melt.
Allow to cool.
Add all other ingredients.
Put into refrigerator and let set.
Real good!

title: black cherry pie
directions: Line bottom and sides of pan with whole vanilla wafers, standing up wafers to form crust.
Crumble some wafers and fill spaces between bottom cookie layer to make crust.
Mix lemon juice and Eagle Brand milk; stir until thick.
Spread even over crust. Drain cherries and spread over top of filling; press down in filling.
Whip and sweeten cream and spread over top.
Crumble a few vanilla wafers and sprinkle over top.
Store in refrigerator.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream together butter, white sugar, then brown sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, a small amount at a time.
Add cereal, oatmeal, coconut and nuts.
Mix.
Drop by small spoonfuls on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 6 to 8 dozen cookies.

title: quiche
directions: Fry sausage and drain. Put in 9 x 12-inch dish. Spread cheese on top. Mix eggs, milk and Bisquick together and pour into casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. This freezes well.

title: creamy chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken breasts in 13 x 9-inch casserole and place cheese on top.
Combine soup and wine and pour over top.
Cover with stuffing crumbs and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: stir-fry chicken with vegetables
directions: Mix water, cornstarch, ginger and soy sauce.
Set aside.
Coat a wok with cooking spray.
Add oil and heat to 375°.
Add onion and garlic.
Stir-fry for 3 to 4 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients and place in casserole.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° until it bubbles.
Serves 12.

title: green peas and rice
directions: Saute the peas, rice and onion in margarine for about 5 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan, stirring well.
Cover the saucepan with foil, then place a lid on top.
Simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: vegetable mold
directions: In saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over 1/2 cup tomato juice to soften.
Over low heat, heat until gelatin is dissolved.
Add remaining 3 cups tomato juice and salad dressing.
Refrigerate until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from a spoon.
Fold remaining ingredients into gelatin mixture.
Pour into 6-cup mold. Serve with sour cream.
Makes 5 cups or 10 servings.

title: baked herb chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients listed after chicken.
Pour over chicken, laid out in a baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: irish potatoes
directions: Mix everything and roll in balls.
Then roll in cinnamon.
Set in refrigerator.

title: english muffin loaves
directions: Combine 3 c. flour, yeast, sugar, salt and soda.
Heat liquids until very warm, 120° - 130°.
Add to dry mixture, beat well.
Stir in enough more flour to make a stiff batter.
Spoon into two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch pans that have been greased and sprinkled with cornmeal.
Sprinkle tops with cornmeal.
Cover; let rise in warm place for 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately and cool.
Slice and toast.
Makes 16 slices per loaf.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Put oatmeal in large bowl.
Stir in milk and boiling water. Add shortening, sugar and salt; let stand until lukewarm. Sprinkle yeast into 1/2 cup of warm water.
Stir until dissolved. Stir into oatmeal mixture.
Add 1/2 the flour; mix until smooth. Add remaining flour, a little at a time.
Mix until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Turn out on board; knead 7 minutes.
Place dough in greased bowl.
Cover with damp cloth; let rise 1 1/2 hours. Knead and shape into loaves.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 40 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Place the ingredients in layers in your baking dish.
Pour two-thirds plus one cup milk over this mixture.
Top with large package shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes and paprika for color.
Bake in 300° oven for one hour.

title: baked scallops
directions: Clean and drain scallops.
On stove, melt butter in baking dish or pan on a low temperature.
Add scallops, salt, pepper and parsley.
Saute 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in wine.
Sprinkle cheese over the top of the mixture.
Bake in 300° oven for about 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Broil 1 to 2 minutes to brown the cheese.
Serve hot.

title: dried beef with rice
directions: Saute onions and peppers in butter until soft but not brown. Add dried beef; cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add rice and continue cooking until thoroughly heated.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mixing bowl pie dough
directions: Place flour and salt in electric mixing bowl.
Measure out a generous 2/3 cup Crisco shortening.
Add to flour and mix on low speed (low to start, you may want to increase the speed after the flour is well mixed with the shortening) until it resembles thick putty.
It may take from 2 to 3 minutes to 4 to 5 minutes before it starts to form into 2 or 3 large lumps.
Then add cold water, one tablespoon at a time; mix well until you have a nice soft dough.
This makes a wonderful, tender, flaky crust.
If dough seems too stiff or cracks while rolling, just put it back in the bowl and add more water, 1 tablespoon at a time.

title: treasure chest dessert
directions: Mix together Rice Krispies, nuts and coconut and brown in oven. Stir in sugar and butter. Put half in 9 x 9-inch square pan. Spoon ice cream and put remaining crumbs on top.

title: deviled ham spread
directions: Blend or process until a fine paste. Makes approximately 1 1/4 cups.

title: luby's spanish slaw
directions: Discard outer leaves from cabbage; wash and cut in half. Remove center core.
Cut into 1/8-inch strips against vein.
Cut pieces into 2-inch portions.
Place in a large serving bowl.
Add parsley, carrot, bell peppers, onion and pickles.
Pour dressing over top and mix well.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: paradise pumpkin pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and egg together. Spread into pie shell.
Combine pumpkin, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, evaporated milk and egg; mix well.
Pour over cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Prepare bread dough as directed to second rise.
Roll half of dough into 12 x 8-inch rectangle.
Melt butter and spread half over dough.
Sprinkle with half of cinnamon and raisins over dough.
Roll up jelly roll style, beginning from long side.
Seal and slice into 12 pieces.
Place in greased 9 x 1/2-inch round pan.
Repeat with remaining half.
Cover; let rise until nearly double, about 30 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine cornmeal and remaining ingredients.
Stir in corn mixture.
Pour into a lightly greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Yields 8 servings.

title: banana-peach freeze
directions: Food process frozen bananas and peaches, separately, until each is the consistency of ice cream.
Pour each one on top of the other into sundae glasses or paper cups.
Follow with a layer of blueberries and grapes.
Top with pureed strawberries.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Cut pockets in chops or roast.
Mix together all ingredients except consomme.
Stuff the pockets.
Cook 2 hours at 375°, basting with the consomme.
Serves 6.

title: pork adobo
directions: Place all ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer until meat is tender, about 2 hours.

title: mexican corn casserole
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Pour 1/2 of the batter into a greased casserole.
Then sprinkle the cheese and chiles over the batter.
Cover with remaining batter.
Bake 1/2 hour at 400°.

title: favorite toffee treat
directions: Arrange 40 crackers on foil lines 11 x 17-inch baking pan. Bring butter and sugar to boil for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers. Bake at 400° for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over and let stand until softened.
Spread over the top and sprinkle with nuts. Place in freezer to cool.
Break into pieces and store in an airtight container.
It won't last long!

title: cheesecake cupcakes
directions: Blend the ingredients until light and fluffy. Put vanilla wafers in the bottom of cupcake liners and a tablespoonful of batter on top. Cook for 20 minutes in preheated 375° oven. After they are thoroughly cooled, put Cool Whip on top and a cherry.

title: colonial carrot pecan cake
directions: Sift together flour and next 4 ingredients; set aside.
In a large size mixing bowl, combine oil and sugar; mix well.
Add half of flour mixture; blend.
Add remaining flour alternately with eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add carrots and pecans.
Mix well.
Bake in 3 layers until toothpick comes out clean (about 30 minutes).
Frost with cream cheese frosting or German Chocolate Filling.

title: turkey and wild rice casserole
directions: Combine turkey with wild rice.
(Include contents of seasoning packet.)
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix and pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool completely before cutting.

title: purple delight beverage
directions: First, pour the blue tint into a cup.
Then pour the grapefruit juice in.
Next comes the tropical punch.
While you're putting in the tropical punch, start to stir it.
Last, stir in the sugar.

title: fresh florida corn chowder
directions: Cut kernels from cobs; set aside.
In large pan, melt butter over medium heat.
Saute onion and celery for about 3 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Stir in flour; cook and stir for 1 minute. Slowly stir in milk, salt and pepper.
Bring to the boiling point, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens slightly.
Stir in corn and simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.
Stir in cheese; heat until cheese melts.
Serve at once in bowls and sprinkle with paprika.

title: holiday breakfast bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients. Add blended eggs and oil. Mix. Add remaining 5 ingredients. Makes 2 loaves of bread. Grease and flour pans. Pour mixture into pans. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: special potatoes
directions: Put hashbrowns in a greased 9x13 pan. Mix all other ingredients (salt and pepper to taste). Pour mixture over hashbrowns and bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: when the wife's away taco salad
directions: Brown beef; drain fat.
Add seasoning and 1 cup water.
Simmer to thicken.
On a large plate layer beef, lettuce, tomato, sour cream, kidney beans, sauce and cheese.
Enjoy.

title: no peeky chicky
directions: Preheat oven to 275°. Remove the skin from the chicken.
Place the chicken in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine soups, rice and water in a large mixing bowl. Mix well, then pour mixture over the chicken. Cover the pan with aluminum foil; bake for 2 hours. Do not peek until done.

title: barbecued beans
directions: Saute beef, onion and celery in small amount of oil until soft.
Combine all other ingredients, except bacon, in casserole. Place bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.
Can do ahead.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Cook peaches in 2 tablespoons sugar a few minutes; then add to first mixture.
Pour in 9-inch pie crust and bake about 45 minutes (until firm) at 350°.
Beat egg whites with 3 teaspoons sugar until stiff and return to oven until meringue browns.

title: flank steak kabobs
directions: If you use white wine, you may need 1/4 to 1/2 cup brown sugar. Serves 4 to 6.

title: camp caramel corn
directions: Slowly	bring the margarine, sugar, syrup and salt to a boil. Continue
cooking
for 10 minutes.	Add baking soda and then quickly pour over the popcorn.
Stir to coat evenly.
Put 14-inch Dutch oven over low heat fire for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: turkey divan
directions: Layer broccoli spears in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan sprayed with Pam.
Slice the turkey in 1/4-inch slices and layer on top of broccoli.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli as directed and drain.
Mix eggs, pepper, salt, cracker crumbs and cheese in casserole.
Add the broccoli and drizzle melted butter over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in blender except oil.
Whip on high until smooth.
Very, very slowly, add the oil; continue to whip until well blended.

title: cherry coconut bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
With hands or pastry blender, mix 1 cup flour, margarine and powdered sugar until smooth.
Spread thin with fingers in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake about 25 minutes.
Stir all remaining ingredients into beaten eggs.
Spread over base. Bake 25 minutes more.
Cool.
Makes 20 (3 x 1-inch) bars.

title: cafe au lait(france)
directions: Make coffee.
Heat milk to scalding.
Pour hot coffee and milk into serving cups at the same time (use equal amounts of each).

title: apple turnovers
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine butter, cream cheese and egg yolk. Beat until smooth.
Add flour and mix well.
Chill.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle corn flakes mixed with 1/2 cup of butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: audrey's buttermilk chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Dip chicken in 1/2 cup buttermilk, then roll in flour/pepper mixture.
Put oil in a baking dish and heat in oven for a minute.
Then place chicken in hot oil, breast side down.
Bake 30 minutes, uncovered.
Turn chicken and bake 15 minutes more.
Turn chicken again and pour the soup/1 cup buttermilk mixture over chicken.
Bake 15 minutes more.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Bone chicken.
Place in buttered dish.
Mix soups and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Mix together stuffing mix and chicken broth.
Top casserole with this mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Cook butter, sugar, pineapple juice, egg, flour and salt in double boiler until thick.
Stir to keep smooth.
Cool.
Add lemon juice.
Cut Marshmallows into small pieces.
Mix with cherries , nuts, and fruit cocktail and add to above.
Add whipped cream, pour into freezer trays.
Freeze over night.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Cook broccoli until tender and drain.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix together soup, cheese, milk, mayo and egg, then pour over broccoli.
Mix together the bread crumbs and butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cabbage-patch casserole
directions: *Or enough to cover medium-sized greased roaster pan 2/3 full, leaving enough space for hamburg mix and soup.

title: orange chiffon salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and fold in orange sherbet.
When partially set, fold in marshmallows, pineapple, orange and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for 1 hour or until firm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Begin to add
to batter, alternating with buttermilk (1 cup). Beat well after each addition.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan
or
stem pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 1/4 hours.
Cool
in
pan
minutes.
Invert
on
cooling racks. Continue to cool.

title: vanessa's quiche
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Prick pie crust all over with fork, line with fork and bake 12 minutes.
Remove foil; bake 5 more minutes. Brush crust with beaten egg white.
Bake 2 more minutes.
Beat eggs, milk, parsley, salt and peppers.
Sprinkle crust with bacon, cheese and onions.
Pour egg mixture over and bake until puffed and golden, about 25 minutes. (Quiche will finish setting after you take it out of oven.)

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and de-stem mushrooms.
Chop mushrooms stems and add the remaining ingredients.
Fill mushroom caps with spinach mixture. Drizzle with melted butter or margarine.
Broil, stuffed side up, for 5 to 8 minutes, until heated.

title: wilma's kolaches
directions: Turn out on lightly floured board and knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl.
Brush with melted shortening. Cover.
Let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk (about 2 hours).

title: chicken breast supreme
directions: Sprinkle breasts with salt.
Wrap each chicken breast with a bacon strip.
Place chicken in single layer in shallow baking dish.
Cover with mixture of sour cream and mushroom soup. Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 250° for 4 hours.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Heat cream cheese and butter. Add corn and jalapeno peppers. Pour into greased baking dish. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: rummy chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in rum about 2 hours; coat with crumbs and brown in butter over medium heat.
Put 1 teaspoon of oil in pan before butter to prevent burning.
Place in a shallow baking dish and salt lightly.
Pour rum marinade into butter drippings. Swish together and pour over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix regular corn, creamed corn, corn meal, beaten eggs and sour cream.
Spray an 11 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Pour mixture in pan.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top of cheese.
Cut up stick of margarine and sprinkle on top of bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: nana's sloppy joes
directions: Mix together.
Bring to boil.
Add chipped ham, a few slices at a time, to make sure all is covered.
Simmer about 30 minutes or longer for thicker sauce.
More chipped ham can be added.

title: grandmother lowman's sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and then add beaten eggs, cream and vanilla.
Sift other dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Roll out very thin on a lightly floured board or pastry cloth.
Cut with a cookie cutter and bake on lightly greased baking sheets at 375° until slightly browned.

title: fruit milk shake
directions: Blend first four ingredients until smooth.
Sweeten to taste (yields 1 cup).

title: california party punch
directions: Mix frozen juices with water as directed on cans.
Mix all juices together.
Cut ice cream and sherbet in 2-inch squares and add to fruit juices.
Chill.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: decorators icing
directions: Using mixer, mix Crisco, syrup, almond flavoring, salt and butter flavoring together.
Gradually add sifted powdered sugar and water to mixture and beat well.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Combine sugar and eggs.
Mix flour and meal.
Add to sugar and eggs.
Gradually add milk, butter, lemon juice and rind.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: apple crisp delight
directions: Butter a baking dish.
Put in the apples and water.
With a fork, mix flour, sugars, cinnamon, butter and salt.
Spread mixture over apples and bake at 350° until apples are tender and topping is crisp, about 40 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: walnut cherry delight
directions: Mix together flour, butter, brown sugar, coconut and 1 cup of nuts. Reserve 1/2 cup of this mixture for topping. Bake the first layer in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook rice as per directions.
In a medium saucepan, heat onions with chili, just enough to melt fat in chili.
Add rice to chili and onions.
Remove paper wrapping from tamales.
Place in a square baking dish and cut into bite-size pieces.
Crush chips over top of tamales.
If you like a lot of cheese, spread a thin layer on top.
Pour rice mixture over top and spread evenly.
Top with a generous layer of cheese and bake for 30 minutes.

title: mom's pound cake
directions: Sift the 3 cups of flour and measure the 3 cups again. Resift with baking soda; set aside. In another bowl, place the softened butter; beat until creamy.
Slowly add sugar, 1 cup at a time, beating well until light yellow and creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Slowly add flour mixture, 1 cup at a time, beating well after each addition.
Then, add sour cream, pinch of salt and vanilla.
Mix until well blended.
Bake in a greased, floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cake is done when cake tester comes out clean.
Remove from oven; wait 5 minutes, then turn out on a wire cooling rack.
Yield: 16 servings.

title: date treasure cake
directions: *Substitute 2 cups whole apricots for dates.

title: chicken soup
directions: Boil chicken in 1 gallon water until tender (approximately 1 hour).
Skin and debone; discard water.
Then in 3 quarts fresh water, simmer chicken, bouillon, carrots and potatoes.
Will be fork-tender in about 30 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: green tomato jam
directions: Put tomatoes in blender and blend well.
Put in pan.
Add sugar.
Mix well.
Boil for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Jell-O.
Put into containers.
Cool and freeze.

title: holiday yams
directions: Combine sugars and cornstarch; blend well.
Stir in orange juice, butter and salt.
Simmer over low heat, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Place yams in a lightly greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Add orange sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Yields 6 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix meat thoroughly with egg, rolled oats and seasonings. Place in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° about 1 1/2 hours.
Last 30 minutes pour catsup on top and return to oven.
Serves 6.

title: squash pie
directions: Cook squash; drain well.
Mix all ingredients with electric mixer or blender until well blended.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pinwheels
directions: Tightly roll up a slice of meat and cheese together with cheese on top.
Secure with toothpicks placed at an angle, lengthwise the roll.
Cut between the toothpicks.
Add an olive or a pickle to the end to keep it from unrolling.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour 1 1/2 cups hot water over oats.
Let stand.
Cream together brown sugar, white sugar and oil.
Beat 2 eggs into the cream mixture.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture; then add oats.
Beat well. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: edna earl vanhoose rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased muffin pan. Bake at 450° until brown.

title: apricot snacks
directions: Spread dab of cream cheese on dried fruit-apricot. Top with pecan half. Chill in refrigerator and serve.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Spread sauerkraut in greased baking dish.
Top with sliced tomato, salad dressing and corn beef cut in bite size pieces. Sprinkle with the cheese.
Toss bread crumbs with melted margarine and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake uncovered at 375 for 20-25 minutes.

title: mock apple butter
directions: Peel and seed zucchini; chop coarsely.
Put in blender with vinegar; blend until smooth.
Pour into saucepan with remaining ingredients and cook, stirring occasionally, until mixture reaches desired thickness.
Cool and keep refrigerated.

title: zucchini special
directions: In large saucepan, cook zucchini covered in boiling water until crisp-tender, about 4 to 5 minutes.
Drain well; set aside. In same saucepan, cook onion and green pepper in oleo just until tender.
Remove from burner and add drained mushrooms, dry spaghetti sauce mix, water and tomato paste.
Mix well.
Gently stir in zucchini and Mozzarella cheese.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: kentucky supper salad
directions: Mix all ingredients carefully so as to mash peas.
(I do this with my hands, but if you are more sophisticated a fork will do.) Salt and pepper to taste.
Place in lettuce leaf lined bowl. Refrigerate until serving time.

title: caesar salad
directions: Clean romaine and tear in bite sized pieces; pat dry on paper towels.
Wrap in plastic film (or plastic bag) and store in vegetable crisper in refrigerator until crisp and cold-several hours or overnight.

title: easy roast chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Mix well remaining ingredients; pour over chicken.
Roast in preheated 350° oven, basting every 15 to 20 minutes, for 45 to 60 minutes or until golden brown and fork-tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
