directions: Cream shortening; add sugar gradually.
Add eggs and mix well until blended.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, nutmeg, soda, salt, allspice and cinnamon.
Add to the creamed mixture. Add pumpkin and vanilla; mix until well blended.
Fold in nutmeats and pour into four greased loaf pans.
Bake in preheated oven for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cut cheese into strips that will fit into chute of food processor.
Lock bowl into position and place shredder disc inside.
Cover.
Fill chute almost to the top with pieces of cheese.
Process at high speed to grate.
Remove shredder disc and cheese.
Position bowl again and put steel blade in place.
Chop onion at high speed.
Add cheese, peanuts, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Process to blend thoroughly at high speed.
Form into a ball.
Wrap in plastic wrap.
Chill thoroughly.
Makes 1 1/4 pounds.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine all ingredients into 1 pie crust.
Place 2nd pie crust on top.
Cut slit in top with a fork.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: instant cocoa mix
directions: Mix in a very large bowl.
Store in airtight container.
Use 1/4 cup mixture for each cup of hot chocolate.

title: chocolate eclair delight
directions: Mix instant pudding mixes with the milk.
When mixed, fold in the Cool Whip.
This is the filling.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: In blender beat eggs.
Gradually add sugar.
Mixture will be thick.
Add a little half and half.
Add vanilla and dash of salt. Pour remaining half and half into ice cream freezer.
Add a layer of ice cubes. Pour 1/2 cup salt over ice.
Continue layering. Pour 1 cup water over top of layers.
About 30 minutes in electric ice cream freezer.

title: squash 'n swiss cheese casserole
directions: Cook squash, onions, bay leaves parsley and thyme in salted water until squash is tender.
Drain.
Remove bay leaves and parsley; set aside.

title: soup's on
directions: Bring water to a boil in large saucepan; add 2 cups of the broccoli, 1/2 cup carrots and onion.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: fudgy brownie cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In top of double boiler over hot, not simmering, water, melt together the chocolates and butter.
Add coffee powder and stir well.
Remove from heat and cool to room temperature.

title: egg yolk paint
directions: Mix egg yolk and water.
Divide mixture among several small cups.
Tint each with different food color to make bright colors. If paint thickens, stir in a few drops of water.
Paint your cookies with a small paint brush.
Then bake your cookies.

title: easy orange chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish and season.
Mix melted butter with orange juice.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with poultry seasoning or thyme.
Turn and baste with juice mixture.
Broil for 15 minutes or until chicken is crisp and tender.

title: decadent brownies
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Thoroughly coat a 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick spray.
With an electric mixer combine sugar and cocoa. Gradually pour in egg substitute and jam, beating on low speed until sugar is no longer grainy.
Add the vanilla, salt and almond extract and beat briefly.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt and stir with rubber spatula.
Pour into pan and bake 30 to 35 minutes. After cooling, cut brownies into 2 x 2-inch bars.
Makes 24 brownies.
Low-fat.
Per bar:
114 calories, 0.7 grams fat, 26 grams carbohydrates, 86 milligrams sodium and no cholesterol.

title: mock sour cream
directions: Blend in blender for 10 seconds.

title: nancy caldwell's zucchini bread
directions: Combine zucchini and beaten eggs.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Can be made in loaf pans, an angel food pan or Bundt pan.
Yields 2 loaves or 3 small.

title: chimichangas
directions: In medium saucepan, combine all ingredients except tortillas and oil.
Bring to boil.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer about 2 hours.
(Meat will be very tender.)
Uncover and boil rapidly 15 minutes or until water has almost evaporated.
Remove from heat. Shred meat with two forks.
Heat tortillas 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Spoon 1/4 cup filling on each tortilla near one edge.
Fold edge nearest filling up and over just until filling is covered. Fold sides envelope fashion and then roll up.
Fasten with toothpick, if necessary.
In heavy skillet, fry filled tortillas in 1/2-inch hot fat about 1 minute on each side or until golden. Drain.
Keep warm in 300° oven.
Garnish with lettuce, guacamole and sour cream.

title: recipe for soul winners
directions: To Prepare:
Mix all ingredients together, sifting in some discipline and 1 heaping cupful of compassion.
Place all in the boiling pan of belief in Christ, then heat it with a willingness to serve others, constrained by the love of God.
Be sure to share with others, or it will become stale.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs, salt, baking powder, buttermilk, vanilla and flour.
Mix real well.
Turn batter into pans.
Cook at 350° for 25 minutes (35 minutes for oblong cake).

title: oatmeal molasses cake(no eggs)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, sugar, baking soda, salt, oatmeal, raisins and allspice with fork in ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar if desired.
Makes 9 servings.
Contains 350 calories.
Surprisingly delicious!!!

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in large bowl.

Cut in shortening and mix thoroughly. Add buttermilk and dissolved yeast. Work together with large spoon until all flour is moistened. Cover bowl and put in refrigerator until ready to use as needed. When ready to use, take out as much as needed.
Roll on floured board to 1/2-inch thickness and cut. Bake at 425° for between 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.
This dough will keep in refrigerator several weeks.

title: eggnog
directions: In a large saucepan, mix eggs, milk and 1/3 cup sugar.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture coats a metal spoon. Remove from heat.
Cool quickly by placing pan in a sink of ice water and stirring 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in vanilla.
Chill 4 to 24 hours.
At serving time, in a bowl, whip cream and 2 tablespoons sugar until soft peaks form.
Transfer chilled egg mixture to punch bowl.
Fold in whipped cream mixture.
Serve at once.
Sprinkle each serving with nutmeg.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Take the orange juice (thawed) and add water, sugar and crushed pineapple.
Drain the fruit cocktail, pineapple, cherries and oranges. Add to orange juice mixture.
Add the bananas (sliced).
Freeze until frozen.

title: fern's chocolate dessert
directions: Mix
together
and
pat
in pan (9 x 13-inch).	Bake at 350° for 10 minutes and cool.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Add vanilla, color, flour, salt, cocoa and buttermilk.
Beat well.
Mix vinegar and soda together and add to batter.
Fold in with a spoon.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apple relish
directions: Apples, peppers, onions----peel, chop, or put through food chopper.
Add all other ingredients.
Boil 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pack into hot jars and seal.

title: eggplant supreme(makes 8 servings)
directions: In a large nonstick skillet, combine eggplant, onion, green pepper, mushrooms, garlic and oil.
Simmer, covered, over medium heat for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add small amounts of water, if necessary, to prevent drying.
Add remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat to low; simmer, covered, for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Place in bowl and chill thoroughly.
Serve cold.

title: buttery dill fish
directions: *Margarine may be substituted.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Pour juices in 10-cup percolator and fill with water.
Add other ingredients to percolator basket.
Let perk through cycle.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients
and pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: crab spread
directions: Mix ingredients and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: plowlines or funnel cake
directions: A long, long chain is right,

title: chicken dressing
directions: Mix chicken broth, bread crumbs, cream of chicken soup and margarine.
Mix well.
Add eggs, onions and celery.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into a greased baking pan or glass baking dish.
Cut chicken up and place on top of dressing before baking. Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: swiss steak
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper. Rub into steak or pound in. Cut into 8 portions.
Peel and slice onions.
Preheat pan. Add half of the Crisco, then onions.
Brown lightly.
Remove from skillet.
Add remaining shortening.
Brown steak on both sides. Reduce heat.
Add celery, garlic, chili sauce and water. Cover. Simmer 1 hour.
Cut green pepper into slices.
Add pepper and onions to meat.
Continue cooking 30 minutes or until meat is tender.

title: family favorite chicken and stuffing bake
directions: Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions adding carrots, celery and onion with seasoning packet.
Combine soup, milk and parsley; set aside.

title: bite size pizza
directions: Lay biscuits out on cookie sheet.
Gently spread, leaving small outer rim.
Spoon out pizza sauce onto each biscuit.
Add pepperoni or favorite toppings.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake according to directions on biscuits can or until cheese is melted and dough is golden brown.

title: baked brisket
directions: Combine Cook-In-Sauce and broth in a large bowl.
Roll meat in sauce until thoroughly covered.
Place in roasting pan and pour remaining sauce over meat. Cover with foil.
Bake in a 250° oven for about 3 hours.
Cool thoroughly before slicing.
Slice thin and place back in sauce overnight.
Heat before serving.
(Woody's Cook-In-Sauce may be purchased from Winn-Dixie stores.)

title: ricotta cheese cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Pour into ungreased 12 x 9-inch pan.
Mix together Ricotta cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Pour over batter in cake pan.
Do not mix! Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: bubbly squeak
directions: Slice potatoes into skillet; sprinkle with salt.
Slice onion over potatoes.
Slice sausage in bite size pieces; add to skillet. Shred cabbage on top and cover.
Add salt to cabbage to taste. Simmer until cabbage is done; do not stir.
When dish starts bubbling and squeaking, it's cooking just right.
A little water may be added 5 minutes before serving to loosen the potatoes from the pan.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together; roll into a log.
Cover with wax paper with chopped pecans.
Roll cheese log in pecans and chill.

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: Stir together milk, cream of chicken soup and onion soup mix; set aside 1/2 cup of soup mixture.
Mix vegetables and rice.
Pour mixture into 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch dish.
Place chicken on top and pour the remaining 1/2 cup of soup mixture over chicken and sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours at 375°.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix sugar, bananas, oil and eggs in a large bowl with a wooden spoon.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° until a wooden pick inserted in center of the bread comes out clean, 60 to 70 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes, then loosen sides of loaf from pan and remove.
Let cool completely before slicing.
Makes 1 loaf.
Freezes well.

title: vegetable salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine drained corn, green beans and peas. Add onion, green pepper and celery.
In a saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper and bring to a boil.
Pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate in metal or glass container.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar well.
Add eggs one at a time, then add flour, 1 cup at a time.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Put in cold oven and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sugarless applesauce cake
directions: Combine raisins, fruit and water in saucepan.
Cook, uncovered, until water is evaporated and fruit is soft.
Set aside to cool.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Melt margarine in large skillet.
Add onion and pepper.
Cook until tender.
Stir in soup and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Add tuna and cooked noodles.
Pour in 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with potato chips.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: roasted red pepper pesto cheesecake
directions: Mix crumbs and butter. Press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan. Bake at 325° for 10 minutes. Mix cream cheese and Ricotta until well blended. Add eggs, 1 at a time, mixing well after each. Blend in remaining ingredients. Pour over crust. Bake at 325° for 55 minutes to 1 hour or until center is almost set. Run knife on metal spatula around pan rim to loosen cake. Cool before removing. Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight. Let stand at room temperature 15 minutes before serving. Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: pumpkin cake roll dessert
directions: Beat eggs at high speed for 5 minutes.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Fold dry, sifted ingredients into the pumpkin mixture.
Spread onto greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Top with walnuts.
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 minutes.
Turn out onto a towel sprinkled with confectioners sugar.
Starting at narrow end, roll cake and towel together.
Cool.
Unroll; spread filling over cooled cake.
Roll. Wrap in waxed paper and foil.
Freeze.
Slice and serve plain or with whipped topping.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Drain shrimp; save juice.
Heat tomato soup in pan, but do not boil.
Blend in cream cheese to melt.
Mix gelatin with shrimp juice and fold into tomato soup and cream cheese mixture.
Add mayonnaise and blend with mixture.
Fold in green pepper, onion and shrimp.
Put in quart mold and refrigerate.
To serve, unmold and serve with crackers.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cook raisins until done (let water be level with raisins when finished cooking).
Mix sugar and flour together; add this plus other ingredients to raisins and water.
Bring to boil and pour into 2 pie shells.

title: stuffing and chicken casserole
directions: Combine stuffing mix, margarine and broth in bowl; mix well. Press half of mixture over bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Combine chicken, onion, celery, salad dressing, eggs, milk and salt in medium bowl; mix well.
Spoon into prepared dish.
Top with remaining stuffing mixture.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.
tags: Stove Top corn bread stuffing mix

title: cracklin bread
directions: Use enough hot water to make into thick enough to shape into small loaves.
Use cracklins with the least fat.
I break them into small pieces.
Bake in moderate oven (400° to 450°) for about 45 minutes.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Saute green pepper, onion and mushrooms in oil (use large skillet).
Add squash. Cover and steam until vegetables are tender. Drain off liquid and add Ricotta cheese. Set aside.
In saucepan, heat together tomato sauce and spices.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan (sprayed with nonstick spray), layer half the vegetable mixture, half of the lasagna noodles and half of the sauce. Repeat with one more layer of each in the same order.
Bake, uncovered, in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes. Sprinkle cheese on top and bake another 10 minutes.
Let set 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: meat loaf with vegetables
directions: Mix ingredients and shape in loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cabbage roll casserole
directions: Butter a good sized casserole dish that can be covered.
Line the dish completely with cabbage leaves.
Fry hamburger, onion, salt and pepper until meat loses its red coloring.
Mix rice into the meat.
Pile mixture into cabbage leaves.
Fix more cabbage leaves over top of meat.
Pour tomato juice or sauce over all. Cover and bake at 350° for at least an hour, until leaves are very tender.

title: perfect chocolate cake
directions: Beat
cocoa and boiling water with wire whip, let cool. Sift flour
before
measuring,
then sift baking soda, baking powder and salt; sift together.
Beat sugar, Crisco, eggs and vanilla; beat 5 minutes.
Beat in flour and cocoa mixture (in fours) start with
cocoa
and end with flour; beat but do not overbeat.
Pour in
layer
cake pans and bake in 350° oven until
done.
Put cream
cheese
frosting
between
layers of completely cooled cake and chocolate frosting on top.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat eggs in, one at a time, until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sifted dry ingredients.
Blend in remaining ingredients until well combined.
Bake in a greased loaf pan about 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: wild rice salad
directions: Cook rice mix according to package directions; cool slightly. Stir in peas and remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill at least 3 hours.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, bananas, flour and nuts. Mix all well and bake in greased loaf pan at about 300° for 1 hour.

title: meat loaf(one of mayor bob's favorites!)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour 1 cup of picante sauce and put a little bit of brown sugar over it.
Bake it in the oven at 350° for an hour.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Grease 2-quart baking dish; cover bottom with bread pieces. Top with eggplant, celery, pepper and onions, sausage and tomatoes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add remaining bread crumbs and cheese.
Return to oven 3 or 4 minutes until cheese melts.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Take 1 large field, half a dozen children, 2 or 3 small dogs, a pinch of brook and some pebbles.
Mix the children and the dogs together well; put them on the field, stirring constantly.
Pour the brook over the pebbles; sprinkle the field with flowers. Spread over all a deep blue sky and bake in the sun.
When brown, set away to cool in the bathtub.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Saute bacon; drain and crumble.
Add onion.
Heat together milk, rice, soup and cheese.
Add bacon and onion.
Wonderful and easy.

title: onion dip
directions: In a medium bowl, blend onion soup mix, sour cream, Worcestershire sauce, cayenne pepper and oregano.
Mix well. Cover; refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Serve with chips or fresh vegetables.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: spinach and eggs grisanti
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions. Drain thoroughly, pressing out as much liquid as you can. *The dish improves in proportion to the amount of liquid you press out.

title: quick tater tot bake
directions: In skillet, brown the meat and onions.
Drain any fat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place in a greased 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: swedish hash
directions: Brown beef
and onions.
Add remaining ingredients; pour into greased dish.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: peanut butter eggs
directions: Cream all ingredients together.
Shape and chill.
Coat chilled eggs with chocolate.
May use chocolate coating caps as directed.

title: crisp chicken bake
directions: Place chicken in shallow casserole.
Combine mushroom soup, sour cream, dry onion soup and pepper.
Spread over chicken.
Top with noodles.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: buttermilk pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy, adding 1/2 cup sugar at a time.
Blend in vanilla.
Add eggs one at a time.
Combine flour and salt.
Add buttermilk. Sprinkle pecans in bottom of pie crust.
Pour custard mix over the pecans and bake 1 hour and 30 minutes at 300°.
The top browns as it cooks.
Best served at room temperature.

title: fruit cake(icebox)
directions: Crush graham crackers and fruit.
Add spices and whipped cream; mix all together.
Save enough crushed graham crackers to roll cake in.
Wrap in waxed paper; store in refrigerator.

title: scones
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, butter or margarine, egg, sugar, raisins and enough milk to form a ball (soft and doughy).
Roll out dough on floured surface. Cut with 3-inch glass approximately 1/2-inch thick.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly brown.
Makes 12 scones.

title: smelly jelly (non-edible)
directions: Heat half of liquid potpourri to boiling point.
Add gelatin; mix until dissolved. Add salt (prevents mold).
Pour into jelly jars and seal with lids.
Makes 4 (4 ounce) jars.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage until done.
Stir until crumbled.
Drain.
Set aside.
Butter each slice of bread and cut in cubes.
Place in 13 x 9-inch dish.
Sprinkle with sausage.
Top with cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients and beat well.
Pour over mixture.
Chill at least 8 hours.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve cut into squares.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage; crumble and drain well.
Line a 9 x 13-inch glass casserole dish with buttered bread, buttered side down. Layer sausage over bread.
In blender, beat 10 eggs and 1/2 cup sour cream.
Pour over sausage and bread.
In blender chop green chillies.
Pour over eggs (or spoon).
Top with Cheddar cheese. Cover with plastic wrap and leave in refrigerator overnight.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until puffed and browned.

title: cream cheese pie crust
directions: Combine cream cheese and butter; blend well, then stir in flour.
Shape dough into a ball.
Place ball between 2 sheets of wax paper.
Roll out into a circle to fit a deep dish pie plate. Remove one sheet of waxed paper and position cream cheese crust into pie plate.
Remove top sheet of waxed paper and flute the edge of crust.
Fill with sweet potato mixture and bake.
Makes 1 deep dish pie.

title: hamburger helper soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in sauce mix, bay leaf, salt, pepper, tomatoes with liquid, and break up tomatoes.
Heat to boiling; stir constantly.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer, stir occasionally for 15 minutes.
Stir in noodles and vegetables, cover and cook 10 minutes.
Tastes even better the next day!

title: meat loaf cabbage rolls
directions: Cook outside cabbage leaves for 2 to 3 minutes in boiling, salted water.
Wrap leaves around pieces of meat loaf.
Place in casserole.
Top with tomato soup.
Bake, uncovered, in a moderate oven at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar, egg and peanut butter. Mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Toss together pineapple chunks and bread crumbs.
Combine sugar, eggs and melted butter.
Pour over pineapple mixture in greased 2-quart dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Great with pork!

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix the sugar, milk and cocoa and boil for 1 minute.
Add oats, peanut butter and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: jello cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix jello, marshmallows and water and let cool until syrupy. Add pineapple, cream and cottage cheese and mix.
Pour into flat glass dish.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaf.
(I substitute small box of Cool Whip for cream.)

title: individual desserts
directions: Place vanilla wafers in cupcake liners in muffin tin.
Mix cream cheese, eggs and sugar.
Put mixture on top of vanilla wafers.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.
Chill.
Top with favorite pie filling or mini chips.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix cucumber, pepper and onion in large bowl.
Mix other ingredients and pour over cucumbers.
Refrigerate for 24 hours. Put in plastic containers and freeze.

title: bread stuffing
directions: In a large skillet, cook onion and celery in butter, stirring often, until onion is tender.
Stir in about 1/3 of the bread cubes.
Turn into deep bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and toss. Stuff turkey just before roasting.
Makes 9 cups (12 pound turkey).

title: garbanzo salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, saving enough anchovies and eggs for garnish.
Toss lightly.
Serve in individual bowls lined with lettuce.
Garnish with chopped eggs and anchovy strips.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: oreo cake
directions: Scrape filling from cookies. Mix cookies with butter in 9 x 13 pan. Cover cookies with ice cream.

title: mrs. sophia's tea cakes
directions: Cream together sugar, margarine, egg, milk and vanilla until fluffy.
Sift together and stir in flour, baking powder and salt.

title: memphis corn pudding
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
in
a
large bowl until blended. Spray baking
dish
with	Pam.
Pour
into a square 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for approximately 40 to 50 minutes or until set or lightly brown.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Remove skin and bones from chicken.
Cut into pieces about 1 1/2-inches square.
Wash, trim and cut coarse tops from onions into 2 1/2-inch lengths, then cut to make strips about 1/4-inch thick.
Arrange chicken and onions on a plate.
Cover and refrigerate until needed.

title: shrimp new orleans
directions: Combine ingredients except shrimp; season.
Pour over shrimp; toss lightly.
Chill 2 hours.
Serve on shredded lettuce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: twenty-four hour salad
directions: In a double boiler, beat egg with a fork; stir in lemon juice, sugar and salt.
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat and allow to cool completely.
Fold in whipped cream, marshmallows and fruits. Refrigerate for 24 hours.
To serve, fold in almonds and arrange on crisp greens.

title: chocolate snack cake
directions: Cook pudding as directed on box.
Add cake mix to pudding. Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Saute meat and onion.
Place 3 cups cabbage in quart casserole; cover with meat mixture; top with remaining.
Place soup over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spring pie
directions: In medium bowl, stir boiling water into gelatin until completely dissolved.
Add sherbet; mix until melted.
Refrigerate about 25 minutes, or until mixture is slightly thickened.
Fold in whipped topping, marshmallows and pineapple.
Pour into crust. Freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer 20 to 30 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind together zucchini, onion and green pepper.
Add salt and let stand overnight.
In the morning, rinse with 1 pint of water, squeeze dry and then add remaining ingredients.
Cook 30 minutes. Put in sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 6 to 7 pints per batch. Recipe of G. Aunt Jane.

title: brownies made with cake mix
directions: Stir together the ingredients (it will be very thick).
Press into a greased 9 x 14-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes for a chewy brownie (slightly longer for a cake type).

title: lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Combine cake mix and sugar in a large mixing bowl. Add oil, water, yogurt, egg substitute and lemon juice. Beat at medium speed for 6 minutes. Stir in poppy seed.
Spray Bundt pan with Baker's Joy or Pam.
Pour in batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Remove from pan and drizzle with Lemon Glaze.

title: roast chicken with lemon and garlic
directions: Preheat oven to 450° to 500°.
Remove chicken parts from cavity of the bird.
Wash bird inside out.
Pat dry.
Rub skin with olive oil.
With an ice pick, poke about 2 dozen holes in each lemon. Break 1 head of garlic into cloves; peel and remove ends.
Stuff the cavity of the bird with the 2 lemons, the garlic cloves and half the thyme.

title: mexicana chicken
directions: Flour, salt and pepper chicken and fry in butter.
Remove chicken and add other ingredients.	Add chicken, 1 bay leaf, 1 1/2 cups chicken broth or stock and 1 cup tomatoes (drained).
Cover and simmer 1 hour.	Cook rice to make 3 cups.
Alternate layers of chicken and rice in buttered casserole after bones have been removed from chicken.
Sprinkle top with soft cheese and bake until well browned.

title: date roll
directions: Crush vanilla wafers and mix in dates and pecans.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over mixture and mix well.
Divide dough in 2 parts and shape into a log.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Refrigerate until firm before slicing.

title: purple lady
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir well.
Add undrained blueberries and pineapple.
Let thicken in refrigerator.
Fold in Cool Whip and pecans.
Pour into lightly greased mold or glass baking dish.
Return to refrigerator.
Serve when set.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Melt 1/4 pound butter; break up 3 slices of bread in small pieces and mix with butter.
Beat 2 eggs light and add sugar, salt and pineapple (juice and all).
Add buttered crumbs.
Pour into an ungreased baking dish.
Sprinkle lightly with nutmeg or mace. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
(May be stretched by adding 2 more slices of bread.)
If doubling recipe, use only 4 eggs.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Melt butter.
Mix all ingredients together; add to butter. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: frozen apple yogurt
directions: Mix yogurt, cinnamon and honey in blender.
Stir in applesauce.
Pour into individual containers.
Freeze at least 3 to 4 hours.
Let soften 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 4.

title: apple pecan muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 1/2-cup muffin cups.
Sift all-purpose flour, baking soda, ground cinnamon and salt into medium bowl.
Combine sugar, oil, egg, lemon juice, vanilla and lemon peel in large bowl; whisk to blend.
Mix in dry ingredients, then apples and pecans.
Spoon 1/3 cup batter into each prepared muffin cup.
Bake until tester inserted into centers comes out clean, about 35 minutes.
Turn muffins out onto rack; cool slightly.
Serve warm.
Makes 12 servings.

title: party mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Melt butter in a shallow baking pan. Stir in salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add Chex and peanuts.
Mix until all pieces are coated.
Heat in oven for 45 to 60 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool.
Store in an airtight container.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Boil chicken and save broth.
Slowly mix water with flour to make a smooth ball.
Place ball on floured surface and roll out flat.
Have broth boiling.
Cut dough into short strips and place a few at a time into boiling broth.
Stir to keep from sticking. Add chicken soup and milk.
Continue to stir.
Add margarine and stir.
Reduce heat and cook 10 minutes. (Watch carefully; dumplings will stick to bottom of pan.)

title: pumpkin custard pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugar and pudding in a large bowl.
Add spices. Fold in topping.
Pour into two 9-inch pie shells (graham cracker or vanilla wafer crusts are good).
Let set in refrigerator.

title: banana slush punch
directions: Heat water and sugar until dissolved.
Add juices and bananas. Pour into ice cube trays, a shallow pan or empty milk carton; freeze.
Thaw 2 to 3 hours to form a slush.
Place in punch bowl. Add tonic water.
Yields about 27 cups.

title: pineapple angel food trifle
directions: Drain pineapple tidbits, reserving 1 cup juice, set aside. Combine instant pudding mix, 1/2 cup reserved juice, and milk in a large bowl, beat at low speed with an electric mixer 2 minutes or until thickened.
Fold in sour cream and pineapple tidbits.
Place one third of cake cubes in bottom of a 16 cup glass bowl, drizzle with 2 or 3 tbsp. remaining reserved pineapple juice.
Spoon one third pudding mix over cake.
Repeat twice ending with pudding mixture.
Cover and chill at least 3 hours - Spread before serving with cool whip.
Garnish with mint leaves, canned pineapple or cherries.

title: grandma judi's golden fowl
directions: Wipe the fowl dry.
Pour Planters peanut oil in the palm of your clean hand and rub into the fowl thoroughly.
Massaging the oil into the skin of the fowl.
Cut the apples in halves (no need to peel) and place into the fowl cavities.
Sprinkle generously with the lemon pepper and garlic seasonings and parsley.
Grill on barbecue until golden or put into a 350° oven uncovered until golden.
Serve with seasoned rice and your choice of vegetable.

title: zucchini refrigerator pickles
directions: Pack zucchini, onions and dill in gallon glass or plastic jar. Combine rest of ingredients and bring to a full rolling boil. Let cool.
Pour over zucchini.
It will not cover all but more juice will form after a couple of hours.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: mints
directions: Mix and knead as for pie dough.
Roll in balls the size of a marble.
Dip one side in a small amount of granulated sugar. Press sugar side into mint mold.
Unmold at once on waxed paper.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into well-greased baking dish.
Prepare topping.

title: fish pie
directions: Make crust of cracker crumbs and melted oleo and press into 8-inch pie plate.
Saute onions in oleo until lightly browned. Add chicken stock and stir.
Spoon onions into cracker crust. Place fish fillets over onions. Beat eggs, milk and seasonings and pour on top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cincinnati chili
directions: Into water, crumble raw hamburger.
Do not brown.
Add all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 3 hours.
Remove garlic clove and bay leaves.
Add whole red peppers if desired.

title: sausage and egg puff
directions: Butter bread and cut into small cubes.
Brown sausage in skillet, making sure there are no large lumps.
Drain.
In 2-quart casserole, layer sausage, bread and cheese.
In a bowl, beat eggs with milk, Tabasco sauce, salt, mustard and Worcestershire sauce. Pour mixture over sausage, bread and cheese. Cover and refrigerate 12 hours or overnight.
Remove 1 hour before cooking.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes or until firm and golden on top. Serves 8.
Make a day ahead.

title: 7-layer casserole
directions: Place rice, corn, tomato sauce and water in layers in a 2 quart baking dish with
a
tight fitting lid.
Pour over all onion, pepper, ground beef,
salt and pepper.
Pour second can of tomato sauce and 1/4 can
water
over all.	Put 4 strips of bacon to cover meat.
Bake
in
a
preheated
oven for 1 hour, covered.
Uncover and bake about 30 minutes longer until bacon is crisp.
Double for larger amount.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Use a large salad bowl.
Layer as listed.
Sprinkle sugar on top of mayonnaise.
Cover with Saran Wrap overnight.
Put bacon on just before serving.

title: brown cow mint
directions: Combine over ice and top with soda to taste.
Makes 1 serving.

title: coconut pineapple cake
directions: Grease bottom and sides of three 9 in. round cake pans; line bottoms with wax paper.
Grease and flour wax paper.

title: date nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of a loaf pan.
Pour boiling water over dates.
Add soda.
Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour and soda to creamed ingredients alternately with date mixture.
Blend well.
Spoon into a pan. Bake 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Store wrapped tightly. Makes 1 large pan or 3 small.

title: chicken or turkey pie
directions: Boil whole chicken, debone and cut up in chunks.
Place chunks in bottom of casserole dish.
Chop onion and celery and spread on top of chicken, along with peas and carrots, mushrooms, pimentos and almonds. Season to taste.
Drop by tablespoons the cheese and mushroom soups on top of pie along with sliced stick butter.
Top pie with strips of Bisquick for crust. Bake at 350° until crust is brown.

title: pie dough
directions: Cut flour, shortening and salt with pastry blender.
Add water and mix.
This makes several pie crusts so it can be frozen until later use.
I freeze them in individual freezer bags and take them from freezer as needed.

title: microwave rhubarb crumble
directions: Cut rhubarb into greased square glass baking dish.
Sprinkle with white sugar.
Microwave on High for 8 minutes.
Mix other ingredients until crumbly and put over rhubarb.
Microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes (don't overbake).
Serve warm with cream.

title: crunchy freeze
directions: Melt margarine in oven at 300° about 10 minutes.
Add Rice Krispies, sugar, coconut and nuts.
Mix well.
Return to oven for about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally, until slightly brown. Cool.
Put half of mixture in cake pan; layer ice cream over mixture.
Add remaining mixture for topping.
Freeze.
Cut into squares and serve.
Delicious with maple syrup drizzled over top. A good make-ahead recipe.

title: cheese log
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Blend with Cheddar, Worcestershire, garlic and onion.
Place on waxed paper and form into a roll or log.
Chill slightly.
Roll into chopped nuts to coat.
Wrap well and chill until firm.

title: sunrise salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and orange sherbet.
Add orange segments.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cranberry salad mold
directions: Dissolve water in jello and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a jello mold; stir, if nuts float.
Chill.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well.
Can be used with cauliflower, broccoli, carrots and celery.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Bring Karo and sugar to a boil.
Add peanut butter.
Stir until smooth.
Take off of fire.
Pour corn flakes into boiler. Stir quickly and make into balls.
Put on wax paper or greased pan.

title: cajun dip
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Mix diced Velveeta with sausage. Add drained Ro-Tel tomatoes, diced and about 1/3 drained off (save to see if needed).
Mix all together for a short while.
Serve with 1 loaf of French bread, cubed and toasted.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add combined milk and egg, mixing until smooth.
Holding finger over opening, fill funnel with 1/4 cup of batter.
Place funnel near hot oil.
Remove finger and pour batter into oil using a circular motion to form a spiral.
Fry until golden brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or serve with preserves.

title: blueberry poppy seed brunch cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour bottom and sides of 9 or 10 inch spring form pan. In large bowl, beat sugar and butter until light and fluffy, add lemon peel and egg; beat 2 minutes at medium speed. Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup, level off. In mixing bowl, combine flour, poppy seed, baking soda and salt. Add this to butter mixture, alternating with sour cream. Spread batter over bottom and 1 inch up sides of pan, making sure batter on sides is 1/4 inch thick.

title: turkey meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients well in food processor or by hand.
Shape into small balls.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with toothpicks.
Makes 24 meatballs.

title: quick and easy dessert
directions: Mix all together and stir well.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Wash chicken; pat dry.
Place chicken in roasting pan; squeeze lemons over chicken.
Add onion and sprinkle garlic powder, pepper, salt and parsley.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° with cover for 1/2 hour.
Remove cover and cook for another 1/2 hour or until tender.

title: pistachio fruit pie
directions: Crush cookies.
Press into bottom of pie pan.
In large bowl, combine pineapple and strawberries. Stir in pudding.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour mixture over crust. Refrigerate until serving time.
May be frozen.

title: risotto milanese
directions: Heat broth in small saucepan over medium heat to simmering; keep hot over low heat.
Heat 6 tablespoons of butter in heavy 10 inch skillet or 2 1/2 quart saucepan over medium heat.
When foam subsides, add onion; saute until onion is soft, about 5 minutes. Stir in rice; cook and stir 2 minutes.
Stir in wine, salt and pepper.
Cook uncovered over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, until wine is evaporated, 3 to 5 minutes.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: After beef has been cooked and drained, add onion, salt and pepper. Cook a couple of minutes before adding mushroom soup.
Add soup and 1/2 can of water to beef.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Add sour cream and remove from heat.
Serve over cooked egg noodles (prepare according to package directions).
Serves 4.

title: crock-pot hamburg soup
directions: Brown hamburg with garlic and onion.
Put in crock-pot and add all vegetables.
Season with salt and pepper or any of your favorite spices.
(Optional:
A can of Hunt's tomato sauce can be added for color.)
Cook for 5 hours or until all vegetables are tender.

title: marinated pork
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a small bowl and stir well. Place tenderloins in large flat nonmetal dish.
Pour mixture over tenderloins, turning to coat.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator at least 8 hours, turning occasionally.
Remove tenderloins, reserving marinade.
Coat grill rack with cooking spray.
Place on grill over medium-hot grill.
Insert a meat thermometer to thickest part.
Cook 20 minutes on each side or until thermometer registers 160°.
Baste often with marinade.
Great served with wild rice.

title: strawberry spread
directions: With a mixer, blend margarine with honey.
Add strawberries and mix until well blended.
Refrigerate and store.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Grate orange peel; set aside.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, baking soda and nutmeg together.
Cream peanut butter and butter together in large bowl.
Blend in egg, milk and orange juice.
Add sifted dry ingredients and orange peel.
Stir to moisten dry ingredients.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Slice carrots, and dice green pepper and onion.
Cook until tender.
Combine tomato soup, oil, salt, sugar and vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Pour hot over vegetable mix.

title: gingersnap cookies
directions: Mix preceding ingredients in order shown.
Chill, then drop from teaspoon onto baking sheet.
Bake at 325° until medium brown. Makes about 80 teaspoon sized cookies.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Cook in large pot, meat, onion, celery and bell pepper until meat is done; drain.
Add tomatoes, beans, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Add cabbage.
Cook slowly for 30 minutes.
Serve with corn bread.

title: four hour rolls
directions: Scald and cool milk, add sugar and moistened yeast cakes.
Add 1 cup flour and beat well.
Add melted shortening, beaten eggs and salt.
Add 2 1/2 cups flour and beat well for a few minutes.
Let rise to double in size and make into rolls.
Put in refrigerator for future use.

title: fruit 'n' oat snack mix
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in airtight container up to 5 days.

title: lisa's fruit loop candy
directions: On low, melt the white chocolate and stir in the fruit loops, marshmallows, pecans, and rice cereal.
Place in buttered pan and cut in squares.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and pour into an unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken honey nut stir-fry
directions: Cut chicken into thin strips; set aside.
In small bowl, combine orange juice, honey, soy sauce, cornstarch and ginger. Mix well.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add carrots and celery.
Stir-fry about 3 minutes.
Remove vegetables and set aside.

title: oklahoma auxiliary buns
directions: Mix all ingredients well and let rise until double in bulk. Make into buns and let rise again on cookie sheet or flat baking pan.
Can also put 3 balls dough in cupcake pans.
Let rise, then bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Brush with melted butter or shortening after removing from oven.

title: dream pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, juice of cherries and juice of pineapple in a saucepan.
Cook until thick, then add vanilla and jello. Cook until dissolved, then set aside to cool.
Add cherries, pineapple and bananas to mixture.
Pour into baked pie shell. Will make 2 small or 1 large pie.
Refrigerate until ready.
May be made a couple of days ahead. Serve with whipped cream and cherries on top.

title: glazed brussels sprouts and carrots
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, bring water to a boil.
Add vegetables. Cover and simmer for 6 to 8 minutes or until almost tender; drain and return to pan.

title: chicken almondine
directions: Saute onion in a little (1/2 tablespoon) butter until tender. Remove onion and place in large mixing bowl.
Add chicken to pan, browning in remaining butter.
In mixing bowl, add remaining ingredients (except rice) to cooked onion.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into baking dish.
Add browned chicken breasts to top of mixture.
Cook for 45 minutes at 350°.
Let cool for about 15 minutes to let sauce thicken.

title: strawberry pie
directions: In a saucepan, add dry ingredients to boiling water.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Cool completely.
Put sliced strawberries in pie shell.
Pour mixture over strawberries until completely covered. Cover pies with Cool Whip, if desired.
Place in refrigerator.

title: pineapple delight cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake mix.
Bake and cool.
Stir pudding into crushed pineapple.
Prepare dessert topping mix.
Fold into mixture.
Spread on cake.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 2/3 stick margarine with cracker crumbs.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Beat remaining margarine, eggs and confectioners sugar for 15 minutes (must beat for 15 minutes). Spread over cracker crumbs.
Slice bananas over this mixture, then drained pineapple over the bananas.
Top with whipped topping, cherries and pecans.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Melt the chocolate in top of a double boiler over barely simmering water.
In 1/4 cup of milk, dissolve the gelatin.

title: goulash
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Add V-8, salt, oregano, onion, tomato soup, garlic, sugar and hamburger.
Heat everything together and serve.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and drain broccoli; cut into small pieces.
Add scallions and raisins.
Mix together the mayo, vinegar and sugar to make dressing.
Pour over broccoli mixture and refrigerate.
Add bacon just before serving.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Mix powdered sugar, coconut, Eagle Brand milk, oleo and chopped nuts.
Chill 45 minutes.
Butter hands.
Roll dough into small balls.
Place on buttered cookie sheet.
Chill until firm.
Melt 12 ounces chocolate chips and 1 slab of paraffin.
Dip balls and replace on cookie sheet.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut up cauliflower; put in bottom of dish.
Add peas; sprinkle with Italian mix.
Cover with mayo.
Put cheese on top of that and cover.
Chill overnight.

title: mom's old-fashioned goulash
directions: Brown ground meats and onion with seasoned salt until done. Add cooked macaroni and mix well. Stir in diced tomatoes, tomato sauce and 1/2 of cheese and any optional vegetables. Simmer with remainder of cheese on top until ready to serve.

title: chocolate cheesecake pie
directions: Sprinkle half of peanuts into bottom pie crust. Drizzle with 1 Tbsp. caramel topping.

title: lentil soup
directions: Wash lentils and soak in water overnight; drain.
Bring 5 quarts of water to a boil.
Saute onions, garlic and celery in vegetable oil and add to boiling water.
Add all other ingredients and bring to a boil again.
Lower heat; cover and cook 2 1/2 hours.
Add additional seasonings to taste prior to serving.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, salt and baking soda. Add almond extract to oleo mixture, then add flour mixture, then oats, then almonds.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Optional:
One-half cup of Burgundy wine may be added while simmering rice.
(Alcohol is simmered away in the cooking.)

title: homemade potato soup
directions: Cook first 10 ingredients together until done.
Add evaporated milk and heat until hot.
May be cooked in crock; takes about 8 hours.

title: lessie's chicken
directions: Dip breasts in margarine, then roll in corn flakes and cheese. You can put flakes, cheese and chicken in a plastic bag and shake to coat.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: eskimo torte
directions: Place marshmallows and juice in large saucepan to melt, then set in refrigerator to cool.
Make sure it does not get too hard, should look like syrup.
Now whip cream, fold in syrup, then pour in graham cracker lined pan (9 x 12-inch).
Sprinkle remaining cracker crumbs over torte.
Set in refrigerator overnight.

title: chocolate cupcakes
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla together until creamy. Add cocoa to boiling water, blend well and cool.
Next add cocoa mixture and remaining ingredients to creamy mixture.
Blend completely.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: witches brew drink
directions: Pour 1 gallon of cranberry juice in a bowl.
Add 1 gallon apple cider.
Stir in 12 ounces thawed orange juice concentrate. Ready to serve.
Enjoy.

title: white bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water and let set for 5 minutes. Add the rest of the ingredients.
Turn onto floured cloth or surface and let rise 10 minutes.
Knead, adding flour as needed. Let raise in greased bowl, covered, until doubled.
Pan out 4 loaves. Raise.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Spread Tater Tots in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown hamburger and onion.
Spread on top.

title: butter frosting
directions: In small bowl cream butter, sugar and cocoa.
Add milk.
Beat to spreading consistency (additional milk may be added if needed). Blend in vanilla.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: chicken salad
directions: In large bowl, combine chicken with oil, orange juice, vinegar and salt.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or at least 3 hours. Just before serving, add remaining ingredients.
Toss gently. Makes 12 servings.

title: artichoke supreme(servings:  8)
directions: Marinate oil, vinegar, mustard, oregano, basil, garlic and cut up artichokes for a few hours.
Mix with remaining ingredients. Absolutely delicious.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: spoon cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350. Mix all ingredients. Bake 35 minutes. Remove from oven. Grate velveeta cheese on top and bake 10 more minutes.

title: lemon fruit salad
directions: In glass bowl, add all ingredients except bananas.
Mix together and refrigerate covered overnight.
Add sliced bananas just before serving.

title: chicken apricot
directions: Remove skin from all chicken pieces.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Place chicken in a large pan and pour mixture over each piece of chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Nice served with flavored rice.

title: frito chili pie
directions: Layer the ingredients in casserole dish: corn chips on bottom, mustard, chili and chopped onions.
Top with cheese. Heat thoroughly 15 to 20 minutes in oven or in microwave oven until cheese melts.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken; debone and cube. In large roaster, combine all ingredients except spaghetti and chicken broth. Add spaghetti and enough broth to thin if too thick. Bake at 350° until cheese melts, approximately 45 minutes.

title: quick chili
directions: Cook ground beef and onions until lightly brown.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Cook beef and onion in a large skillet until beef is browned, stirring until it crumbles. Drain.

title: snow balls
directions: Cream butter, then add powdered sugar.
Cream until smooth. Sift and add flour, salt and vanilla.
Mix nuts into mixture. Roll into balls and bake on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes (start to brown).
Roll in powdered sugar. Cool and roll again.
(I usually roll 4 to 5 times.)

title: norm's clam sauce
directions: Drain juice from clams and place in separate bowl.
Melt margarine and oil in medium size saucepan.
Add onion and saute five minutes.
Add the clam juice, garlic powder, parsley, oregano and chopped garlic.
Cook 10 minutes.
After 10 minutes cooking, add cheese and clams and cook five minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.
Best served over linguine.

title: lemon rum cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cake and pudding mixes, oil, 1/2 cup rum, milk, juice of 1/2 lemon and eggs.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend oil and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add vanilla, carrots and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in a 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: berried treasure pie
directions: Graham Cracker Crust:
Melt the margarine.
Add the cinnamon and graham cracker crumbs.
Mix and spread in plates (makes 4 pies).

title: fruit salad
directions: Beat egg in saucepan.
Add other ingredients.
Boil until fairly thick (it will thicken some as it cools). Pour over whatever fruit combination you like.
I use crushed pineapple, miniature marshmallows, pecans, orange sections, bananas, grapes and maraschino cherries.

title: onion casserole
directions: Slice onions and make into rings.
Fry in butter until clear. Layer, in baking dish, a layer of onions and layer of cheese until all ingredients are placed.

title: date nut bread
directions: Combine dates, boiling water and butter; set aside.
In large bowl mix all dry ingredients.
Add date mixture, egg, vanilla and nuts.
Grease and flour 2 large loaf pans.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 1/4 hours.

title: overnight chicken hot dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, part of the time covered.
Remove cover last half hour so top will brown.

title: stuffed macaroni shells(with meat stuffing)
directions: Cook shells as directed. Saute broken up chopped meat in butter and chopped parsley.
Season with salt and pepper.
Fill parboiled shells immediately.
Cover bottom of baking dish with sauce.
Arrange filled shells in single layer over the sauce.
Top with remaining sauce; sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken breasts in rice
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken breasts in mixture and bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: In small bowl mix sugar, butter and cream cheese.
In large bowl mix flour, eggs and milk.
Pour ingredients of small bowl into large bowl.
Mix well.
Pour in morsels.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: whipped cherry salad
directions: Add all ingredients together and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: lemon potatoes
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Coat potatoes with lemon juice, olive oil, butter and salt.
Grate lemon zest on top of potatoes. Bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes or until browned.
Remove potatoes from baking dish and serve.

title: bean dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put 1 tablespoon oil in frypan and heat. Add onion and garlic.
Cook about 1 minute.
Add hamburger and cook until done.
Remove excess grease.
Mix refried beans into meat, add enchilada and salsa sauces.
Put into casserole and place in oven.
Cook about 15 minutes.
Remove and stir in sour cream.
Cover top with grated cheese.
Put back into oven until cheese melts.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: banana split cheesecake squares
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 c. sugar and melted oleo. Line bottom of 9x13 inch baking pan with foil for easy removal of squares.
Press crust mixture on bottom of baking pan.
Blend cream cheese, remaining sugar and vanilla in bowl with mixer at medium speed.
Add eggs & mix will blended.
Stir in mashed banana.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 mins. or until center is almost set.
Remove from oven.
Cool.
Refrigerate 12 hours or overnight.
Top with strawberries, sliced banana and pineapple.
Sprinkle with nuts and drizzle with melted chocolate if desired.
Cut into squares.

title: bit o spice prune cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add sugar, oil, eggs, vanilla and buttermilk.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in prunes and nuts.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until done.
Put in bowl and add tomatoes.
Spoon it in a casserole in layers; first macaroni and then cheese.
(Take cheese and fold it in quarters and lay on top of macaroni.)
When finished, put in oven and bake until cheese is melted and top is a little brown.
Bake at about 350°.

title: italian trash
directions: Preheat oven to 300 degrees. Combine all dry ingredients in a very large bowl. Drizzle Italian dressing over top and toss to mix well. Spread in 2 shallow pans. Bake, stirring once, for 30 minutes. Cool completely and then store in airtight containers.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarter pieces.
Dip in melted butter.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon.
Put biscuits loosely in greased Bundt pan. Bake at 450° until golden brown.
Invert on plate.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar, pecans and margarine well.
Put in pan and bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, pecans and butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in 9-inch pan, stirring often.
Let cool.
Combine strawberries, sugar, lemon juice and egg whites.
Beat at high speed with mixer, about 20 minutes or when fluffy.
Fold whipped cream in strawberries.
Remove 1/3 of crumb mixture from pan.
Pat remaining crumbs into smooth layer.
Pour strawberry mixture over crumbs in pan and sprinkle reserved crumbs over the top.
Freeze. Remove from freezer a few minutes before serving.

title: buttermilk custard pie
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs and flour.
Add buttermilk and mix well.
Stir in flavoring and butter.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: butter pecan rolls
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put 1 cup chopped pecans on the bottom.
Place 24 frozen roll dough balls on top of pecans. Sprinkle pudding mix over top.
Melt together butter, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Drizzle on top.
Add a few more pecans on top. Cover and let rise overnight.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Flip.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion; add other ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.

title: anacuchos
directions: Place all ingredients, except meat and basting oil in blender; process until well mixed.
Pour marinade over meat in a glass or ceramic bowl (not plastic).
Cover; refrigerate for 48 hours.

title: pots de creme(simple)
directions: Place all ingredients except cream in blender.
Blend on low for 60 seconds.
Pour into individual demitasse cups or Pots de Creme pots and chill 2 hours or until set.
Serve with whipped cream.
Yields 4 to 5 good size servings.
Very rich.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Put sugar in pan; add water and then yeast and let rise.
Mix flour and shortening.
Combine flour mixture with sugar, yeast and sugar mixture.
Let rise 15 +- minutes.
Oil hands and pinch off for rolls and let rise 15 minutes to 1 hour.
Bake in preheated oven, 425°, for 15 minutes.

title: easy boiled custard
directions: Mix and beat until it begins to thicken.
It will be much thicker after it sets.

title: "grandma bea's" cabbage slaw
directions: Bring to a boil the vinegar, salad oil, sugar, brown sugar, salt and celery seed. Mix first four ingredients together and pour over cabbage mixture. Refrigerate.

title: stuffed ham
directions: Mix kale, onion, cabbage, red pepper and salt.
Lay ham on cheesecloth.
Cut slits into top of ham and work it around to form pockets.
Stuff the kale mixture into the pockets.
Make as many slits into the ham as you can.
Tie ham up inside of cheesecloth along with any remaining mixture.
Put into a large stock pot with enough water to cover.
Boil 15 minutes to each pound of ham of 15 pounds or under; 20 minutes to a pound if there is a bone.
This ham may be eaten hot or cold.
When ham is sliced the effect is of green veining through the pink meat.

title: chicken scampi
directions: In saucepan with salted water, place broccoli and steam 4 minutes or until crisp.
In the meantime, boil linguine in salted water for 9 minutes and drain.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Cook until thick.
Add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and dot of butter. Pour hot filling into baked pie shell.
Use egg whites for meringue and brown.

title: chicken athena
directions: In skillet, brown meat in oil.
Add onion and cook 2 minutes. Stir in tomatoes, marinade from artichokes and rosemary.
Cook over medium heat 10 to 15 minutes or until thickened, stirring frequently.
Stir in artichoke hearts.
Heat through.
Top with cheese.
Garnish with chopped parsley, if desired.
Serve with rice.

title: caramel pie
directions: Place unopened cans in a pan of boiling water.
Continue boiling for 2 hours.
Slowly and carefully poke a hole in top of each can and let cool for 15 minutes.
Pour into baked pie shell and chill.
To serve, top with Cool Whip.

title: party mix
directions: Pour over mixture.
Cook 2 hours at 200°.
Stir every 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and roll into balls 1-inch in diameter.
Chill until firm.
Melt chocolate and paraffin in double boiler.
Leave over hot water while dipping balls.
Insert toothpick into a ball and dip into chocolate.
Drain on waxed paper.
Makes 150 balls.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Fold together egg yolks, milk, lemon rind and juice.
Pour in a graham cracker crust.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar, gradually add sugar.
Top pie with meringue and brown in a 450° oven.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: saucy chicken bake
directions: Place chicken in a 13 x 9 baking dish; sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Add Chicken a' la King and mushroom soup over chicken.
Sprinkle pimentos over the sauce.
Cover with sliced onions.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until chicken is fork tender.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Mix together with a mixer the pumpkin, honey, molasses, milk, eggs and butter.
Make sure they are well combined.
In a separate bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, ginger, raisins and nuts.
Mix well.
Add the dry ingredients to the liquid ones and mix only until batter is moistened.
Pour into a greased 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine crushed graham crackers and 1 stick margarine for bottom crust. Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: 3-step cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar, and vanilla at medium speed until well blended.
Blend in eggs until smooth.
Stir in chocolate chips then pour batter into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, or until center is almost set.
Cool.
For best results chill for 3 hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix together squash, onion, chicken soup and sour cream.
Melt margarine and mix with stuffing mix.
Mix all stuffing in squash, except a small amount to sprinkle on top before putting in oven. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: pears baked with swordfish(4 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 500°. Set each piece of fish on a square of aluminum foil that is big enough to fold over and enclose fish. Place 1/4 of the onion rings, pears, ginger, lime peel, lime juice and allspice on each piece of fish. Fold foil around each to make a tight pack and bake for 15 minutes.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix sugar, flour and eggs with pineapple.
Place in buttered casserole and place buttered diced bread on top.
Cook in not too hot oven 1/2 to 3/4 hour.

title: yummy chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together the butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend thoroughly.
In a separate bowl, sift together the flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture; blend thoroughly. Add oats, chocolate chips and nuts; mix well.
Drop by tablespoon onto buttered baking sheet(s).
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes, or until evenly browned.
Let cool on wire rack. Makes about 36 fantastic chocolate chip cookies.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts with salt and pepper and roll in flour.
Melt 4 tablespoons butter in skillet.
Brown chicken and remove to roaster.
Add broth
to pan juices.
Scrape bits from sides and bottom.
Pour over chicken.
Saute onion, parsley and mushrooms in remaining 4 tablespoons butter.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove chicken to serving plate.
Stir mustard and sour cream into liquid in roaster.
Heat and pour over chicken or serve on the side.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons warm water.
Mix all ingredients together.
Does not have to rise.
Roll and cut as you would regular biscuits.

title: spray and wash
directions: Mix together.
Spray on spots on clothing.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat the eggs.
Mix together the melted oleo, flour, sugar and salt.
Add to the eggs.
Stir in the milk and cream-style corn. Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 45 minutes or until set.

title: sugared walnuts
directions: Heat walnut halves in 375° oven for 5 minutes, stirring once. Butter sides of heavy 2-quart saucepan and combine sugar, water, cinnamon and salt.
Heat and stir until sugar dissolves and mixture boils.
Cook without stirring to soft ball stage (236°). Remove from heat.
Beat by hand one minute or until mixture just becomes creamy.
Add vanilla and the warm nuts.
Stir gently until nuts are well coated.
Turn out on buttered surface.
Separate at once with two spoons or fork.

title: elegant "turkey" casserole almondine
directions: In a large skillet, saute onions and mushrooms in margarine. Stir in almonds and mushroom soup, soyameat, seasoning and sour cream.
Pour mixture into pastry.
Fold pastry from the pan sides over filling, making a small rolled crust completely around the casserole.
In a small bowl, toss bread crumbs with melted margarine, sprinkle over the top of the casserole.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and chocolate.
Add eggs, one at a time, then add vanilla, salt, flour, baking powder and buttermilk.
Stir in nuts and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (layer); 75 minutes in tube pan.
Grease and flour pans.
Makes 3 (8-inch) layers or 2 pans.

title: fruit slush
directions: Remove sugar/water mixture from heat.
Add juices.
Freeze in ice cube trays and store frozen cubes in freezer bags.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix together and beat like heck!
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: creamy frozen lime pie
directions: In small mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth. Gradually add sweetened condensed milk and evaporated milk; beat until smooth.
With mixer on medium speed, add lime juice and beat for 1 minute.
Pour into pie crust and freeze for at least 2 hours.
Let stand at room temperature 10 to 15 minutes.
Garnish with lime slices, berries or mint sprigs before serving.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix fruit and nuts with 1/2 cut of the flour.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add remaining ingredients for batter. Stir in fruits and nuts.
Chill overnight or at least 4 hours. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add rice, taco seasoning and the amount of water called for on the seasoning packet.
Cook until liquid is absorbed.
Add picante sauce or salsa.
Mix well.

title: chicken chop suey
directions: Cook chicken until very tender with enough water to have a cup or more of stock.
Cut up chicken and place in pot after deboning. Add stock, celery, onions, soy sauce and 2 tablespoons oleo, if desired.
Add sugar.
Cook about 45 minutes or until onions and celery are tender.
Mix brown sauce or bread molasses with flour and water.
Add to chicken and mix well.
Drain vegetables and rice.
Add to mixture and cook 15 minutes longer.
Serve over rice.

title: tangerine chicken and rice
directions: Marinate chicken in dressing in the refrigerator at least 6 hours.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken and marinade in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle filets with soy sauce.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes, until filets are done.
Meanwhile, prepare rice according to directions on box.
When chicken and rice are both done, add drained oranges to the rice, stirring gently.

title: crickets
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Beat butter and sugars in large bowl with mixer.
Add eggs, vanilla and dry ingredients.
Mix on low just until combined.
Fold in raisins and pecans.
Drop on ungreased baking sheet by teaspoonfuls.
Bake 10 to 13 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel apples and slice thinly.
Place in cooking pan.
Add 1/4 cup water and sugar (white).
Sprinkle desired cinnamon and nutmeg over the apples.
Blend brown sugar, butter, flour, water and salt until crumbly.
Add to apples.
Bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: taco beef soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook ground beef and onions until meat is browned.
Drain off excess fat.
Add water, undrained tomatoes, undrained kidney beans, tomato sauce and taco seasoning mix. Simmer covered 15 minutes.
Serve with corn chips and top with grated Cheddar cheese.

title: russian teacakes
directions: Mix butter, vanilla and sugar well.
Sift flour and salt; stir in sugar mixture, mix in nuts.
Chill dough.
Heat oven to 400°. Roll dough into 1 inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
While still warm, roll in powdered sugar. Cool.
Roll in sugar again.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: teriyaki chicken wings
directions: Marinate for 2 hours.
Bake in juices at 375° for 45 minutes each side.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Add brown sugar.
Blend in eggs and vanilla. Add flour mixture gradually, mixing well.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Cut in bars.

title: lace cookies
directions: Blend well.
Arrange by half teaspoon at least 2 inches apart on heavy cookie sheet or on foil.
Bake until lightly browned. Cool slightly.
As soon as firm enough remove from cookie sheet. Makes about 90.
Oven set at 375°.

title: egg custards
directions: Mix and pour into pie shells and cook until done.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top before cooking.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: carrot pineapple loaf
directions: Mix together by hand all ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: beef in beer
directions: Cut the meat into cubes; saute in the oil until brown on all sides.
Remove from pan; put in casserole.
Saute onions in the same pan until golden brown.
Add to the meat with the mushrooms and carrots.
Mix cornstarch with a little of the stock in the same pan, then stir in the rest of the stock, tomato paste and parsley. Bring to a boil; stir constantly.
Pour over the beef and vegetables.
Season to taste with salt and pepper; pour on the beer.
Cook, covered, in a 350° oven for 2 to 3 hours, or until tender.
Cool.

title: festive fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Set pineapple aside.
Pour juice into a small saucepan.
Add sugar and flour.
Bring to a boil.
Quickly stir in egg; cook until thickened.
Remove from heat; cool.
Refrigerate.
In a large bowl, combine pineapple, oranges, pears, apples, kiwi and nuts.
Pour dressing over and blend well.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef and boil potatoes.
Mix all ingredients together and simmer.
Add 2 cups of water or more, if needed. Makes about 4 quarts.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with non-stick coating.
Line the bottom of the pan with can of crescent rolls.
In a separate bowl mix together the sausage, cheese and eggs.
Pour the mixture over the crescent rolls and spread evenly.
Cover the top with another can of crescent rolls and bake 30 minutes at 350° or until browned on top.

title: sunday barbecued pork chops
directions: Sear chops on both sides in shortening.
Combine remaining ingredients and heat; add chops.
Cook slowly for 1 hour or 1 1/2 hours.
Place pork chops in baking dish.
Heat in 375° oven for about 15 minutes.
Serve sauce on rice.
Yields 6 servings.

title: spinach squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, melt butter in oven while it's preheating.
In a large bowl, beat eggs, then add flour, milk, salt and baking powder.
Add grated cheese, cooled spinach, onion and bacon (optional) to egg mixture.
Spoon into pan and level.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Bake 35 minutes.
Cool 45 minutes and cut into 1-inch squares.
May be frozen.

title: crab and spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook vermicelli by package directions; drain.
Melt margarine in a 3-quart saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until limp (about 5 minutes).
Stir in soup; blend in half and half, Worcestershire sauce and mustard. Add vermicelli and mix well.
Gently stir in crab, eggs and water chestnuts.
Season with salt and pepper.
Spoon vermicelli mixture into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese (or mix cheese soup in earlier).
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: mexican chicken lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cook lasagna noodles; drain.
Combine lasagna sauce from package, chicken, green pepper, pinto beans, chili powder and crushed red pepper in large skillet; heat thoroughly.
Spread 1/2 cup sauce mixture over bottom of 8 x 8-inch greased baking dish.
Place a layer of noodles over sauce. Spread 1/2 cup mixture over noodles.
Sprinkle with grated cheese. Repeat layers.
Top with Cheddar cheese and olives.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, or until heated through.
Let cool 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: banana split cake
directions: First Layer:
Mix graham cracker crumbs, 1/2 cup butter and sugar together and press in a 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: corn-broccoli casserole
directions: Combine corns, broccoli and cheese.
Add half of the crackers. Place in greased casserole.
Place the remaining crackers on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese melts.
May be frozen before baked or after.
Makes about a 3-quart casserole.

title: easy bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Let stand a few minutes.
Add salt, sugar and oil.
Add flour 4 cups at a time.
After all flour is mixed in, knead 10 minutes.
Let rise 1 hour.
Punch down, then let rise another hour.
Shape into loaves.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Makes 5 medium loaves.

title: pacific paella
directions: Cut chicken breast into 1/2 inch strips.
Combine paprika, salt and pepper in small bowl.
Add chicken and stir until completely coated with seasonings.
Cut sausage into 1/4 inch pieces.
Remove casings.
Add enough water to chicken broth to make 3 3/4 cups. Bring to boil in 12-inch skillet.
Stir in rice, onion, garlic, turmeric, chicken, sausage and tomatoes.
Cover tightly and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in shrimp and green pepper. Add mussels on top.
Let stand covered until all liquid is absorbed, about 5 minutes.
Makes 10 servings.

title: ham delights
directions: Mix sauce.
Spread on inside of rolls; put cheese and ham. Bake 10 minutes at 300° to 325°.
Wrap in foil.

title: baked fudge pudding
directions: Mix together beaten eggs and sugar.
Sift together flour, cocoa and salt.
Add dry mixture to eggs and sugar. Add chopped nuts and flavoring.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place pan into a second pan of hot tap water.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; mix with onion soup and cream soup.
Also place green chilies in mixture.
Layer tortillas, hamburger mixture and cheese.
The last layer should be cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted at 350°.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Blend all ingredients together and pour into 13 x 9-inch ungreased pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: scotch toffee bars
directions: *Take from oven and while hot cover top with chips and spread to frost, then sprinkle with nuts.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Add flour gradually.
Add vanilla flavoring.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes at 325°.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: flaky biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together into a mixing bowl.
Pour oil and milk into one measuring cup but do not stir. Add all at once to flour mixture.
Stir quickly with a fork until dough clings together.
Knead the dough lightly about 10 times. Place the dough on a piece of waxed paper, 12 x 16-inches.
Pat dough out to about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with unfloured medium-sized cookie cutter.
Place biscuits onto ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 475° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 12 (2-inch biscuits).

title: refrigerator mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water until tender.
Add rest of ingredients and heat until fluffy.
Cool.
Cover and refrigerate up to 2 weeks.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan or 2-quart casserole. Dot with butter and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Saute zucchini, celery and onion in skillet until onion is clear.
Season and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Sprinkle cheese on, stir and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chile rellenos casserole
directions: Slit chilies lengthwise on one side. Remove seeds and drain. Slice Monterey Jack cheese into 1/4-inch thick slices and place inside chilies. Place stuffed chilies in an ungreased 3-quart baking dish.

title: grandma's rolls
directions: Add together in mixing bowl yeast and warm water.
Add warm milk, flour, sugar, salt and oil.
Let rise to double its size in warm place (about 1 hour).
Roll out and let rise to double size (1 1/2 hours).
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: nut fingers
directions: Sift together the salt, powdered sugar and flour.
With a fork, mix margarine and dry ingredients with the ice water and vanilla.
Add the pecans.
Roll into desired shape and bake about 30 minutes at 375° or until lightly browned.
When cool, roll in powdered sugar.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Stir boiling water and oatmeal.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Cream the shortening, sugars and eggs. Add flour, soda, salt, vanilla and cinnamon. Add cooled oatmeal. Bake in a 9
13-inch greased pan for 35 minutes at 375°.

title: grape-nut cookies
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients. Add the soda mixture, vanilla, flour, cream of tartar and salt.
Mix the remaining ingredients and add to the mixture.
Refrigerate and then make into small balls. Flatten with fork. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil all ingredients (except oats and peanut butter) together for 2 minutes.
After mixture begins to boil, remove from heat and add the oats and peanut butter.
Stir and drop by spoonful onto wax paper.	This is an easy recipe to just make half a batch. Half a batch would make about 18 or 20 cookies.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, Marshmallow Creme and milk until smooth. Serve with bite size pieces of fresh fruit. Yields 1 1/2 cups dip.

title: sunday chicken
