directions: In large baking pan, place rice, cream of celery soup, mushroom soup and water or milk.
Mix well.
Lay chicken pieces on top and sprinkle with 1/2 envelope of Lipton onion soup.
Cover tightly so that no steam can escape.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute seasoning.
Add ground meat and brown.
Add sauces and water.
Cook 20 minutes.

title: green wonder salad
directions: Stir together sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper and dissolve. Mix all ingredients and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: lemon buttermilk pound cake
directions: Bring butter, eggs and buttermilk to room temperature.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
In a small mixing bowl, sift flour and baking soda.
Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, beat butter with an electric mixer on medium speed until softened.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat until combined.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating for 1 minute after each addition and scraping bowl frequently. (Scraping the bowl assures that the batter will be thoroughly mixed.)
Add lemon peel, lemon juice and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk alternately to beaten mixture.
Beat after each addition just until combined real well.
Turn batter into prepared pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 55 or 60 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack for 15 minutes.

title: watergate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in a greased and floured pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, until done.

title: white cutouts
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
This recipe makes a large batch of cookies.
Can be cut in half.

title: erwtensoep(dutch pea soup)
directions: In a large 6 to 8-quart casserole, combine the split peas, the pigs feet and/or hock, the salt pork and the water.
Bring to a high boil, skimming off the foam with a perforated spoon as it comes to the top.
Reduce the heat to low; partially cover and simmer for about 3 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Add the potatoes, carrots, celeriac, celery leaves and leeks.
Simmer again for about 30 minutes partially covered.
Watch the heat and stir from time to time; the soup will be very thick and tends to scorch on the bottom.
With tongs or a slotted spoon, transfer the meat to a cutting board.
Remove and discard the fatty skin, bones and whatever else looks undesirable.
Cut up the meat into little pieces and add the sliced sausage, the crumbled summer savory and several grindings of pepper.
Add salt to taste.
Stirring constantly, bring the soup to a simmer over moderate heat and cook for a few minutes to heat the sausage through.
Taste for seasonings and serve from a heated tureen or individual soup plates.

title: praline bars
directions: Place graham crackers on pan with sides.
Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add sugar and pecans.
Bring to boil and boil slowly 2 minutes.
Pour over graham crackers.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes. Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.
Enjoy!!

title: homemade bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; add sugar, salt, shortening and flour.
Mix into firm dough.
Turn dough out onto floured board and fold from side to side and side to center.
This works air into the dough.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise in warm temperature.
When almost double in size, make into loaves. Place in greased pans.
Let rise until light and almost double in size.
Bake at 375° for approximately 50 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cover potatoes with water in 2 1/2-quart bowl.
Stir in salt and let stand, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Drain thoroughly.

title: irish potato custard pie
directions: Whip potatoes and salt until light.
Add sugar and butter while warm, then add milk and egg yolks.
Last, fold in egg whites which have been beaten light.
Put in unbaked shell.
Bake in a 400° oven until steel knife comes out clean.

title: bundle burgers
directions: Mix together ground beef and evaporated milk.
Divide and flatten into five saucer size patties.
Prepare stuffing according to package directions and spread on each patty.
Roll up and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cover with the following sauce.

title: chicken chalupas
directions: Mix the chicken, 1/2 of the sour cream, 1 can of soup, chili peppers, cheese and onions together.
Fill each tortilla with the mixture (about 3/4 of a cup); roll the tortilla.
Place it in a casserole dish.
Mix other can of soup with the rest of the sour cream; cover the tortillas with it.
Sprinkle a little cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: easy homemade bread
directions: Mix yeast with water in a large bowl.
Add sugar, salt, eggs and butter; then add in flour (mixer can be used).
Stir with a spoon until all flour is well mixed in.
Let sit for 1 hour. Grease and flour hands; then divide dough into 3 loaves.
Put in greased pans.
Cover with towel and let sit 40 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: grandma's brown rice
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in oil while preparing the rice according to the package directions.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Toss and serve.

title: uncooked fruitcake
directions: Slowly melt 48 marshmallows with 1 pound oleo.
Pour this over 1 pound crushed graham crackers.
Put pineapple, cherries, dates, coconut and pecans.
Work with your hands until thoroughly mixed. Mold into wax paper lined pans or foil loaf pans.
Let set 24 hours.
Turn out and wrap in wax paper and foil.

title: hazelnut cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and dash of salt; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, beat margarine with electric mixer on low speed for 30 seconds.
Add sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add egg, orange or lemon peel and vanilla; beat well.
Stir in juice, then flour mixture and ground nuts and dates.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet.
If desired, to each add a whole nut on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until edges begin to brown.
Transfer to a wire rack.
Cool.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: banana salad
directions: Scald milk.
Mix sugar and flour in small bowl and add enough milk for paste and to thicken milk when hot.
Stir.
Layer white sauce, bananas and peanuts in salad bowl.

title: shole zard
directions: Stir rice into the water until it comes to a boil.
Boil for 2 to 3 hours until it is well done, then add sugar.
After 15 minutes, add butter and saffron.
After 15 more minutes pour it in cups and decorate with cinnamon and sliced almonds.

title: microwave chili con carne
directions: Crumble ground beef into a 2-quart microproof casserole or baking dish.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic.
Cook, uncovered, on High (maximum power) for 4 minutes.
Drain meat and break up with fork.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook, covered, on 70 (Roast) for 15 to 18 minutes or until hot.
Stir once during cooking time; adjust seasonings.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and slice sweet potatoes into 1/4-inch rounds.
Place in a large iron skillet.
Add sugar, margarine and small amount of water.
Cover and cook over medium heat 20 to 25 minutes until candied.
Goes good with ham.

title: shirley's yeast rolls
directions: Mix all together.
Set in a warm place until doubled in size (about 45 minutes to 1 hour).
Pour out in flour and pinch off for rolls.
Spread melted butter, with garlic salt added to it, on top of rolls and let rise again (1 hour).
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes or until brown.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: easy rice casserole
directions: After all is mixed, put cover on electric fry pan until it comes to a boil, then turn down to simmer and cook for 20 minutes without removing cover.

title: no-fat cream soup base
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in an airtight container.
When ready to use, add 2 cups of cold water to 1 cup of mixture.
Heat to thicken, stirring often.
Add cooked vegetables or whatever your cream soup calls for.

title: ham and swiss sandwiches
directions: Cut finger rolls in half by separating tops from bottoms. Leave all rolls connected.
Layer bottom rolls with ham and cheese, then top of rolls in pan.
Make mixture of melted butter, soy sauce, onions and mustard.
Cut sandwiches and pour mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: hero sandwich
directions: Cut bread in half lengthwise.
In small bowl, combine mayonnaise, mustard and horseradish.
Spread mayonnaise mixture on both sides of loaf.
Arrange slices of cheese, meat, green pepper, tomato, onion and lettuce on bottom half of loaf.
Garnish with alfalfa sprouts.
Replace top half of loaf.
Secure with wooden skewers.
Cut diagonally into slices to serve, or wrap and refrigerate until serving time.
Makes 8 servings.

title: potatoes
directions: Quarter (or smaller) potatoes. Put in pan lined with aluminum foil. Slice stick of margarine over top of potatoes. Chop up onion in potatoes. Sprinkle with onion salt. Cover with aluminum foil. Bake in oven at 450° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: squash patties
directions: Combine all.
Heat oil in frying pan.
Drop mixture by spoonfuls into hot oil.
Flatten out to 1/4 thickness.
Cook until brown on both sides.

title: mexican breakfast
directions: Overlap ham on tortilla.
Melt butter in skillet.
Place tortilla with meat in skillet.
Top with egg, cheese and onion. Cover skillet with lid and cook over medium-low heat 5 minutes or until egg is set.
Sprinkle with chili powder and fold in half.

title: ambrosia cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add other ingredients and mix well. Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes in 3 greased and floured cake pans.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and just before serving, add 1 large bottle ginger ale and add ice cubes.

title: dressing
directions: Crumble and combine cornbread and biscuits.
Add seasonings, eggs and liquid ingredients.
Mix well. Place in a greased long pan.
Bake in 350
to 400 degree oven until done (about 45 minutes).

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Put sugar, flour and salt in mixing bowl.
Add milk, Pet milk, eggs and vanilla.
Combine well.
Put in ice cream freezer; freeze.
Turn until you can't turn the handle.
Cover with towels. Let set for 1 hour.
Enjoy.

title: strawberry bavarian dessert
directions: If using frozen berries, thaw and let warm to room temperature.

title: viva house vegetarian lasagna
directions: Cheese mixture:
Mix together spinach, egg, Ricotta and Mozzarella (save 1/2 cup Mozzarella for top of lasagna).
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: economical meat and vegetable casserole
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, milk, egg, onion, salt and mustard.
Shape to form 24 meatballs.
Cook them in butter until lightly browned on all sides.
Drain off excess fat.
Combine soup, cheese and sage.
Arrange meatballs around sides of shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Spoon soup mixture into center.
Place cooked vegetables over top.
Cover with foil.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to package; drain.
In a pot, combine butter, onion, flour and seasoning.
Blend in milk gradually. Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add broccoli and water; cook until heated.
Serves 6.

title: enchiladas acapulco
directions: Brown meat and peppers.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce and kidney beans.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add 1/4 pound cheese and cook until melted.

title: impossible pie
directions: Blend in blender 1 minute.
Pour into glass pie plate that has been well buttered and floured.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sausage-pancake pie
directions: Cook and
crumble
sausage in skillet.	Place in 9-inch pie pan.
Beat eggs slightly, add pancake mix and milk.
Blend with fork.
Pour
over sausage.	Sprinkle with cheese and bake 20 minutes at	400°.
Cut
into
wedges
and serve with syrup. Serves 4.

title: easy fudge
directions: Melt margarine, chocolate and peanut butter together in heavy-duty saucepan over a slow heat, stirring constantly until it begins to boil.
Remove from heat immediately.
Stir in cereal. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill; cut into squares. (Refrigerate in hot weather.)
Can be done in microwave.

title: baked carrots
directions: Cook sliced carrots and drain.
Combine all ingredients, except chips.
Mix well and pour in a greased casserole dish.
Top with chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Cut into chunks.
Reserve 1/2 cup of broth and mix with soup and cheese.
Mix well.
Separate crescent rolls.
Place chicken in each roll, dividing evenly and roll up. Butter a casserole dish and spread soup mixture evenly in bottom of dish.
Place roll-ups in dish and bake in 350° oven until rolls are golden brown, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: plum good cake
directions: Mix with spoon.
Put in greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake 55 minutes at 325°.

title: "easy" chocolate-peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix peanut butter, sugar and eggs.
Add chips or chunks. Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease pan; spoon out cookie batter.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Ready to eat.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 5-quart Dutch oven, combine beef, undiluted soup, dry soup mix, wine and onion; mix well.
Top with potato pieces and carrots, mixing in slightly.
Cover and bake 2 hours.
Stir in broccoli, cover and bake 15 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: sugar crisp tea macaroons
directions: Combine and thoroughly mix the first 6 ingredients (shortening, sugars, salt, almond extract, eggs).
Stir in nuts and coconut. Sift the flour and soda and add to liquid mixture.
Stir in oats. Shape dough into 3/4-inch balls.
Roll in green or red sugar. Place on greased sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes to a delicate brown.
Makes 10 to 11 dozen.

title: chocolate melt cookies
directions: Melt chocolate morsels and margarine in microwave.
Add nuts and marshmallows. Stir well and drop by spoon on cookie sheet. Put in refrigerator and let chill.

title: rocky road chocolate squares
directions: Sift sugar and flour together.
In separate kettle, combine butter, cocoa and water.
Bring to boil.
Pour over sugar and flour and mix well.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan (15 x 10-inch).
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until partly tender.
Layer baking dish with broccoli and crackers.
Place cheese on top to melt, then pour milk over the casserole.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and milk thickens.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.
Roll in 1 cup chopped pecans before serving.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix well all ingredients, except the crackers.
Place in baking dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Bake in a 325° to 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chow mein hot dish(makes 12 to 16 servings)
directions: Pour 2 1/2 cups boiling water over rice.
Let stand while preparing other ingredients.
Brown meat and onion together (drain fat).
Add Worcestershire sauce, soy sauce and celery.
While browning, add soup and brown sugar to rice mixture.
Stir together.
Pour into casserole and cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: five flavor cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening until light.
Add eggs which have been beaten; combine flour and baking powder.
Add to cream mixture.
Mix milk alternately; stir in flavoring.
Spoon into 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done. Add glaze while in pan.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail about 2 hours before mixing so it will be dry.
Mix Cool Whip and mayonnaise together.
Put in other ingredients; mix well.
Put in fruit cocktail and mix well.
Put in refrigerator.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Melt butter; then add other ingredients.
Stir in pecans. Spread in a flat pan.
Toast at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes until browned.
Stir after baking.
Dry on a paper towel.

title: smothered pork chops
directions: In skillet, brown chops (use 1 tablespoon shortening if needed).
Pour
off
fat.
Stir in soup, water and thyme.
Add onions, carrots
and mushrooms.
Cover.
Cook over low heat 45 minutes or until tender.
Stir now and then.
Very good served with rice.

title: strawberry torte
directions: Prepare jello, using only 1 cup hot water.
Cool and set (not too thick).
Mix with 1 (8 ounce) whipped topping.
Line a 10 x 12-inch pan with thin slices of cake.
Break remaining half of cake into pieces.
Add to jello mixture along with thawed strawberries. Fold in fresh berries.
Retain 9 berry slices for decoration.
Top with remaining whipped topping and garnish with 9 berry slices. Refrigerate and serve cool.
This may also be doubled and layered in a punch bowl for a larger group or individual parfaits.
Diced bananas could also be added.

title: okra croquettes
directions: Combine okra, onion, flour, cornmeal, salt and pepper.
Beat egg slightly and add to okra mixture.
Mix well.
Heat cooking oil in skillet (I use safflower oil).
Drop okra from a tablespoon in hot oil.
Flatten with a pancake turner.
Cook about 3 minutes on each side.
Drain on paper towels.
Serves 6.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Shake flour in one (14 x 20-inch) Reynolds oven bag.
Add brown sugar and soy sauce to bag.
Squeeze to blend flour in bag.
Add pineapple and green pepper to bag.
Add chicken to bag.
Turn bag until the chicken is coated with sauce; arrange bag in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, so that ingredients are arranged evenly.
Close bag with tie; cut 6 slits in top of bag.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve over hot rice.

title: tuna melt sandwiches
directions: Combine tuna, mayonnaise, onion, celery and relish; mix well. Top 4 slices bread with one cheese slice.
Spread tuna mixture over the cheese and top with remaining bread.
Spread each sandwich with a wee bit of soft butter; slice in skillet.
Cook on medium heat until lightly browned on both sides.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Beat together oil, 2 cups sugar and 4 eggs.
Blend in water, sweet potatoes, 1 cup nuts, vanilla, cinnamon and flour.
Beat until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, using a long cake pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.

title: nibbles
directions: Preheat oven to 275°. In a large bowl, combine cereal and pretzel sticks. In a small saucepan, melt margarine over low heat. Add remaining ingredients except nuts, stirring well. Stir into cereal mixture. Add nuts and stir to combine. Transfer mixture to a shallow roasting pan. Bake for 1 hour, stirring every 10 minutes.

title: coffee cake ring
directions: Scald 1 cup milk; let cool to lukewarm and add yeast, eggs and sugar.
Beat with eggbeater.
Take flour, sugar, oleo, nutmeg or lemon and mix like pie crust.
Then add to the first mixture (for Christmas, add 1 cup of candied fruit) and mix well.
Cover and put into refrigerator overnight.
When you are ready to bake it, divide dough into 2 or 3 parts and roll about 1/2-inch thick. Brush surface with melted butter; strew on sugar, cinnamon, raisins and chopped nuts.
Roll as jelly roll.
Let set in warm place about 1/2 hour.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost top with powdered sugar frosting and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: coffee punch
directions: Heat sugar, instant coffee and water until dissolved. Refrigerate overnight.
Mix milk and both chocolate and vanilla ice cream, then pour coffee mixture over ice cream.
Serve in punch bowl.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Make a mixture of cornstarch and water.
Mix until smooth (no lumps).
Set aside.

title: play dough
directions: Cook all ingredients for 3 minutes.
Knead and put into airtight container when cool.

title: skillet squash
directions: Place all of the ingredients in a skillet.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Pour in casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: wacky cake
directions: Put all dry ingredients in cake pan and make 3 depressions. First vinegar, second vanilla and third oleo.
Pour 2 cups cold water over all and mix well.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: ranch crackers
directions: Place foil on cookie sheet.
Mix all ingredients together and spread on cookie sheet.
Bake for 2 hours at 200°.
Stir at 1/2 hour intervals.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Cook tortellini according to package directions (omitting salt).
Drain.
In a medium bowl, toss tortellini with dressing. Cool 10 minutes.
Add cucumber, tomato and green onion.
Toss gently to coat.
Serve at room temperature or cover and refrigerate.
Serve over salad greens.

title: grandma pearl's pound cake
directions: Cream eggs and sugar with butter. Add flour and vanilla. Bake in a loaf pan at 350° until golden brown.

title: chop stick casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except noodles.
Then add half of noodles and toss.
Put into sprayed casserole.
Top with remainder of noodles and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: stuffed noodles
directions: Boil noodles.
Make spaghetti sauce and brown hamburger.
Stir cream cheese and eggs until smooth.
Add last 4 ingredients.
Pour about 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce in bottom of pan.
Stuff noodles with cheese mixture.
Set in pan.
Pour remaining sauce over all the noodles.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: rocky road candy
directions: In a heavy saucepan over low heat, melt morsels with condensed milk and margarine.
Remove from heat.
In a large bowl, combine nuts and marshmallows.
Stir in chocolate mixture.
Spread wax paper to line a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill 2 hours.
Remove paper and cut into squares.
Store, loosely covered, at room temperature.

title: marshmallow cream fruit dip
directions: Mix marshmallow cream and yogurt together.
Add cinnamon. Serve with fruit.

title: grandma's molasses popcorn balls
directions: Boil this mixture until a small amount forms a ball when dropped into cold water.
Pour over 4 quarts popped corn.
When cool enough to handle, butter hands and shape loosely into balls.

title: beef and vegetable oriental
directions: Cook and prepare rice.
Brown ground beef.
Cut each zucchini crosswise in thirds.
Cut each third lengthwise into thin slices. Cut green pepper into 1-inch pieces.
When beef is browned, add zucchini, green pepper, undiluted beef broth and ginger.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender crisp.
Blend cornstarch and soy sauce in cup; add this to simmering beef mixture, stirring constantly, until liquid is thickened.
Serve with rice.
Contains 350 calories per serving.

title: ham and cheese roll-ups
directions: Mix baking mix and water until dough forms.
Smooth into ball on cloth covered surface dusted with baking mix.
Knead 15 times. Roll into rectangle, 15 x 9-inch; spread with mustard.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Roll up tightly, beginning at 15-inch side.
Pinch edge into roll (moisten if necessary).
Wrap and refrigerate at least 30 minutes but no longer than 24 hours.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: I use Keebler cookie crust pie shell.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and water in saucepan.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; stir in gelatin.
Pour over peaches; mix well. Pour into pie shell and refrigerate until set.
When ready to serve, spread topping over all.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar thoroughly.
Beat egg yolks until thick. Blend in.
Mix fruit and nuts (chopped) with 1 cup flour.
Add to mixture.
Sift remaining 3 cups flour and baking powder together. Add in.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into mixture along with the lemon extract.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Cover with foil.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake in 250° oven on top rack with pan of water underneath for first 30 minutes, then remove water and continue baking until tests done.

title: italian bread
directions: Stir together in a large bowl the flour, yeast, sugar and salt.
Mix together the warm water and oil.
Add to flour-yeast mixture and beat well with electric beater.
Stir in 1 1/2 to 2 cups of flour.
Knead in 1/2 to 1 cup of flour.
Let rise 1 hour in oiled bowl.
Punch down. Shape into 2 loaves.
Let rise 1/2 hour.
Sprinkle cornmeal on pan and place bread into it.
After it rises, make slits.
Brush with beaten egg. Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake 30 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat egg yolks, cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Add corn, milk and butter.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole.
Set dish in a pan of hot water. Bake approximately 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: honey canned peaches or pears
directions: Blanch peaches or pears to get skins off.
Let stand in solution of 1 gallon
water, vinegar and salt for 20 minutes.
Mix honey and 4 cups water.
Bring to boil and cook for short time until good and hot.
Place drained fruit in sterilized jars; add syrup.
Put lids on; process in hot water bath for pints 25 minutes or for quarts 30 minutes.

title: oven baked beans
directions: Combine in casserole.
Bake in oven at 350°.

title: rainbow salad
directions: Pour 1 cup boiling water
over
lime
jello
and mix.
Add lemon juice.
Line bottom of
pan
with pineapple.
Place maraschino cherries in centers of pineapple.
Pour
in
lime jello mixture.
Let set until firm.
Pour 1 cup boiling water over
lemon
jello and mix.
Mix salad dressing with cream cheese and
add
to
slightly congealed lemon jello mixture and beat. Pour mixture
on
lime
jello.
When
it
begins
to congeal, pour 1 cup boiling water over strawberry jello.
Mix and add 1 cup cold water.
Add sliced bananas and when slightly set, pour next to center lemon mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients until tender.
Add milk, margarine and salt.
Cook 15 minutes.
Mash potatoes for a creamier soup. Ready to serve.

title: spanish rice
directions: In skillet, brown hamburger.
Add taco mix and tomato sauce. Simmer.
In another skillet, put 1 tablespoon oil.
Add rice.
Just heat, don't brown the rice.
Add water.
Simmer until water absorbs into the rice.
Mix meat and rice.
Makes 8 cups of Spanish rice.

title: barbecue chuck roast
directions: Combine and pour over meat. Bake at 350° until done; shred meat. Serve with mashed potatoes, rice or over a bed of noodles.

title: tacos
directions: Brown and drain the meat.
Add the remaining ingredients. Stir and simmer, uncovered, for 20 to 30 minutes.
This is now ready to build your tacos.
This will also freeze very well.

title: gumdrop bars
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Sift together the flour, powdered milk and salt.
Mix the sugar, shortening, egg and water well in a bowl.
Add the flour mixture. Stir in about 2/3 of the gumdrop mixture. Spread batter in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle rest of mixture over batter. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all together; cook in double boiler until thickens.

title: overnight salad
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients.
Mix next 2 ingredients.
Ice top of salad.
Sprinkle on thin layer of Parmesan cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Toss well before serving.
May top with egg slices, salad toppings, or bacon right before serving.

title: stuffed shells florentine
directions: Cook pasta in boiling water in a saucepan for 9 minutes; salt may be added if desired.
Drain immediately.
Cook spinach according to package directions; drain.
Add Ricotta cheese, egg and 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese to spinach; mix well.
Spoon into shells.
Spread half the spaghetti sauce in two 2-quart baking dishes.
Arrange filled shells in prepared dishes.
Pour remaining sauce on shells.
Sprinkle with shredded Mozzarella cheese and remaining Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: potato-cheese bread
directions: In small bowl, pour warm water, sugar and yeast.
Do not stir, but make sure each particle of yeast gets wet.
Wait 10 minutes until yeast is thick and foamy.
While waiting, in large bowl, mix milk, salt, egg, cheese, potatoes, 1 cup flour and shortening. Add yeast mixture and remaining flour, one cup at a time, until dough is easy to handle.

title: cinnamon ring roll(christmas coffee cake)
directions: Let milk cool to lukewarm and add yeast.
Stir with plastic spoon until dissolved.
Cream shortening and 2 tablespoons sugar. Add eggs.
Add milk mixture, salt and flour.
Mix.
Let rise in a warm place until doubled in bulk.
Punch down.
Pinch off pieces and roll in walnut size balls.
Dip in melted butter and roll in cinnamon and sugar mix.
Layer balls in a greased 10-inch tube pan.
Let rise about 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Turn onto tray.
Decorate with maraschino cherries and pecan halves.
(May freeze and reheat at a later date.)

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onion in margarine over medium heat.
Add meat and cook until brown.
Add flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add soup.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat thoroughly, but do not boil.
Sprinkle parsley. Serve over hot cooked noodles.
Serves 4.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients and stir well.
Place the chicken pieces in baking dish and pour sauce over.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Turn chicken and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Cook 10 minutes longer, uncovered, or until done.

title: quick chocolate frosting
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in double boiler.
Stir until blended.
Mix hot milk with sugar; blend into chocolate mixture and beat until smooth.
Stir vanilla and salt into chocolate mixture.
Beat until smooth and thickened, about 5 minutes.
Makes enough frosting for filling and topping a 9-inch double layer cake.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Combine all ingredients with mixer.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Pour on glaze when cake has cooled.

title: baked cauliflower(this is also good with broccoli!)
directions: Cook cauliflower in boiling salted water until done but not too soft.
Drain and place in a baking dish.
Melt butter; add flour and stir until blended.
Add milk and continue stirring. Add seasonings, green onions and pimento.
Pour over cauliflower. Top with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 375 degrees for about 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix 3 cans of soup thoroughly. Put chicken in bottom of casserole dish. Pour 3 combined soups over chicken. Melt margarine and stir into dressing mix and finish moistening with chicken broth. Spoon over the top of chicken and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together first five ingredients.
Sift together next four ingredients.
Add to first mixture, then add pie filling and mix well. Bake in loaf pans 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: halusky(small dumplings)
directions: After mixing dough, spread about 1/3 of the dough over a plate and scrape small chunks of dough into boiling salt water.
When dough rises to the top, let boil for about 3 minutes, drain and rinse.
Continue until all the dough is used up.

title: beef stew
directions: Cover and bake at 300° for 4 hours. Serve over rice.

title: lo-cal spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve in hollowed loaf of bread, surrounded by small bread squares for dipping.

title: simple and easy pie crusteverton, missouri
directions: Cut oleo into the flour.
Add milk and knead lightly.
Roll out on a floured board.
Makes 2 (9-inch) crusts.
Batch can be or tripled easily.

title: perfect raisin drop cookies
directions: Add water to raisins and boil 5 minutes.
Stir in the soda and let cool.
Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add raisins.
Sift other ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Drop by teaspoon on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: venison roast
directions: Heat soup, water
and
soup
mix
until smooth and well mixed. Line a 13 x
x	2-inch pan with heavy-duty foil and add meat and soup
mixture.	Bake in a 350° oven until tender. If too dry, add a small amount of hot water.

title: flo's apple crisp
directions: Place apples in greased shallow baking dish or pan, about 1 1/2-quart capacity.
Blend flour with sugar, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add egg and mix with fork until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sour rye bread
directions: Turn Sour Bread Starter into large mixing bowl and stir in the 2 cups water slowly until well blended.
Blend in 1 cup of rye flour and stir well.
Cover lightly and let stand in a warm place (about 85°) for 20 to 40 hours, depending on sourness.
Dissolve the yeast in 1/4 cup warm water, then stir into the soured mixture. Add salt and very gradually beat in the remaining rye flour.
Add the white flour, a little at a time, beating well after each addition.
When stiff dough is formed, let it rest in the bowl for about 10 to 15 minutes, then turn the dough out on a lightly floured board and knead until smooth.
Place the dough in a lightly greased bowl, turning to grease the top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled in bulk, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Turn the dough out onto a lightly floured board and divide it into 2 parts after reserving about 1/2 cup of the dough.
Store in covered container in the refrigerator for next baking.
Grease and flour pan; let rise again (very little) and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: aunt fanny's baked squash
directions: Note:
Salt and pepper may be increased.

title: crispy chicken
directions: In a shallow bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Place butter in another bowl.
Dip chicken in butter, then into cereal mixture. Place in a greased 11x7 baking pan.
Drizzle with remaining butter.
Bake uncovered at 400 degrees for 20-25 minutes or until juices run clear.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, green pepper and onion; drain.
Stir in pepper, tomato sauce and catsup.
Alternate layers of meat mixture and cheese in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Arrange biscuits around edge of casserole.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook onions and green peppers slowly in oleo until onions are done.
Add hamburger and saute until the mixture falls apart.
Add tomatoes, rice and seasonings.
Arrange in casserole.
Cover and bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes or until done.
Serves 8.

title: luncheon salad
directions: Heat soup to boiling.
Stir in gelatine until dissolved. Cool.
Add mayonnaise and cream cheese; blend until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spoon into 8 x 10-inch oiled mold. Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.

title: coconut custard
directions: Mix sugar and eggs.
Add milk and vanilla.
Put 1/2 of coconut in bottom of unbaked pie shell.
Pour in sugar and egg mixture. Top with remaining coconut.
Bake at 300° until done.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Brush pie crust with some egg white.
Bake at 375° for 4 minutes.
Cool.
Spoon pie filling into pie crust.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Place sliced potatoes in bottom of casserole dish.
Saute onion in butter.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat stirring constantly until bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Add milk and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Heat to boiling; stir constantly for 1 minute. Pour over potatoes.
Cook uncovered for 1 hour at 375°.
Mix remaining cheese and bread crumbs, sprinkle on top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes more.

title: buffet potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, eggs, pickles, onions and salt.
Mix with mustard and mayonnaise.
Chill thoroughly and serve on lettuce. Garnish with deviled eggs and tomatoes and top with mayonnaise. Serves 6.

title: citrus rice salad
directions: Drain oranges; mix juice, water, raisins and spices in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Stir in rice.
Return to boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; let stand 5 minutes.
Spread in shallow pan; freeze 10 minutes to quickly cool rice.
Toss with remaining ingredients.
Makes 5 cups or 8 servings.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Soften cream cheese and 1 stick
margarine to room temperature.
Blend cream cheese and margarine with 1 cup of plain flour, then divide into 24 balls and place in miniature muffin pans.
Flatten balls out to fit tins.

title: honey and spice chicken
directions: Place chicken in shallow baking dish.
Bake for 40 minutes. Mix ingredients.
Brush both sides with sauce.
Bake 30 minutes longer or until tender in 350° oven.

title: cherry jubilee cake
directions: In a large bowl, blend all ingredients except eggs.
Beat at medium speed for 1 minute.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat 1 minute after each addition.
Spread batter in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until cake tests done with a toothpick.
Cool right side up for about 15 minutes, then remove from pan.
Mix the powdered sugar, 6 maraschino cherries (chopped) and 2 tablespoons juice from cherries.
Pour over cake while still warm to make a glaze.

title: peach banana freeze
directions: Mash peaches and bananas until mushy.
Stir in lemonade. Combine cream and sugar and whip until thick and creamy.
Fold into peach and banana mixture.
Pour in 8-inch square dish and freeze until firm, stirring once or twice.

title: roast pork with thyme & mushroom sauce
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients and brush on roast.
Place in roasting pan fat side up.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 to 2 hours, basting occasionally.
Near end of roasting, mix together potatoes, carrots, and onion.
Toss vegetables with olive oil, vinegar, and salt.	Roast in pan with pork roast last 10 to 20 minutes of cooking time.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Put chicken in Dutch oven with enough boiling water to cover. Add salt and simmer for 45 minutes.
Add potatoes, onion, beans, tomatoes and sugar.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add corn, cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Season and add catsup or Worcestershire sauce.
Add butter and stir well.
Transfer to serving dish and serve hot.
Serves 4-6.

title: quick salad
directions: Cook bacon and let drain on paper towel.
Save grease.
Tear lettuce into pieces in a big bowl.
Mix 1 cup of mayo with sugar. Mix in enough bacon grease to make creamy.
Pour over lettuce. Crumble bacon in lettuce.
Now mix together.
It's delicious.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apple, nuts and Miracle Whip.
Toss.
Add raisins or maraschino cherries if desired.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in large rectangular pan.
Mix biscuit mix, milk and sugar.
Pour over butter.
Batter should just barely cover bottom of pan.
Pour peaches and juice over batter.
Bake at 325° until crust is brown.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches with juice into a 9 x 13 casserole dish. Mix other ingredients together in a bowl and pour over peaches. Bake at 350° for at least 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: black bean soup
directions: Heat olive oil.
Add onion and garlic for 5 minutes, stirring. Add other seasonings.
Cook, stirring for 1 minute more.
Add beans and broth and cook on low heat for 15 minutes.

title: english muffins
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in sugar, salt and butter.
Cool.
Measure water into large bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast; stir until dissolved. Add lukewarm milk mixture.
Add half of the flour; beat until smooth.
Stir in rest of flour.
Turn onto lightly floured board. Knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in buttered bowl and brush with butter.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.
Punch dough down and divide in half.
On board heavily sprinkled with cornmeal, roll out each half to thickness of 1/4-inch.
Cut into rounds with 3-inch cookie cutter.
Cover and let rest for 30 minutes.
Place on lightly greased, medium hot griddle, cornmeal side down.
Bake 15 minutes; turn and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: bean dip pizza
directions: Mix the sour cream, mayonnaise and seasoning packet together; set aside.
Layer ingredients on a large cake plate, starting with the bean dip and ending with the cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: divinity candy
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup and water thoroughly, then cook until it forms a medium ball when dropped in cold water (240°).
Pour 2/3 of syrup slowly over beaten egg whites, beating constantly.
Cook the other 1/3 of syrup until it forms a very firm ball (255°) then beat it slowly into the first mixture, beating constantly until creamy.
Add vanilla and nuts and drop onto waxed paper or pour into greased dish.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in margarine.
Combine peel, juice and egg; add to dry ingredients.
Mix just until moistened.
Fold in berries and nuts.
Bake at 350° for approximately 60 minutes in greased loaf pan.
Cool.
Wrap in foil.
Store overnight before cutting.
Makes 1 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf or 2 small pans.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Mix together flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
In a large mixing bowl mix shortening and sugar, add tomato soup (with baking soda), egg and vanilla.
Add flour mixture; mix well.
Pour into baking pans (greased and floured).

title: glazed baby carrots
directions: Cook carrots and drain.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add all ingredients and cook, stirring, for about 2 minutes until glazed.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Beat margarine, sugar and eggs until creamy.
Add dry ingredients. Chill dough.
Roll into balls.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon (2 teaspoons cinnamon and 2 teaspoons sugar).
Place on cookie sheet 1 inch apart.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: ham heroes
directions: Combine; spread on buns.
Wrap in Reynolds Wrap.
Store in refrigerator until time to use.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
